29febc3f-90a8-4d05-a580-a80f01d3ee52
Preheat the oven @350 degrees F. Grease a Bundt pan with butter and set aside.
29febc3f-90a8-4d05-a580-a80f01d3ee52
Combine dry ingredients Sift all-purpose flour, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in a large mixing bowl. Set aside.
29febc3f-90a8-4d05-a580-a80f01d3ee52
Combine wet ingredients Cream butter, orange zest, and sugar until light and fluffy. Scrape the sides of the bowl, so all of the butter-sugar mixtures is well mixed.
29febc3f-90a8-4d05-a580-a80f01d3ee52
Once the creaming process is completed and the mixture is a pale and light color, start blending the eggs into the mixture, one by one. Beat until fluffy. Add orange extract to the mixture and mix it well.
29febc3f-90a8-4d05-a580-a80f01d3ee52
Save one tablespoon of the flour mixture and add the remaining dry ingredients to the wet ingredients. Pour in buttermilk, orange juice, and mix until well blended. Run a spoon around the bowls edge and mix for one last time until all the flour has been incorporated well into the mixture.
29febc3f-90a8-4d05-a580-a80f01d3ee52
Dust cranberries with the saved 1 tablespoon of flour and mix.
29febc3f-90a8-4d05-a580-a80f01d3ee52
Assemble the cake Add cranberries, flour, and white chocolate to the batter. Fold the fruit and chocolate gently into the batter.
29febc3f-90a8-4d05-a580-a80f01d3ee52
Pour the batter into the greased pan. Top the batter with cranberries and white chocolate. Tap the Bundt pan gently on the counter a few times to release any trapped air.
29febc3f-90a8-4d05-a580-a80f01d3ee52
Bake the Cake Bake the cake in a preheated oven for 45-50 minutes or until the toothpick comes out clean. Remove from the oven and allow it to cook for 10 minutes in the pan.
29febc3f-90a8-4d05-a580-a80f01d3ee52
Run a butter knife around the cake edges. Gently remove the cake from the pan.
29febc3f-90a8-4d05-a580-a80f01d3ee52
To give the cake a festive look, decorate the cooled cake with a white chocolate drizzle and topped it with fresh orange zest and dried cranberries. Serve and enjoy!
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf ROAST VEGETABLES Preheat oven to 425 degrees F.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf ROAST VEGETABLES Rinse tomatoes and red bell pepper under tap water. Cut the peppers in half lengthwise, clean out the core and the seeds. Discard them. Slice tomatoes in halves.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf ROAST VEGETABLES On a greased baking tray, arrange the tomatoes and bell peppers in a single layer with the cut-side down.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf ROAST VEGETABLES Toss in garlic pods. Brush the tomatoes and bell pepper with oil and season with salt and pepper.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf ROAST VEGETABLES Bake them on the bottom shelf of the oven for 30 minutes.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf MAKING OF THE BISQUE Turn the Instant Pot to Saute mode. Once it displays hot, add oil to the insert. Add bay leaves and sauté for 1 minute. This way, the leaves will release more flavor.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf MAKING OF THE BISQUE Add chopped onions. Cook for 2-3 minutes until onions are soft and fragrant.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf MAKING OF THE BISQUE Add chopped carrots and cook for another 2 minutes. Toss in chopped zucchini and mix to combine.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf MAKING OF THE BISQUE Stir in the tomato puree. Add red chili flakes, rosemary, thyme, fresh basil leaves, and salt to the Instant Pot insert.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf MAKING OF THE BISQUE Pour in vegetable stock. Stir to combine. Add tamari and brown sugar. Mix until combined.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf MAKING OF THE BISQUE Finally, add the roasted bell peppers, garlic, and tomatoes to the insert.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf MAKING OF THE BISQUE Turn the Instant Pot off. Close the lid and seal the pot. Press the Manual or pressure cook button and cook the Instant Pot Butternut squash curry for 8 minutes on HIGH.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf MAKING OF THE BISQUE Once the cooking time has elapsed, turn off the Instant Pot. Allow the pressure to release naturally. When the pin drops, carefully open the lid. Just before you blend the bisque, remove the bay leaves and discard.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf MAKING OF THE BISQUE Blend the bisque using an immersion blender until smooth.
ac9cdd13-3e17-47e7-9b76-577f07d103bf MAKING OF THE BISQUE Once blended, do the taste test and adjust the spice level. Serve warm with some homemade garlic rolls and topped with fresh parsley leaves and pinenuts.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f BASIC GRAVY Melt butter over medium heat in a heavy-bottomed pan. Once the butter starts to melt, add chopped onions to the pan. Sauté until the onions turn translucent.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f BASIC GRAVY Add ginger and garlic to the onions. Sauté the ginger and garlic for 1-2 minutes or until fragrant.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f BASIC GRAVY Add cashews to this mix. Cook cashews for 2-3 minutes over medium heat, stirring intermittently.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f BASIC GRAVY No add chopped tomatoes to the pan. Sauté the tomatoes with onions + cashews. Lower the heat to the low setting and cover the pan. Allow the mixture to simmer over low heat until the tomatoes are soft and tender.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f BASIC GRAVY Once the tomatoes are soft, uncover the pan. Take it off the heat and allow the masala to cool.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f BASIC GRAVY Once cooled, transfer this mix to a blender. Puree the cooled masala in the blender until smooth and creamy. Set aside.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f ASSEMBLE PANEER BUTTER MASALA Heat a heavy-bottomed cooking pan or Kadai over medium heat. Add butter and oil to it. As the butter starts to melt, add bay leaf, cinnamon, green cardamom, black cardamom, and cloves to the pan.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f ASSEMBLE PANEER BUTTER MASALA Sauté for a few seconds until the whole spices are fragrant. Now add Kashmiri red chili powder to the whole spices.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f ASSEMBLE PANEER BUTTER MASALA Mix until fully combined. Do not cook for long or the chilies will burn. Next, add the butter gravy back to the pan. Mix until the sauce is fully blended.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f ASSEMBLE PANEER BUTTER MASALA Its time to season our masala. Add the coriander powder, turmeric, and salt to the masala. Stir around a while until the spices are well blended in the gravy.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f ASSEMBLE PANEER BUTTER MASALA Cook the mixture for 2-3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Now add the tomato paste and garam masala powder to the cooking gravy. Cook for another 1-2 minutes on medium heat. Keep stirring.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f ASSEMBLE PANEER BUTTER MASALA Now add water to the butter masala gravy. Depending on the consistency you like, add water slowly. If you prefer a thick gravy, add less water than recommended in the recipe.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f ASSEMBLE PANEER BUTTER MASALA By now, the masala will start to ooze oil from the sides. Add Kasoori methi to the cooking gravy; mix it well. Now, add our star ingredient paneer cubes to the gravy.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f ASSEMBLE PANEER BUTTER MASALA Gently mix the paneer into the gravy. Add cream to the gravy. Cover and allow the paneer butter masala to simmer for 4-5 minutes on low heat. After the time has elapsed, take the pan off the heat, and our delicious and creamy paneer butter masala is ready to be devoured.
1c8630e7-64c1-405b-af91-484e3344c10f GARNISH Transfer the paneer butter masala to a serving dish. Spoon the remaining cream over paneer, garnish with chopped cilantro leaves, and serve hot with warm tandoori roti or naan.
b649c455-ee12-4eae-b4a8-4d2183cd6af4
Combine all the ingredients listed under 'SALSA' in a bowl. Mix it well. Adjust the seasonings and set it aside.
b649c455-ee12-4eae-b4a8-4d2183cd6af4
Spread a layer of roasted red bell pepper hummus on each cracker.
b649c455-ee12-4eae-b4a8-4d2183cd6af4
Layer it with a cucumber slice.
b649c455-ee12-4eae-b4a8-4d2183cd6af4
Then add two teaspoons of black bean and corn salsa on top. Not too much, just two teaspoons. We dont want the salsa running off the bites.
b649c455-ee12-4eae-b4a8-4d2183cd6af4
Lastly, sprinkle the bites with chopped cilantro leaves. Repeat these steps with all the crackers, and thats it! You are all done.
b6931e96-392a-485f-8654-25eff30939f4 MAKE SUGAR MIXTURE Combine sugar and water in a pan.
b6931e96-392a-485f-8654-25eff30939f4 MAKE SUGAR MIXTURE Stir in eliachi powder and whisk to combine.
b6931e96-392a-485f-8654-25eff30939f4 MAKE SUGAR MIXTURE Bring this mixture to a boil, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves. Once done, remove the pot from heat and set aside.
b6931e96-392a-485f-8654-25eff30939f4 PREPARE ATTE KA HALWA Add ghee to a heavy-bottomed pan. Turn the heat to medium-low heat and allow the ghee to melt. Add wheat flour to the melted ghee.
b6931e96-392a-485f-8654-25eff30939f4 PREPARE ATTE KA HALWA Combine the flour and ghee. Mix until the mixture becomes crumbly.
b6931e96-392a-485f-8654-25eff30939f4 PREPARE ATTE KA HALWA Add another 2 tablespoons of ghee to the wheat flour.
b6931e96-392a-485f-8654-25eff30939f4 PREPARE ATTE KA HALWA After adding an extra 2 tablespoons of ghee, the flour mixture will become runny. That's the consistency we are looking at.
b6931e96-392a-485f-8654-25eff30939f4 PREPARE ATTE KA HALWA Keep stirring wheat flour until the color changes from light brown to a deep golden brown for about 8-10 minutes.
b6931e96-392a-485f-8654-25eff30939f4 PREPARE ATTE KA HALWA Once the flour turns deep brown in color, turn the gas dial to the lowest setting. Gradually add the water, stirring continuously to prevent the halwa from turning lumpy. Be very careful, as the water will splash all over as it hits the warm halwa.
b6931e96-392a-485f-8654-25eff30939f4 PREPARE ATTE KA HALWA Increase the heat to the medium-low setting and simmer the halwa, stirring constantly until the water evaporates and the halwa starts to thickens. (Do not leave the halwa unattended at this point.)
b6931e96-392a-485f-8654-25eff30939f4 PREPARE ATTE KA HALWA Once the halwa thickens, take it off the heat. Do not cook the halwa for long. Cooking longer will result in dry halwa.
b6931e96-392a-485f-8654-25eff30939f4 PREPARE ATTE KA HALWA Serve hot.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Heat the oven 15 minutes before baking.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION In a large mixing bowl, sift together all-purpose flour, salt, and baking powder. Make sure you spoon and level the flour from the container. Set aside.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION Combine sugar and butter in a separate mixing bowl. Beat the two until butter turns pale yellow, light, and fluffy.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION While beating the mixture, use a rubber spatula to scrape the bowls sides a couple of times.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION Add milk, yogurt, and vanilla essence to the sugar mix. Mix to combine.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION Add in the sifted dry ingredients and beat until a smooth batter forms. Do not over mix the batter.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION Add in the secret ingredients unsweetened applesauce. Gently fold the applesauce until incorporated. Be careful not to over mix the batter.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION Using a spatula, scrape the bowls bottom and sides and make sure everything is thoroughly combined and smooth.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION To prevent liners from sticking to cupcakes, spray them with nonstick cooking spray or brush with a little melted butter.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION Use an ice cream scoop and add the eggless vanilla cupcake batter to the lined cupcake pan. Fill each mold 2/3 of the way up with the batter. Give them some room to rise.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION After filling the cupcake liners with batter, tap the pan on the kitchen counter a couple of times. This tapping will help get rid of air bubbles. Do not let the batter-filled-cupcake-pan sit on the counter for long.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION Bake the eggless vanilla cupcakes in the preheated oven for about 18-20 minutes or until the toothpick comes out clean. Do not overbake. Overbaking will result in dry cupcakes.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION The baking time was 20 minutes for me. But every oven is different; therefore, keep a watchful eye on the cupcakes and make sure they dont burn.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION Remove from the oven and allow the cupcakes to cool for 10 minutes in the pan. After the resting time is over, remove the cupcakes from the pan. Cool them on a cooling rack.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION Allow the cupcakes to cool completely, before unwrapping the liner. Unwrap the liner and reveal the inner beauty.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION You can bake a cake out of this recipe. This cake is baked in a 8" x 1½" round cake pan. It's a thin cake pan; therefore, bake the cake for 30-35 minutes @ 350 degrees F.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION This recipe also bakes into a delicious 6-inch round cake.
8e42a511-4f2e-4480-a2a2-59e09ca16d07 CUPCAKE PREPARATION Bake for 40-45 minutes or until the toothpick comes out clean. This recipe has not been experimented with a 8 X 3 inch round cake pan.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
Rinse and soak chana dal for 30 minutes in lukewarm water. Set aside.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
After the resting time is over, drain the dal and rinse again . set aside.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
Start the Instant Pot in SAUTE mode and heat oil in it. Once the oil is hot, add cloves and bay leaves. As they start to crackle, add cumin seeds.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
Cook the cumin seeds for few seconds.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
Add chopped garlic to the insert. Cook for a minute.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
Add diced onions to the Instant Pot insert. Sauté for 2-3 minutes.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
Stir in the rinsed chana dal and cook for another 2 minutes. Stir in all the spices salt, red chili powder, and garam masala powder.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
Sauté the spices for a minute. Stir in rinsed rice. Cook the rice with the rest of the ingredients for a minute.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
Pour in water. Mix to combine.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
Seal the lid of the Instant Pot with the vent in the sealing position. Cancel the saute mode. Select the PRESSURE COOK OR MANUAL mode. Cook on high pressure for 4 minutes.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
After the instant pot beeps, let the rice rest for 4 minutes in its own steam then release the pressure (QPR quick pressure release). When the pin drops, carefully open the lid.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
Fluff the rice with a fork.
2c4cf88e-ffaf-4a52-85b2-2c19ef547868
Sprinkle some lemon juice and serve hot with your favorite raita.
80fdea1f-3f29-41bc-abc0-9737e8b2d150
Melt ghee in a heavy bottomed pan, and add milk powder.
80fdea1f-3f29-41bc-abc0-9737e8b2d150
Stir until the mixture looks crumbly. Maintain the heat at the medium-low setting.
80fdea1f-3f29-41bc-abc0-9737e8b2d150
Pour milk into this mixture and mix it well. Add milk slowly. The mixture will come together as a soft, elastic dough. If the mixture doesnt bind well, add another tablespoon of milk.
80fdea1f-3f29-41bc-abc0-9737e8b2d150
Add powdered sugar, pistachio essence, and stir to combine.
80fdea1f-3f29-41bc-abc0-9737e8b2d150
Keep stirring continuously, do not leave the mixture unattended at any time as it may burn. Keep stirring and soon the mixture will start to thicken.
80fdea1f-3f29-41bc-abc0-9737e8b2d150
Take it off the flame and allow it to cool slightly. Add Pistachios to the mixture. Mix to combine.
80fdea1f-3f29-41bc-abc0-9737e8b2d150
Pour it into a baking dish and generously sprinkle the remaining 2 tablespoons of crushed green pistachio pieces on top.
80fdea1f-3f29-41bc-abc0-9737e8b2d150
Allow the burfi to set (remain undisturbed) for 4-6 hours or overnight.
80fdea1f-3f29-41bc-abc0-9737e8b2d150
This decadent nutty pista burfi tastes amazing at room temperature.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 SOAK THE LENTILS Sort through the lentils to remove all the pebbles and gritty things.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 SOAK THE LENTILS Rinse the lentils and beans until tap water. Rub the grains in between your fingers to get rid of all the residues.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 SOAK THE LENTILS Transfer the rinsed lentils to a clean bowl. Soak the dal in enough water to cover the dal by about an inch. Make sure the grains are completely submerged in water. Soak the dal overnight.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 BOIL THE DAL After the soak time is over, drain the water completely. Rinse the soak dal thoroughly under tap water, drain. Now, transfer the dal to a pressure cooker.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 BOIL THE DAL Pour in water. Make sure the dal is completely submerged in water. Add salt and turmeric to Maa ki dal. Mix to combine.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 BOIL THE DAL Seal the pressure with the lid and pressure cook the dal for 12-14 whistles. Remove from heat and allow the steam to release naturally.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 BOIL THE DAL Carefully open the lid and check the dal. Take a Rajma between your fingers and apply gentle pressure; if it breaks easily, the dal is ready. With the help of a masher, gently split the dal.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Add butter to a large pan. As the butter heats up, add cumin seeds to the pan. Sauté for a minute.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Stir in ginger and garlic paste.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Sauté for a few seconds until the raw smell goes away. Maintain the heat at medium and keep stirring continuously as we dont want to burn the garlic.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Add chopped onions to the pan. Mix well.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Add degi mirch and Kashmiri red chili powder. Mix to combine.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Now, add chopped tomatoes. Keep stirring until the tomatoes break down and dissolve in the gravy.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Cook, stirring frequently until the oil separates from the masala.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Add tomato paste and mix. Tomato puree will lend our dal makhani gravy a smooth texture.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Mix it well. Stir in the spices coriander powder, garam masala powder, and salt. Mix to combine.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Now, add the boiled dal to the pan. Add ¾ cup of milk and lower the heat to the lowest setting.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Mix well. Allow the dal to simmer uncovered at the lowest setting for about an hour. Keep stirring occasionally to prevent the dal from burning or sticking to the bottom of the pan.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI After the dal has simmered for an hour, it will appear thick; add 3/4 cup of lukewarm water to the dal. You may need more, so add accordingly. Add cream.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Add kasoori methi and allow the dal makhani to simmer for another 5-10 minutes at the lowest setting.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 ASSEMBLE DAL MAKHANI Dal will have a velvety and creamy texture by now. Take it off the flame and cover it with a lid.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 FINAL TEMPERING Heat butter or ghee in a separate pan. As the butter heats up, add garlic paste to the pan. Sauté for a minute.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 FINAL TEMPERING Add Kashmiri chili powder to the pan. Mix well.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 FINAL TEMPERING Take the pan off the heat and pour this tadka over dal makhani. Mix until fully incorporated.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 DHUNGAR METHOD Heat 2 pieces of charcoal briquettes over direct heat until red hot.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 DHUNGAR METHOD With the help of tongs, carefully drop the burning charcoal into a steel bowl or Katori.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 DHUNGAR METHOD Drizzle two teaspoons of ghee on top of the charcoal.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 DHUNGAR METHOD The charcoal will start to emit smoke. Immediately cover the bowl with a glass lid and let the dal makhani soak in all that smoky flavors for about 3-4 minutes. After 4 minutes, remove the lid, carefully lift the hot bowl, and set aside.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 DHUNGAR METHOD Give the dal a final mix. Garnish dal makhni with butter and serve hot.
82bc2ae8-0135-4893-ac2d-c8a27270e376 DHUNGAR METHOD Dal makhni thickens as it cools; therefore, add more water to adjust it to the consistency you like.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Before you start working with Phyllo sheets, I would recommend setting up your work station first.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Get the wooden surface or chopping board ready, butter in a bowl, muffin pan, a kitchen towel, pastry brush, pizza cutter, and of course, thawed phyllo sheets as per package instructions.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Remove the phyllo sheets from the box. Unwrap one roll of phyllo dough and lay it flat on a clean surface. I am going to work with 6 sheets at a time.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Therefore, roll the remaining sheets. Wrap it in its plastic wrap and store the sheets back in the refrigerator.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS PROTIP The thicker the cup, the better. The thicker phyllo cup is capable enough to handle our Rasmalai mousse.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS To prevent drying and breaking the sheets, cover the sheets you are working on with a moist kitchen towel.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Melt butter in a microwavable bowl. Lay one sheet on a clean surface and brush the entire sheet with butter or oil. Be careful while working with the phyllo sheet, as it is very delicate and may break.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS PROTIP- You may have to hold the sheet from one end, as they are paper-thin sheets and may curl up while applying butter.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Uncover the second sheet and lay it on top of the buttered phyllo sheet. Press gently so that the sheets stick to each other.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Repeat the process cover the whole sheet with a thin layer of butter. Continue this process with the third, fourth, fifth, and sixth sheets.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Once you have a stack of 6 sheets, all buttered up, split them into two halves vertically.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Using a pizza cutter, cut the sheets into 6 squares horizontally. Depending on your preference, you can divide them into desired shapes square or a circle.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS PROTIP Keep the square slightly bigger than the muffin pan cavity.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Grease a muffin pan. Apply butter inside each mold of the muffin pan. Transfer a phyllo sheets square into the greased muffin pan. Gently press each square into the mold of a muffin pan.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Press the squares evenly around the edges to prevent air pockets. Poke a few tiny-sized holes at the bottom of each cup to let the steam escape.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Now that we have our phyllo cups set into the muffin pan, its time to bake them.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Bake at 350 degrees F for 10-12 minutes or until golden. Keep a watchful eye around 10 minutes as they burn easily.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Once done and beautifully baked, remove the phyllo cups from the oven. Let them cool for a few minutes, then remove them from the muffin pan.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Since the muffin pan was greased, the baked phyllo cups will slide out easily.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS For some reason, if they are stuck to the pans bottom, take a butter knife and give the phyllo cups a slight push; it will come out effortlessly.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe BITE-SIZED PHYLLO CUPS Bite-sized phyllo cups are ready to be filled.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MIX Combine milk powder, confectioners sugar, cardamom powder, and pistachio powder in a mixing bowl.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MIX Mix until combined. Make sure you break all the lumps. Set aside.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE Take 1 cup of heavy whipping cream in a cup. Add agar-agar powder.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE Add rasmalai mix to the cream.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE Whisk it well into the cream, making sure there are no lumps in the mixture. Set aside.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE Pour the remaining 1 cup cream into a large mixing bowl.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE Now, strain the rasmalai mix through the strainer.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE Push the rasmalai mix liquid through the strainer with a spoon. Discard the chunks left behind.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE Whisk the heavy whipping cream and rasmalai mix with an electric whisk or stand mixer at medium speed.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE The mixture will start to get frothy and bubbly. Add confectioners sugar and cornstarch at this point. Keep whisking for another 2-3 minutes.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE After 4-5 minutes into the beating, the mixture will start to thicken. Once it appears thick, add cardamom essence to the rasmalai cream.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE Increase the speed to medium-high and beat for an additional 1 minute. Your rasmalai cream will start to look all puffy, and the whisking marks from the balloon whisk will be quite distinct.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE To double-check that your rasmalai mousse is done, remove the which and hold it upside down. If the mousse stays stiff without dropping, its all done.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE But if the mousse falls of the attachment, then beat it for another 15-30 seconds until the stiff peaks form.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE Add the toasted saffron to the rasmalai mousse. For toasted saffron, see the notes below.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe RASMALAI MOUSSE Fold it gently into the mousse. As so start folding, saffron will impart a rich deep yellow color to our mousse.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe ASSEMBLING RASMALAI MOUSSE PHYLLO CUPS Once blended, transfer the mousse into a piping bag. To do that, insert your nozzle into the piping bag, fill the bag with rasmalai mousse. Squeeze the piping bag a little to remove any air bubble.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe ASSEMBLING RASMALAI MOUSSE PHYLLO CUPS Fill each phyllo cups with swirls of rasmalai mousse. Garnish each phyllo cups with rasmalai wedge chopped nuts, and rose petals.
5d8034ee-1e8d-4610-a29d-435af21c8cfe ASSEMBLING RASMALAI MOUSSE PHYLLO CUPS Repeat the process with the rest of the phyllo cups and serve immediately.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff PREPARING CORN CROQUETTES Before you progress with the recipe: thaw just ONE puff pastry sheet at room temperature for at least 30 minutes.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff PREPARING CORN CROQUETTES While the pastry sheets are thawing, lets prepare the corn croquettes. Gather your ingredients Add corn kernels, frozen peas, and carrots to the food processor.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff PREPARING CORN CROQUETTES Pulse until the mixture looks like coarse breadcrumbs. The mixture should look coarse, not smooth, or paste-like. Therefore, take precautions and pulse in increments until you reach the desired texture.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff PREPARING CORN CROQUETTES In a large bowl, combine the corn-peas-carrot mixture with mashed potatoes. Mix until incorporated. Add chopped onions and green chilies. Mix in chopped cilantro.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff PREPARING CORN CROQUETTES Stir in all the seasonings cumin seeds, paprika, salt, and pepper. You can taste the mixture at this stage and adjust the seasonings if needed.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff PREPARING CORN CROQUETTES Stir in breadcrumbs. Mix until all the ingredients are evenly mixed.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff PREPARING CORN CROQUETTES The combined mixture should feel dry, not sticky. Grease your palms with oil and shape the mixture into croquettes. Place the croquettes on a plate and allow to rest in the refrigerator for 20 minutes.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff PREPARING CORN CROQUETTES Arrange these croquettes in a single layer in the air fryer.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff PREPARING CORN CROQUETTES Bake @375 degree F for 10-12 minutes, turning them about halfway through cooking. Bake until the croquettes are slightly golden brown and crispy. Remove from airfryer and set them aside to cool.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff ASSEMBLING HALLOWEEN CORN CROQUETTES Time to assemble. Unfold the thawed pastry sheet and place it on a lightly flour-dusted surface.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff ASSEMBLING HALLOWEEN CORN CROQUETTES Using a rolling pin, flatten out the dough into a big square.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff ASSEMBLING HALLOWEEN CORN CROQUETTES Start preheating your oven @350 degree F.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff ASSEMBLING HALLOWEEN CORN CROQUETTES Using a pizza cutter, cut the puff pastry sheet lengthwise into 1/4 inch strips. You will end up with 38-40 thin strips. You will need 4 strips in total on each croquette.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff ASSEMBLING HALLOWEEN CORN CROQUETTES Stretch and wrap 3 strips on the bottom part of each corn croquettes. Leave some space in between for the eyes and cover the last strip on the top, making it look like a bandana (headscarf).
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff ASSEMBLING HALLOWEEN CORN CROQUETTES Repeat the process with the rest of the croquettes. Secure the end of the last strip by pinching the dough together to secure the strip if necessary.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff ASSEMBLING HALLOWEEN CORN CROQUETTES Arrange the wrapped corn croquettes mummies on a greased baking tray and brush them all with oil.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff ASSEMBLING HALLOWEEN CORN CROQUETTES Bake the corn croquettes mummies, in the preheated oven. At 375 degrees F for 14 -16 minutes or until golden brown.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff ASSEMBLING HALLOWEEN CORN CROQUETTES Brush the freshly-baked croquettes with melted butter and allow the corn croquettes mummies to cool.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff ASSEMBLING HALLOWEEN CORN CROQUETTES Time to attach the eyes to these mummies. I have used a dab of vegan mayo to stick the edible eyeballs to my corn croquettes.
9c522924-73dd-429a-952d-c5ebdaeae3ff ASSEMBLING HALLOWEEN CORN CROQUETTES Serve these Halloween corn croquette with green chutney or tomato ketchup.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 PREPARE SABUDANA PEARLS Transfer sabudana to a bowl and wash thoroughly under tap water. Drain it completely. Next, add just enough water to cover the sabudana.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 PREPARE SABUDANA PEARLS ALWAYS use a 1:1 ratio to soak sabudana as we do for sabudana khichdi. Allow it to soak for 4-5 hours or until the sabudana pearls are soft enough to break when pressed between your index finger and thumb.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 PREPARE SABUDANA PEARLS By now, sabudana must have soaked up all the water, but still, drain to allow any excess moisture to drain away. Set the soaked sabudana pearls aside.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 TOAST THE PEANUTS Heat a large pan over medium heat. Once the pan is hot, add peanuts in a single layer. Do not add any oil. They have enough fat on their own.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 TOAST THE PEANUTS Keep stirring the peanuts frequently until they are slightly golden brown. Remove from the stove and allow it to cool comfortably.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 TOAST THE PEANUTS Now rub the peanuts between your hands and gently blow air into the pan to separate the peanuts skin.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 TOAST THE PEANUTS Transfer the peanuts to a grinder and grind until the peanuts resemble-like breadcrumbs.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 ASSEMBLE SABUDANA VADAS Place soaked sabudana in a large mixing bowl. Add mashed potatoes, ground peanuts, cilantro leaves, green chilies, salt, red chili powder, and cumin powder. Mix until everything is well combined.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 ASSEMBLE SABUDANA VADAS Fold it gently; take care not to break or mash the sabudana pearls.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 SHAPE THE VADAS Grease your hands with oil. Take 3 tablespoons of sabudana mixture in your hands. Roll the mix into a ball and then gently flatten the sabudana ball.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 SHAPE THE VADAS Place it on a clean plate. Repeat the process with the remaining mixture until all the vadas are formed.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 SHAPE THE VADAS Or spread the mixture out on the counter and cut them like round patties/cutlets.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 FRY THE VADAS Heat oil in a frying pan. Once the oil is hot enough for frying, drop 3-4 vadas in the pan, do not overcrowd the pan.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 FRY THE VADAS Fry the vadas at a low heat setting, turning them frequently until golden brown. Once done, remove the vadas from oil and drain on a kitchen paper towel.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 COOK VADAS IN A PAN Heat and grease a nonstick pan on a medium flame.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 COOK VADAS IN A PAN Transfer cutlets/patties onto the hot pan and cook until evenly brown on both sides turning occasionally.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 COOK VADAS IN APPE PAN Heat the appe pan/Ebleskiver pan on medium-low heat. Add a free drop of oil in each round mold. Place the sabudana vada in each mold, and cook covered for 4-5 minutes.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 COOK VADAS IN APPE PAN Once the bottom side is brown, flip and cook from the other side too until crisp and golden. Depending on the side of the vadas, they may take longer to cook.
e8e4d2c1-6c3d-4574-8bee-7d679ac4c898 COOK VADAS IN APPE PAN Serve with your favorite chutney and enjoy these delicious and tasty cutlets/patties!!
0d4de976-9ca2-4b3e-8d3c-bd79729e2087
Heat coconut oil in a pan.
0d4de976-9ca2-4b3e-8d3c-bd79729e2087
Add makhane/lotus seeds to the pan.
0d4de976-9ca2-4b3e-8d3c-bd79729e2087
Cook them over medium heat until they become light brown in color and brittle, stirring occasionally. This may take 7-8 minutes.
0d4de976-9ca2-4b3e-8d3c-bd79729e2087
PRO TIP Make sure foxnuts/ makhane are crispy and brittle before you move on to the next step. If makhane is not brittle they will turn soggy as soon as we add jaggery to it.
0d4de976-9ca2-4b3e-8d3c-bd79729e2087
Cook for 1-2 minutes. To check if the seeds are thoroughly cooked, press them in between fingers and it should feel hard and brittle. Take it off the flame.
0d4de976-9ca2-4b3e-8d3c-bd79729e2087
Meanwhile, combine jaggery with 3 tablespoons of water and boil until thick.
0d4de976-9ca2-4b3e-8d3c-bd79729e2087
Keep stirring continuously, and jaggery will stick onto the makhana/fox nuts.
0d4de976-9ca2-4b3e-8d3c-bd79729e2087
Allow it to cool completely. Store in an airtight container, and it will stay good for 2-3 weeks.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 MARINATE PANEER CUBES Slice paneer into cubes. If you prefer smaller paneer pieces, you can slice the paneer into small cubes or even bite-sized pieces.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 MARINATE PANEER CUBES Combine yogurt in a large mixing bowl. Whisk until smooth and lump-free. Add degi mirch, salt, coriander powder, turmeric, lemon juice, ginger, and garlic paste to the bowl.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 MARINATE PANEER CUBES Now add mustard oil along with kasoori methi to the marinade.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 MARINATE PANEER CUBES Whisk it well until combined. Do the taste test. Adjust the seasonings if needed.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 MARINATE PANEER CUBES Add paneer cubes to the marinade.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 MARINATE PANEER CUBES Cover with a plastic wrap and marinade paneer for 20 minutes in the refrigerator.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 PREPARE PIZZA DOUGH Meanwhile, combine instant yeast, salt, and flour in a large mixing bowl. Mix to combine.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 PREPARE PIZZA DOUGH Attach the dough attachment to the stand mixer and give the dry ingredients a good mix for 5 seconds on low speed.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 PREPARE PIZZA DOUGH Now pour in olive oil and start mixing the dough at low speed. Gradually add water to the dough.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 PREPARE PIZZA DOUGH Once all the water is added, increase the speed and mix until a soft dough forms.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 PREPARE PIZZA DOUGH Grease the Instant Pot insert. Transfer the dough to the Instant Pot. Cover it with a glass lid.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 PREPARE PIZZA DOUGH Turn the Instant pot on by pressing the Yogurt button. Adjust the pressure to Less. Set the timer to 20 minutes.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 GRILL PANEER CUBES While the dough is proofing, lets grill our paneer. Transfer the marinated paneer to the insert of an airfryer.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 GRILL PANEER CUBES Spray the pieces with oil and bake them at 300 degrees F for 5-6 minutes, turning them halfway during cooking.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 GRILL PANEER CUBES Once all the cubes are cooked, set them aside.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 GRILL PANEER CUBES Once the dough proofed, gently punch it down to flatten it. Remove the dough from the instant pot insert.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 ASSEMBLE PANEER TIKKA PIZZA Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F for 20 minutes.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 ASSEMBLE PANEER TIKKA PIZZA Transfer the dough onto a greased baking pan/tray and lightly stretch the dough outwards using your fingers tips.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 ASSEMBLE PANEER TIKKA PIZZA Grease your fingers tips with oil and keep pushing and working on the dough until it reaches the edges of the pan. The finished pizza dough will be 14"-16" in diameter.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 ASSEMBLE PANEER TIKKA PIZZA Prick the base of the pizza with a fork to avoid puffing up like naan.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 ASSEMBLE PANEER TIKKA PIZZA Layer the pizza with the pizza sauce first, followed by the fresh mozzarella cheese.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 ASSEMBLE PANEER TIKKA PIZZA PROTIP Do not spreadthe sauce on the edges. Leave the edges bare with nosauce.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 ASSEMBLE PANEER TIKKA PIZZA Now add the topping to the pizza sliced onions, bell peppers, and grilled paneer cubes. Sprinkle Italian herb seasoning on top. Brush the edges with some olive oil.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 ASSEMBLE PANEER TIKKA PIZZA Now, bake the pizza in the preheated oven at 425 degrees F for 18-20 minutes or until the cheese is all melted and the crust is golden brown.
7147893a-18b0-4105-9710-565d7d874c96 ASSEMBLE PANEER TIKKA PIZZA Once baked, remove the pizza from the oven. Cut into slices and serve hot.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
Turn the Instant Pot on to SAUTE mode. Add oil.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
As the Instant pot insert heats up, add bay leaf and garlic paste to the insert. Sauté for a few minutes.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
Add onions to the insert. Sauté for 3-4 minutes or until onions are translucent.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
Next, add diced carrots and celery to the insert and mix well. Sauté for 2-3 minutes.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
Then add diced tomatoes and marinara sauce to the insert. Mix it well.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
Remember to deglaze the bottom of the inner pot to avoid the burn message.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
Now add Italian seasoning, red chili flakes, and salt to the insert. Mix to combine.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
Add white cannellini beans and pour in vegetable stock.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
Finally, add raw ditalini pasta to the inner pot. Seal the Instant pot with its lid and set the valve to SEALING. Press the CANCEL button.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
Press pressure cook/Manual on the front panel and adjust the time to 4 minutes on HIGH pressure. The display will read as ON until the IP comes to pressure. This will take about 10-12 minutes.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
Once the cooking time has elapsed, your Instant Pot will beep, allow the Instant pot to sit. Let the pressure release naturally for 5 minutes. Then release the steam by carefully turning the valve to VENTING. This will quick-release the remaining steam.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
Once the instant pot pin drops, carefully open the lid. Add fresh spinach leaves.
fd4b6420-193a-4c14-9473-2fd70c740d76
Mix it well. Spinach leaves will wilt soon in the soup. Spoon the soup in a large bowl, garnish with grated parmesan cheese and serve warm.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Preheat oven @350 degree F.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Brush a 9×5 inch baking pan with butter. Set aside.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Combine tutti frutti and flour in a bowl. Toss it well to combine.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Pass the tutti frutti through a strainer to shake off the excess. Set aside.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Combine flour, baking powder, cornstarch, baking soda in a large mixing bowl. Sift the dry ingredients together. Set aside.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Combine oil and sugar in a separate bowl. Using a hand mixer, beat sugar and oil until thoroughly combined.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Pour in milk and almond extract. Add milk in batches. With an electric mixer, mix on low speed.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Spoon in flour mixture and mix until just combined.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Scrape down the sides of the bowl to ensure that the batter is evenly combined. Add dusted tutti frutti to the batter. Fold in gently and do not overmix.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Pour the batter in the prepared greased pan. Using a spatula, spread the batter evenly in the pan. Now, sprinkle some more tutti frutti over the top of the batter.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Bake for 45- 50 minutes to an hour or until the toothpick comes out clean.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Remove the cake from the oven. Let it rest in the pan for 5-10 minutes. After that, run a butter knife around the edges of the cake to loosen it from the sides of the baking pan.
3ead4fc0-fe5f-4524-b592-8246622a4924
Carefully flip the cake onto a clean plate. Let the cake cool completely before slicing.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 MAKE TEH DOUGH Combine flour, baking soda, sugar, and salt in a large mixing bowl.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 MAKE TEH DOUGH Add yogurt and mix until it resembles coarse crumbs.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 MAKE TEH DOUGH Pour in milk and knead until the dough starts to come together. Do not add all the milk at once.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 MAKE TEH DOUGH Add ghee and knead again until the mixture forms a soft, pliable dough.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 MAKE TEH DOUGH Cover the kneaded dough with a damp towel. Let the dough rest for 30 minutes in a warm, draft-free environment.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 PREPARE THE FILLING Combine paneer and mashed potatoes in a large mixing bowl. Add onions, red chili powder, coriander powder, amchur powder, cumin powder, garam masala powder, and salt.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 PREPARE THE FILLING Stir in chopped cilantro leaves and mix until all the ingredients are well blended. Set aside.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN After the resting time is over, knead the dough for 2-3 minutes. Transform the dough onto a clean, flour-dusted surface. Knead and roll until smooth.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN Roll it like a log. Divide the log into 6 equal pieces for large Chur Chur naan.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN Roll each piece into a ball.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN Cover the dough balls with a damp cloth and let it rest for another 20 minutes.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN After the rest time, roll the dough ball into a big round using a rolling pin. Roll the dough as thin as possible. Brush the rolled dough surface with ghee.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN Starting from one end, begin folding the rolled out dough. Continue folding the dough like an accordion style until you have reached the end.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN Take the pleated dough and stretch it a little. Now, starting from one end, begin rolling the dough into a pinwheel.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN Continue until you have reached the end. Press and secure the ends.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN Repeat the process with the remaining dough balls. To prevent drying, keep the rolled-out dough balls covered with a damp cloth all the time.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN Take a dough ball, and flatten it using your hands. Place 2 tablespoons of paneer-potato filling in the center of the dough circle.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN Bring all the sides together and seal the circle with the filling.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN Dust the surface with some flour. Now, using your hands, spread the dough into a 4-5 round.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 SHAPE THE NAAN Spread some chopped cilantro leaves on top. While you are spreading the dough with your fingers, press the leaves onto the dough.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 COOK THE PANEER CHUR CHUR NAAN Heat a heavy-based pan on medium heat. Apply some water to the other side of the paneer naan and place the naan onto the heated tawa (water side down). Press the naan onto the tawa so that it sticks to the tawa.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 COOK THE PANEER CHUR CHUR NAAN Cook the naan until the little bubbles start to appear on the surface of the naan.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 COOK THE PANEER CHUR CHUR NAAN Flip the tawa over direct flame. Lower the flame to medium-low and then cook the paneer naan over the direct flame, without burning.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 COOK THE PANEER CHUR CHUR NAAN Cook the naan until evenly brown from all sides.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 COOK THE PANEER CHUR CHUR NAAN Once down, gently squeeze the paneer naan to give it that chur chur texture. Apply ghee over the Paneer chur chur naan and serve hot.
f1033491-1c5e-4c70-9275-3215fea32ee0 COOK THE PANEER CHUR CHUR NAAN Cook the remaining naan in the same manner and keep the cooked chur chur naan covered at all times as you cook the rest. Serve warm with your favorite curry or raita.
3ccc5b2c-bfd5-42bc-a3ec-eac42c8f6f44 PREPARE TOASTED CHICKPEAS Preheat oven at 400 degrees F.
3ccc5b2c-bfd5-42bc-a3ec-eac42c8f6f44 PREPARE TOASTED CHICKPEAS In a large bowl, combine boiled and drained chickpeas with olive oil, onion powder, garlic salt, cajun seasoning, and dried parsley.
3ccc5b2c-bfd5-42bc-a3ec-eac42c8f6f44 PREPARE TOASTED CHICKPEAS Toss to coat. Arrange the seasoned chickpeas on a greased baking tray.
3ccc5b2c-bfd5-42bc-a3ec-eac42c8f6f44 PREPARE TOASTED CHICKPEAS Bake in a preheated oven on the lowest rack setting for 10-15 minutes until crispy- turning over once. Once done, remove from the oven and set aside.
3ccc5b2c-bfd5-42bc-a3ec-eac42c8f6f44 PREPARE STUFFED BELL PEPPERS Preheat your oven to 375 degrees F. Cook the quinoa according to package instructions.
3ccc5b2c-bfd5-42bc-a3ec-eac42c8f6f44 PREPARE STUFFED BELL PEPPERS While the chickpeas are cooking, lets prepare the peppers. Wash the bell peppers. Slice the peppers in half lengthwise and discard the seeds and membranes from the inside of the peppers. Spray the inside of bell peppers with oil and sprinkle some salt and pepper. Set them aside.
3ccc5b2c-bfd5-42bc-a3ec-eac42c8f6f44 PREPARE STUFFED BELL PEPPERS In a large bowl, combine quinoa, chickpeas, green chilies, cheese, cilantro, cumin, garlic salt, onion powder, chili powder, salt, pepper, and lemon juice. Mix until all ingredients are combined.
3ccc5b2c-bfd5-42bc-a3ec-eac42c8f6f44 PREPARE STUFFED BELL PEPPERS Spoon the quinoa and roasted chickpea filling into each bell pepper groove.
3ccc5b2c-bfd5-42bc-a3ec-eac42c8f6f44 PREPARE STUFFED BELL PEPPERS Arrange the stuffed bell peppers in a 9×13 inch baking dish and generously sprinkle each bell pepper with extra cheese. Cover the peppers with aluminum foil.
3ccc5b2c-bfd5-42bc-a3ec-eac42c8f6f44 PREPARE STUFFED BELL PEPPERS Transfer the baking tray to the oven and cook for about 45 minutes or until the peppers are tender and the cheese is all melted and bubbly.
3ccc5b2c-bfd5-42bc-a3ec-eac42c8f6f44 PREPARE STUFFED BELL PEPPERS Garnish with chopped cilantro leaves, spring onions, and serve immediately.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd GRILL THE CORN Turn the grill on. Place the corn on the hot grill.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd GRILL THE CORN Cook the corn over the hot grill for 8-10 minutes per side or until done, turning frequently.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd GRILL THE CORN Once the corn has charred, allow it to cool until comfortable enough to handle. Once its cooled, hold the corn cob vertically on a plate. Using a sharp knife cut down on the corn and slice the kernels off the cob. Set the corn kernels aside.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd MAKING OF THE SOUP Turn the Instant Pot to Saute mode. Once it displays hot, add oil to the insert. Add cloves, peppercorns, and bay leaf and sauté for 1 minute. This way, the whole spices will release more flavor.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd MAKING OF THE SOUP Add chopped onions. Cook for 2-3 minutes until onions are soft and fragrant.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd MAKING OF THE SOUP Add diced carrots and cook for another 2 minutes.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd MAKING OF THE SOUP Stir in all the spices turmeric, cumin powder, salt, and garlic powder. Mix to combine. Now add grilled corn kernels to the Instant pot insert.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd MAKING OF THE SOUP Pour in milk and water to the cooking corn mixture. Stir until combined.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd MAKING OF THE SOUP Turn the Instant Pot off. Close the lid and seal the pot. Press the Manual or pressure cook button and cook the Instant Pot Makai Ka Shorba (Spiced Corn Soup) for 6 minutes on HIGH.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd MAKING OF THE SOUP Once the cooking time has elapsed, turn off the Instant Pot. Allow the pressure to release naturally. When the pin drops, carefully open the lid.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd MAKING OF THE SOUP Just before you blend the bisque, remove the bay leaf and discard.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd MAKING OF THE SOUP Blend the shorba using an immersion blender until smooth and creamy.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd MAKING OF THE SOUP PROTIP If you like a chunky shorba, you can just give a few swirls of the immersion blender, rather than blending it smooth. For a creamy consistency, blend the shorba until it reaches a sauce-like consistency. Add 1/4 cup of water and bring it to a boil again.
497e3054-e85c-46d4-a172-d5a6e3565cfd MAKING OF THE SOUP Sprinkle lemon juice. Garnish with sweet corn kernels, cilantro leaves, and be prepared for everyone lining up for seconds.
3bd9acb4-4da6-4f3d-a5a3-07b86d0fc364
Before you begin with this recipe, make sure you rinse your greens thoroughly under cold water to get rid of all the gritty things.
3bd9acb4-4da6-4f3d-a5a3-07b86d0fc364
Dry it in-between layers of paper towels and add it to the food processor.
3bd9acb4-4da6-4f3d-a5a3-07b86d0fc364
Add the rest of the ingredients toasted pinenuts, garlic, salt, black pepper, nutritional yeast, and lemon juice to a food processor.
3bd9acb4-4da6-4f3d-a5a3-07b86d0fc364
Blend on HIGH until it forms a paste.
3bd9acb4-4da6-4f3d-a5a3-07b86d0fc364
Now, pour in olive oil, a few drizzles at a time, and PULSE in 5-8 seconds burst. Add olive oil steadily. Scrape the sides at regular intervals.
3bd9acb4-4da6-4f3d-a5a3-07b86d0fc364
Continue blending until the desired texture is attained. The finished pesto should have the consistency of a creamed butter smooth and creamy.
3bd9acb4-4da6-4f3d-a5a3-07b86d0fc364
If you find the basil pesto dry, add an extra tablespoon of EVOO to achieve the consistency you like. Taste and adjust the seasonings.
3bd9acb4-4da6-4f3d-a5a3-07b86d0fc364
Feel free to add an extra teaspoon of nutritional cheese for a cheesy flavor.
3bd9acb4-4da6-4f3d-a5a3-07b86d0fc364
Homemade basil pesto stores well covered in the refrigerator for up to a week.
3bd9acb4-4da6-4f3d-a5a3-07b86d0fc364
Dont forget to drizzle a thin layer of olive oil on top of the container. This will prevent discoloration.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922
Clean and wash the chicken pieces thoroughly under tap water. Drain the water completely.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922
Transfer chicken to a large mixing bowl and add lemon juice. Rub the juice all over the chicken. Add ginger and garlic paste.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922
Then, add all the spices degi mirch, coriander powder, turmeric powder, garam masala powder, salt, and fried onions. You can add fresh cilantro leaves and mint leaves to the marinade too. Add yogurt to the spice mix.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922
Mix and roll the chicken to coat in the marinade.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922
Cover and allow it to rest for an hour.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 MAKING OF BIRISTA- FRIED ONIONS Combine onions and cornstarch in a large bowl. Toss to coat cornstarch all over the onion rings.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 MAKING OF BIRISTA- FRIED ONIONS Heat oil in a pan. Dust of the excess cornstarch and add a small batch of onion rings to the hot oil. When the oil is hot, add the onions. Never add the onions to cold oil; they will not become crispy. Fry the onions for 9-10 minutes or until deep golden brown. Remove from oil and drain on a kitchen paper towel. Repeat the process with the rest of the onions.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 MAKING OF BIRISTA- FRIED ONIONS Fried onions are ready for biryani. Fried onions will stay good for a month in the refrigerator.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 MAKING OF BIRISTA- FRIED ONIONS Lets move on to the next step. Add milk to a microwave-safe bowl. Heat the milk for 40 seconds. Remove from the microwave and add saffron strands to the milk. Stir until combined and set aside.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 PREPARING RICE While the chicken is marinating, rinse the rice under tap water until the water runs clear. Soak rice for 15 minutes.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 PREPARING RICE In a wide dutch oven, add water and bring it to a boil. Season it with salt, black cardamom, cloves, and bay leaves. The ratio of rice to water should be 1:3, meaning 1 cup of rice and 3 cups of water. Drain and rinse the rice again. Add the drained rice to the boiling water.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 PREPARING RICE Gently mix the rice and parboil it for 4-6 minutes in hot water. The rice should be 70% cooked, meaning when pressed in between the fingers in breaks with slight pressure. If it breaks instantly when pressed, then you have overcooked the rice. Do not proceed with this rice as you will end up with sticky biryani.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 PREPARING RICE Once the rice is parboiled, turn the heat off. Remove the rice in the strainer.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 COOK THE CHICKEN Heat ghee in a heavy-bottomed dutch oven. Add whole black cardamom, peppercorns, cinnamon stick, bay leaves, star anise, mace, and shahi jeera.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 COOK THE CHICKEN Cook the whole spices for a few seconds. Add sliced onions to the spices. Cook until the onions are lightly golden in color.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 COOK THE CHICKEN Add marinated chicken to the pan.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 COOK THE CHICKEN Mix to combine and cook chicken on medium-low heat for 7-8 minutes. The yogurt in the marinade will release its water. Dont worry; we will use these juices to layer our biryani.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 COOK THE CHICKEN Add kasoori methi to the chicken and take it off the flame.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 COOK THE CHICKEN Now, layer the parboiled rice on top of the chicken. Spread it evenly all over the chicken. The chicken should be covered with a generous layer of rice.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 COOK THE CHICKEN Pour saffron milk all over the rice. Saffron adds a nice yellow touch to the final dish.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 COOK THE CHICKEN Add mint leaves.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 COOK THE CHICKEN Generously add fried onions or birista all over the biryani. Finally, layer it with cilantro leaves. For that rich buttery taste, add ghee on top of all that layering.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 COOK THE CHICKEN Place a heavy lid over the pan. Seal the lid and pan with kneaded dough. Turn the heat on and cook the biryani for 2-3 minutes on high heat. After that, lower the heat to the lowest setting and let the biryani simmer for 10-12 minutes.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 COOK THE CHICKEN Once the cooking time is over, turn the flame off. Allow the rice to rest in its own steam for 4-5 minutes. Carefully remove the dough seal from all around the pan.
0fe2a7e1-7f7b-4cf6-abd3-dbfd3bc66922 COOK THE CHICKEN Its time to lift the lid. Gently fluff the rice with a spatula. Hidden underneath the rice, you will discover tender, juicy pieces of chicken bursting with fantastic flavor from all the spices and herbs.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Preheat the oven to 330 degrees F.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Grease an 8-inch round springform baking pan. Set aside.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Combine sugar and butter in a large mixing bowl. Using a handheld beater, cream butter, and sugar together until light in color and fluffy.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Next, add mawa to the creamed sugar-butter mixture. Beat the mixture until smooth and creamy.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Now, add yogurt to the mawa mixture. Mix until combined.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Add baking powder. Mix it well. Make sure to scrape the sides of the bowl regularly.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Add fine sooji to this mix. Beat until smooth and well blended.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Slowly add milk to the mawa sooji mixture. The batter may look curdled at this point. Dont worry; its absolutely fine. This curdling of ingredients will not affect the final cake.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Once all the milk is used, scrape the sides of the bowl one last time.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Pour the sooji mawa cake batter in the greased pan.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Use an offset spatula spread the sooji mawa cake batter evenly into the corners and along the edges of the baking pan.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
To help get rid of trapped air bubbles, tap the baking pan on the counter a few times. Sprinkle crushed pistachios on top.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Place the pan in the preheated oven and bake for 40-42 minutes or until the toothpick comes out clean.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Remove the Sooji mawa cake from the oven and set it over the counter to cool. Allow the cake to cool in the pan for 10-12 minutes.
8d2f04ae-e865-4f12-9552-998f9414143a
Run a knife around the edges of the cake to loosen the band. Serve hot with a cup of hot tea or coffee.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f MAKE THE SAUCE In a small bowl, whisk all the sauce ingredients until combined. Set it aside.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f PREPARE TOFU Unwrap the tofu from its package and drain the excess liquid. Place the block of tofu in between two kitchen paper towels.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f PREPARE TOFU Place a heavy object on top to drain any excess liquid. Allow the tofu to press for 15 minutes under this heavy object.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f PREPARE TOFU The extra liquid will drain away. After the rest time, unwrap the tofu block.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f PREPARE TOFU Chop the pressed tofu into small cubes.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f PREPARE CRISPY TOFU BITES Add the chopped tofu to a large bowl and add cornstarch.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f PREPARE CRISPY TOFU BITES Toss to coat the tofu bites with cornstarch. Make sure every tofu piece is well coated in cornstarch.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f PREPARE CRISPY TOFU BITES Add Mazola Corn Oil to a large skillet.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f PREPARE CRISPY TOFU BITES Add tofu pieces and cook on medium heat until crisp and slightly brown. It should take 5-6 minutes.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f PREPARE CRISPY TOFU BITES Once cooked, remove from heat and set aside.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f COOK AND ASSEMBLE EVERYTHING Add Mazola Corn Oil to the same skillet. Once its hot, add chopped green beans to the skillet and cook for a minute. Do not overcook.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f COOK AND ASSEMBLE EVERYTHING Add ginger and garlic paste cook for 2-3 minutes. Add chopped onions to the pan. Cook for a minute.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f COOK AND ASSEMBLE EVERYTHING Next, add bell peppers. Stir to combine.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f COOK AND ASSEMBLE EVERYTHING Lower the heat to the lowest setting and pour in the sauce that we have prepared earlier in the recipe. Mix until combined.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f COOK AND ASSEMBLE EVERYTHING Finally, add the crispy tofu bites and basil leaves.
db201b2e-bc74-46b5-8535-75abea20cb0f COOK AND ASSEMBLE EVERYTHING Toss everything together and cook for another 2 minutes on low heat. Once done, remove from heat and serve with white rice.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES In a pressure cooker add carrots, peas, cauliflower, and beets along with 1.5 cups of water. Pressure cook for 3-4 whistles.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES Allow the pressure to release naturally. Drain the boiled veggies and set aside. Save the water.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES In the same cooker, boil the potatoes separately. Once done, peel the potatoes and set aside.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES Heat 3 tablespoons butter in a heavy-bottomed pan.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES Add bell peppers and cook for 2-3 minutes on medium flame, stirring constantly.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES Add boiled peas and carrots to the pan.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES Mash the veggies using a masher.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES Pour in 3 tablespoons of water and mash the vegetables.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES Cook until the oil starts to separate. Keep mashing the vegetables all along.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES Pour in another 1/4 cup of water.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES Add beets, cauliflower, and boiled potatoes to the tomato mixture.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES Keep crushing the vegetables with a masher. Add 1/4 of water.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 PREPARING VEGGIES Mash the vegetables to desired consistency. Cook for another 3-4 minutes and then take it off the heat.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 ASSEMBLING PAV BHAJI Heat a skillet over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of butter along with ginger paste and cook for a minute.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 ASSEMBLING PAV BHAJI Add onions and sauté until soft and translucent.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 ASSEMBLING PAV BHAJI Stir in chopped tomatoes.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 ASSEMBLING PAV BHAJI Pour in 2-3 tablespoons of water.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 ASSEMBLING PAV BHAJI Cover the tomatoes with a lid and cook until they become soft.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 ASSEMBLING PAV BHAJI Mash the tomatoes with a masher.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 ASSEMBLING PAV BHAJI Add the Pav Bhaji Masala along with another 2-3 tablespoons of water.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 ASSEMBLING PAV BHAJI Mix until everything is combined.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 ASSEMBLING PAV BHAJI Mash and cook until the oil starts to separate.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 ASSEMBLING PAV BHAJI Stir in salt and Kashmiri red chili powder.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 ASSEMBLING PAV BHAJI Finally, add the mashed vegetables to the skillet. Add kasoori methi and cook for another 3-4 minutes or until the oil separates.
f77663f8-51bb-45d9-a292-9babf3d94709 ASSEMBLING PAV BHAJI Top with chopped coriander leaves and serve hot.
d6b02d4b-48ff-4b4a-aae9-df2a2361c5c6
Rinse and drain quinoa. Boil quinoa as per package instructions.
d6b02d4b-48ff-4b4a-aae9-df2a2361c5c6
Allow it to cool completely.
d6b02d4b-48ff-4b4a-aae9-df2a2361c5c6
Peel and grate the zucchini in a bowl. Sprinkle the grated zucchini with salt. Let it rest for 5 minutes. Now, transfer grated zucchini to a clean muslin cloth and squeeze out all the moisture from the zucchini.
d6b02d4b-48ff-4b4a-aae9-df2a2361c5c6
It should measure 1 cup after pressing out all of the water.
d6b02d4b-48ff-4b4a-aae9-df2a2361c5c6
Preheat oven @400 degrees F. In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients. Mix it well until it forms a non-sticky dough.
d6b02d4b-48ff-4b4a-aae9-df2a2361c5c6
Finish it off with 1 tablespoon of oil and mix again.
d6b02d4b-48ff-4b4a-aae9-df2a2361c5c6
Shape the dough into bite-sized bites. Brush quinoa bites with oil. Transfer the bites to the hot oven to bake.
d6b02d4b-48ff-4b4a-aae9-df2a2361c5c6
Bake for 15 20 minutes.
d6b02d4b-48ff-4b4a-aae9-df2a2361c5c6
Halfway into the cooking (7.5 minutes) flip the bites over and bake for another 10 minutes or until golden brown. This way they will brown up evenly. To attain a darker color, broil these bites for 3-4 minutes. Keep a watchful eye as they can get burn easily.
d6b02d4b-48ff-4b4a-aae9-df2a2361c5c6
Remove from oven and serve this quinoa bites with a hot and spicy vegan mayo sriracha dip and enjoy!!
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 SAFFRON MILK Combine 1/4 cup milk and saffron strands in a microwavable bowlheat for 40 seconds. Remove and mix.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 SAFFRON MILK Let it rest for 5 minutes, and saffron will induce a beautiful yellow color in the milk.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 PREPARE KESAR MAWA MODAK Heat a heavy-bottomed pan over medium heat. Next, combine ghee and milk powder in the pan.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 PREPARE KESAR MAWA MODAK Soon the mixture will turn into a gooey paste. No worries, keep stirring.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 PREPARE KESAR MAWA MODAK Pour in the remaining milk and saffron milk. Mix to combine. After 5 minutes into the cooking, the mawa and ghee mixture will start to thicken.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 PREPARE KESAR MAWA MODAK Keep stirring continuously to avoid lump formation.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 PREPARE KESAR MAWA MODAK Once the mixture comes together like a soft dough, take the pan off the heat.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 PREPARE KESAR MAWA MODAK Set aside the Kesar mawa mixture for 5 minutes or until the mawa mixture is still warm but comfortably cool to handle.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 PREPARE KESAR MAWA MODAK While the mixture is resting, lets prepare the filling. Combine slivered almonds, pistachios, desiccated coconut, jaggery, cardamom powder, and cashews in a bowl. Mix to combine.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 PREPARE KESAR MAWA MODAK Once the mawa mixture is comfortable to touch, add powdered sugar, cardamom powder, and kewra essence to the Kesar mawa mix. Mix until everything is well combined.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 PREPARE KESAR MAWA MODAK Knead it well until it forms a soft and smooth dough. The Kesar mawa mixture for making modak is ready now.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 ASSEMBLING MODAK Brush the modak mold with some melted ghee. Once greased, take some Kesar mawa mixture and spread it on both the sides of the mold.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 ASSEMBLING MODAK Firmly press the mawa mixture around the mold. Now, press both the mold ends together to give modak its shape.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 ASSEMBLING MODAK Flip the mold over, and stuff the filling mixture at the bottom of the mold.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 ASSEMBLING MODAK Take a small piece of Kesar mawa and seal the bottom part. Discard the excess mawa. Give the mold a final press.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 ASSEMBLING MODAK Gently open the mold. Discard the excess mawa around the edges of the mold to give your modak an elegant look.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 ASSEMBLING MODAK Press it around the edges or bottom to release the modak out of its mold. Similarly, shape all the Kesar mawa modak until all the mixture is used up.
a96451da-56cd-4c9a-a01f-13d82ad52e60 ASSEMBLING MODAK Arrange the Mawa modak or Khavyache modak on a plate. Garnish with edible silver leaf, some saffron strands, and serve.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Rinse moong dal under tap water a few times to get rid of any dust and grit. Transfer the rinsed lentils to a bowl and add hot water to the bowl.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Soak the lentils in hot water for 20 minutes. Lentils will swell in size.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
After the resting time, transfer the lentils to a strainer and drain the water. Rinse the lentils thoroughly under running water for a couple of minutes. Set aside to drain. Make sure the daal is drained thoroughly.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Transfer the lentils to a pan. Sauté moong dal over medium heat stirring frequently. Initially, the lentils will stick to the spoon.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Saute for 8-10 minutes or until the lentils feel dry. The trick is to evaporate all the moisture from the dal. So, do not overcook the lentils. Take the pan off the heat and allow the lentils to cool comfortably.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Transfer the moong dal to a food processor.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Pulse the lentils until fine and powdery.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Pass the freshly ground lentils through the sieve to remove any bits of lentils and return it to the food processor to grind them into a fine powder. Set the ground lentils aside.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Heat ghee in the same pan. Add the moong dal powder to this pan. Roast the powdered moong dal on medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook until the lentils turn deep yellow and impart a nutty fragrance.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
This roasting will take somewhere about 30-35 minutes. I know it sounds like a labor-intensive process, but this is the only lengthy process involved in making these moong dal ladoos.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
After the moong dal powder is cooked, lower the heat to the lowest setting and stir in the cardamom powder. Mix to combine. Pour in the saffron milk mixture.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Mix to combine the saffron milk into the moong dal mixture. Saffron milk will lend a beautiful yellow color to the mix.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Add the powdered sugar to the warm moong dal mixture. Mix until the sugar is well incorporated.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
PROTIP- Moong dal ladoos are very sweet therefore, 1 cup sugar is added. But if you prefer sugar on the lower side, then add 3/4 cup, to begin with, and adjust according to taste.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Take the moong dal mix off the heat and allow it to cool to a comfortable temperature.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
While the moong dal mixture is still warm, take 2 tablespoons of mixture in your palms. Press and roll the mix firmly in between your palm to form a round shape.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Roll the ladoos until you achieve the desired round shape. Do not let the mixture cool down; try to shape the ladoos, while the mix is still warm.
76e70d18-6221-4900-a9f7-3c3ec3fcf121
Repeat this process until all the ladoos are formed. You can decorate moong dal laddus with saffron strands and pistachios.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb
Slice paneer into 1-inch cubes. Set aside.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb PREPARE ACHARI MARINADE Combine yogurt in a large mixing bowl. Whisk until smooth and lump-free. Add ginger-garlic paste, and lemon juice to the bowl.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb PREPARE ACHARI MARINADE Pour in mustard oil, salt, degi mirch, and achari masala.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb PREPARE ACHARI MARINADE Whisk all the ingredients until well blended. There are no lumps in the mixture.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb PREPARE ACHARI MARINADE Add roasted besan to the marinade mixture.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb PREPARE ACHARI MARINADE Pour the marinade mixture over paneer cubes.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb PREPARE ACHARI MARINADE Rub the marinate well so that it coats all the paneer cubes evenly. Cover the bowl with a plastic wrap and refrigerate. Let the paneer tikka marinate for an hour. Let it rest and soak in all the flavorful spices.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb ASSEMBLING THE PANEER TIKKAS While the paneer is marinating, slice the veggies of your choice in 1-inch cubes.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb ASSEMBLING THE PANEER TIKKAS Remove the paneer from the refrigerator and unwrap it. Gently toss the veggies to coat in the marinade. Set it aside.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb ASSEMBLING THE PANEER TIKKAS Place a steel bowl on top of the achari paneer tikka. Heat 2 pieces of charcoal over direct heat until red hot. With the help of tongs, carefully drop the burning charcoal in that bowl.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb ASSEMBLING THE PANEER TIKKAS Pour two teaspoons of ghee on top of the charcoal. The charcoal will start to emit smoke. Immediately cover the bowl with a glass lid and let the paneer tikka soak in all that smoky flavors for about 5 to 10 minutes.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb ASSEMBLING THE PANEER TIKKAS Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 450 degrees F. Skewer pieces of marinated paneer on each of the skewers, alternating it with slices of bell pepper and onion.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb ASSEMBLING THE PANEER TIKKAS Arrange all the prepared paneer tikka skewers on a baking sheet. Spray or brush the achari paneer tikka with oil or ghee.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb ASSEMBLING THE PANEER TIKKAS Bake at 450 degrees F for 5-6 minutes. Then switch the setting to broil and broil the achari paneer tikkas for 3-4 minutes or until the tikkas look slightly charred, watching it the whole time.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb ASSEMBLING THE PANEER TIKKAS Remove from the oven when the tikkas start to get slightly brown around the edges.
b9cd733e-7799-4dca-a778-52e684e27bbb ASSEMBLING THE PANEER TIKKAS Generously brush with butter. Sprinkle some chaat masala and serve hot with cilantro chutney and onion rings.
4bed1eeb-2bb1-4e36-be81-6c2da8a80ec2
Heat ghee in a pan. Add phool makhane and toast until crisp and light brown. Remove from pan and set aside.
4bed1eeb-2bb1-4e36-be81-6c2da8a80ec2
Add raisins to the same pan. Toast until light brown. Remove from heat and set aside.
4bed1eeb-2bb1-4e36-be81-6c2da8a80ec2
Add some more ghee to the same pan. Add coriander powder.
4bed1eeb-2bb1-4e36-be81-6c2da8a80ec2
Roast the coriander powder on medium-low heat. Keep stirring as it gets burned quickly.
4bed1eeb-2bb1-4e36-be81-6c2da8a80ec2
Cook the coriander powder for 10-12 minutes or until fragrant and a deep dark brown color is attained.
4bed1eeb-2bb1-4e36-be81-6c2da8a80ec2
Remove the pan from heat. Add coconut powder and powdered sugar.
4bed1eeb-2bb1-4e36-be81-6c2da8a80ec2
Add toasted phool makhane, raisins, slivered almonds, cardamom powder, and chaar magaz to the panjiri.
4bed1eeb-2bb1-4e36-be81-6c2da8a80ec2
Keep mixing until everything is well incorporated.
4bed1eeb-2bb1-4e36-be81-6c2da8a80ec2
Dhaniya panjiri is ready for prasad (offering).
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE BOORA Combine sugar and water in a heavy-bottomed pan.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE BOORA Cook over low to medium heat, Keep cooking the sugar mixture, while continually stirring.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE BOORA Cook this until the sugar melts and the mixture thickens, and it looks foamy and transparent about 5 to 6 minutes. Pour in milk. Stir to combine.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE BOORA Keep stirring the mixture. As the sugar syrup is cooked, water starts to evaporate, and the sugar concentration increases.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE BOORA After about 8-10 minutes more into the cooking, as the sugar begins to bubble, it will splatter, and you will notice some crystallizing sugar sticking to the sides of the pan. Keep scraping the sugar.
