92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE BOORA As the sugar syrup gets thicker, lower the flame to the lowest setting. Take cold water in a bowl. Drop a teaspoon of sugar syrup into the cold water.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE BOORA If you remove the dropped sugar syrup from the cold water, it will form a soft, flexible ball. If it doesnt form a softball, cook the sugar syrup for another 2-3 minutes.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE BOORA Increase the flame to the medium-low setting and add ghee to the sugar syrup. Keep stirring and scraping the sugar, continuously.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE BOORA Soon all the water will evaporate, and sugar will start to crystalize. Sugar will be still soft and moist at this stage, keep crushing the lumps. Keep stirring.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE BOORA Finally, sugar will reach a point where it has lost its moisture and will resemble a fine powder. Take it off the flame.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE BOORA Our fine sugar is ready. We have one more small step to attain Boora. Pour boora into the sieve and stir with a spoon to aid the boora to pass through.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE BOORA This process will separate all the lumps. All we get after straining is ~ fine powder sugar that is porous in texture. This is Boora or Bura sugar!
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE MATHURA KE PEDE Add mawa to a heavy-bottomed pan. Turn the heat to a low-medium setting and start cooking the mawa, stirring constantly.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE MATHURA KE PEDE After cooking mawa for about 4-5 minutes, it will start to look dry. Add ghee and mix to combine. Keep stirring.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE MATHURA KE PEDE Another 6-8 minutes into the cooking, the mawa color will start to change to pale caramel brown.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE MATHURA KE PEDE Maintain the heat and keep roasting the mawa. Extra 10 minutes into the cooking and mawa will turn into a deep brown color that we are looking for.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE MATHURA KE PEDE Remove from heat and set aside for 5 minutes. Add boora to the peda mixture.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE MATHURA KE PEDE Keep stirring until the boora is fully incorporated in the peda mix.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE MATHURA KE PEDE Transfer the peda mix to a large bowl. Add the cardamom powder and knead the peda mix until its smooth and binds well.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE MATHURA KE PEDE Lets start making Mathura ke pede. Take a golf-ball-sized piece of peda mix in between your palms and make a round ball. Slightly flatten the ball to shape it like a peda.
92bea609-9f38-4487-9a68-9a0cb1845a8b MAKE MATHURA KE PEDE Roll the shaped pedas in the leftover boora. Set aside. Repeat the process until all peda mixture is used.
02710318-8ff2-4816-9603-9e67d18dabb0 CHICKPEA-SUN DRIED TOMATOES PATTIES Drain and rinse the canned chickpeas thoroughly under tap water.
02710318-8ff2-4816-9603-9e67d18dabb0 CHICKPEA-SUN DRIED TOMATOES PATTIES In a food processor, combine all your chickpea patties ingredients.
02710318-8ff2-4816-9603-9e67d18dabb0 CHICKPEA-SUN DRIED TOMATOES PATTIES Pulse just a few times until everything is mixed together.
02710318-8ff2-4816-9603-9e67d18dabb0 CHICKPEA-SUN DRIED TOMATOES PATTIES Divide the mixture into 8 equal parts and shape them into burger patties.
02710318-8ff2-4816-9603-9e67d18dabb0 CHICKPEA-SUN DRIED TOMATOES PATTIES Heat a skillet. Grease it well. Place the patties on the skillet and cook for 6-7 minutes per side. Do not press on the patties while they are cooking. Cook until they are evenly brown and crisp on both sides. Once done, take it off the flame.
02710318-8ff2-4816-9603-9e67d18dabb0 SRIRACHA MAYO Add 1 teaspoon of sriracha sauce to 1/4 cup of mayo. Like it hot, add more sriracha sauce. Adjust according to taste.
02710318-8ff2-4816-9603-9e67d18dabb0 ASSEMBLE THE CHICKPEA BURGER Add the buns to the heated skillet. Cook them for 30 seconds. Remove from the skillet and start assembling the burger. Generously top both sides of buns with sriracha mayo.
02710318-8ff2-4816-9603-9e67d18dabb0 ASSEMBLE THE CHICKPEA BURGER Layer with a tomato slice, fresh lettuce leaves, and chickpea-sun dried tomato patty. As per taste, you can drizzle each patty with extra sriracha mayo.
02710318-8ff2-4816-9603-9e67d18dabb0 ASSEMBLE THE CHICKPEA BURGER Top with onion, tomato slices, and pickles. Finish each slider with the top bun. Serve immediately.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE STRAINED YOGURT Line a fine sieve or colander with a cheesecloth. Place a bowl underneath the sieve. Now, pour yogurt into the middle of the cheesecloth.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE STRAINED YOGURT Gather the sides of the cheesecloth and tightly fold the cheesecloth. Do not squeeze the cheesecloth.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE STRAINED YOGURT Place a plate and heavyweight over the folded cheesecloth. Let the sieve, bowl, and yogurt rest overnight in the refrigerator.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE STRAINED YOGURT After the rest time is over, the excess liquid (whey) will strain into the bowl underneath and you will end up with a thick yogurt that will have cream-cheese like consistency. Store the yogurt in the fridge.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE CRUST Preheat oven to 350°F.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE CRUST Combine almond flour, ghee, honey, and cardamom powder to a food processor.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE CRUST Pulse a couple of times until mixed. Once done, pinch the dough in your fist. It should come together like a non-sticky dough when pressed.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE CRUST Remove the dough from the food processor and knead for 2-3 minutes until it forms a smooth ball. Do not over-knead. Transfer the Gulab Jamun tart dough onto an 8-inch greased pie pan with a removable bottom.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE CRUST Using your hands, firmly pat the tart dough evenly along the bottom. Push it up to the sides so that it covers the edges too.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE CRUST Prick holes in the spread-out tart dough. This allows the steam to escape while the crust is baking.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE CRUST Bake the pie pan in the preheated oven until the crust is golden brown, about 10-12 minutes.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE CRUST Remove the tart pan from the oven and set aside to cool.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE FILLING While the crust is cooling, lets make the filling.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE FILLING Dissolve and hydrate agar-agar in lukewarm water. Let it set.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE FILLING Soak saffron strands in warm milk. Saffron will release its golden color and aroma when mixed in warm milk.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE FILLING Remove the strained yogurt from the muslin cloth. Transfer it to a large mixing bowl.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE FILLING Add powdered sugar to the strained yogurt. Stir in cardamom powder and kewra essence.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE FILLING Add hydrated agar-agar and saffron milk to the bowl.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 PREPARE THE FILLING Stir all the ingredients together until well mixed. Add whipped cream and fold until smooth. Set aside.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 ASSEMBLE THE GULAB JAMUN YOGURT TART After the crust has cooled completely, arrange sliced Gulab Jamuns into the pre-baked tart shell.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 ASSEMBLE THE GULAB JAMUN YOGURT TART Pour the yogurt filling over the sliced gulab jamuns.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 ASSEMBLE THE GULAB JAMUN YOGURT TART Using an offset spatula spread the even layer of yogurt filling over the Gulab Jamuns.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 ASSEMBLE THE GULAB JAMUN YOGURT TART Cover the tart lightly with a foil and transfer the Gulab Jamun yogurt tart to the refrigerator and chill for 4-5 hours or overnight.
feefbdbe-9320-400a-8cb9-a21ced1660d8 ASSEMBLE THE GULAB JAMUN YOGURT TART Once chilled, garnish the Gulab Jamun tart with crushed pistachios, dried rose petals, and sliced jamuns.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
Crumble paneer in a bowl until it resembles breadcrumbs.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
Make sure the paneer feels moist and grainy when rubbed in between the fingers, and not sticky. Wet sticky paneer will throw the whole recipe off-balance.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
Combine paneer and condensed milk in a bowl.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
Add Rooh Afza syrup. Instead of Rooh Afza syrup, you can use few drops of pink food color + 2 teaspoons of Rosewater.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
Add milk powder or milk mawa powder.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
Mix to combine. The mixture will become crumbly.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
Add 2 tablespoons of milk and mix until incorporated.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
Transfer this mixture to a food processor.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
If needed, add another tablespoon of milk and the pulse until it comes together like a soft dough.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
The mixture should feel like a soft-non-sticky dough when pressed in between the fingers.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
Transfer this mixture to a bowl and allow the mixture to rest for 15 minutes. The mix will become firm once cooled.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
For a smooth and crack-free texture of ladoos, knead the dough once it's cooled.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
In a bowl, combine gulkand and assorted nuts for filling. Mix it well.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
Grease your hands with ghee and start shaping the dough into ladoos.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
Take a ladoo and flatten it. Place the filling in the center. Bring all the edges together and fold the dough to form a ladoo.
6830b9d5-dad0-4c0d-86c0-2c1afaf79548
Keep them covered all the time or they will dry out. It can be made ahead of time and stores well in your refrigerator for 7 days.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 ACTIVATE YEAST Combine active dry yeast, sugar, and lukewarm water in a bowl. Give it a good stir. Let this mixture rest for 5-10 minutes to foam up.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 ACTIVATE YEAST If your yeast fails this step please discard the yeast and start all over again. Do not proceed to the next step or you will end up with dense and sticky bread.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 MAKE THE DOUGH Add flour, olive oil, Italian herb seasonings, proofed yeast, and salt to the stand mixer bowl.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 MAKE THE DOUGH Pour water into the bowl. Using the dough hook, mix the ingredients on medium speed until it forms a smooth dough.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 FIRST RISE Spray a bowl with oil. Transfer the dough into that greased bowl. Brush the top of the dough with oil.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 FIRST RISE Cover the bowl with a plastic wrap or a wet kitchen towel and let it rise in a warm, draft-free environment or inside your oven for 1-2 hours.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 FIRST RISE After the resting time is over, the dough will double in size and look all fluffy and airy.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 KNEAD THE DOUGH Remove the dough from the bowl, sprinkle it with a bit of flour, and punch the dough down.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 KNEAD THE DOUGH Knead the dough by stretching and pulling the dough. This step is necessary if the dough is not kneaded well, the bread will turn out dense.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 SECOND RISE Grease a 9-inch baking tray and transfer dough onto that baking tray. Stretch the dough to fit the entire pan.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 SECOND RISE Cover and let it rise for another 30-40 minutes or until doubled in size.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 SECOND RISE Once the dough has doubled in size, make about 15-16 indents all over the dough. You can use your fingers or the back of a spatula to make dimples in the focaccia dough.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 LET'S BAKE THE FOCACCIA BREAD Preheat your oven to 400 degrees F.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 LET'S BAKE THE FOCACCIA BREAD While the oven is heating, you can top your bread with crushed black pepper, rosemary, and sea salt. Finally, drizzle olive oil all over the unbaked focaccia bread.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 LET'S BAKE THE FOCACCIA BREAD Or you can create a veggie art all over your focaccia bread. To create this art, I have used red bell peppers, red onions, cilantro leaves, olives, and yellow peppers.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 LET'S BAKE THE FOCACCIA BREAD Bake the focaccia bread in the preheated oven for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Once done, remove from oven and brush with more olive oil if desired.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 LET'S BAKE THE FOCACCIA BREAD Let the freshly baked focaccia bread cool in the pan for 5 minutes then transfer to a cooling rack.
7fec5c2b-120f-4087-976f-dd0211d17f41 LET'S BAKE THE FOCACCIA BREAD Slice the focaccia bread into squares pieces and serve warm.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Thoroughly clean and rinse the raw chicken. Set it aside.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Combine vegetarian oyster sauce, tamari, vegan fish sauce, and brown sugar in a mixing bowl. Whisk to combine. Set aside.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Heat oil in a skillet. Add the chicken.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Cook for 3-4 minutes until it starts to brown and no longer pink. Use a spoon to move around the chicken so that its evenly cooked.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Once done, remove the chicken from heat and set aside.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Heat sesame oil in the same skillet. Add green beans to the skillet and cook for 4-5 minutes, stirring them occasionally.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Once the green beans are fork-tender, add bell peppers, and garlic to the skillet. Mix to combine.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Stir in onions.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Cook for additional 3-4 minutes until the onions begin to soften.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Return the chicken to the skillet. Move the chicken and veggies to the side of the skillet.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Stir in the sauce mixture. Mix everything together.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Drain the excess liquid. Cook for another 2 minutes until the sauce starts to thicken.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Remove the skillet from heat. Add chopped green onions and Thai Basil leaves.
4dd456b2-007c-4510-b8e8-b8b36584a438
Give it a toss. Transfer Thai basil chicken to a bowl and serve hot.
44d84f16-bf19-4993-8e22-ce5240fd427d
Rinse bhindi thoroughly under tap water. Let it air dry on a kitchen towel.
44d84f16-bf19-4993-8e22-ce5240fd427d
Slice off the hard green top. Slice the bhindi in half lengthwise. Set it aside.
44d84f16-bf19-4993-8e22-ce5240fd427d
Heat oil in a pan. Add sliced bhindi to the pan.
44d84f16-bf19-4993-8e22-ce5240fd427d
Sauté bhindi for 2-3 minutes until its soft and tender. Once tender, remove from heat and set aside.
44d84f16-bf19-4993-8e22-ce5240fd427d
Heat oil in a pan. Add cumin seeds. Once the cumin seeds start to splatter, stir in the tomato puree.
44d84f16-bf19-4993-8e22-ce5240fd427d
Cook tomato puree for another 4-5 minutes. Stir in the spices coriander powder, Kashmiri red chili powder, salt, turmeric, and amchur powder.
44d84f16-bf19-4993-8e22-ce5240fd427d
Mix to combine. Cook the tomato puree with spices for 2-3 minutes or until the oil separates.
44d84f16-bf19-4993-8e22-ce5240fd427d
Add pearl onions to the cooked tomato.
44d84f16-bf19-4993-8e22-ce5240fd427d
Stir in green chilies. Add chopped cilantro leaves and stir to combine.
44d84f16-bf19-4993-8e22-ce5240fd427d
Cover and let cook the onions for 3-4 minutes or until fork-tender.
44d84f16-bf19-4993-8e22-ce5240fd427d
Uncover the pan and check if the onions are soft. Return the pre-cooked bhindi to the pan.
44d84f16-bf19-4993-8e22-ce5240fd427d
Stir until well-combined. Cover and cook bhindi for another 3-4 minutes (to desired tenderness).
c1dcdf83-c830-44ed-8ed9-a1349f27ffa0
Heat milk, honey, and hot cocoa mix in a small saucepan. Mix until it just combines. Remove from heat and allow the mix to cool.
c1dcdf83-c830-44ed-8ed9-a1349f27ffa0
Transfer this chocolate mix along with ice, vanilla extract, and cooled brownies to a blender.
c1dcdf83-c830-44ed-8ed9-a1349f27ffa0
Brownies will grind down into little crumbles. Blend until it sort of looks like a slushy. Once you have achieved that consistency, fill up your mugs. Serve immediately topped with whipped cream frosting, colorful marshmallows, brownie crumbles, some chocolate sprinkles, and enjoy!
4214a5e0-bce0-4496-8846-d7157a405eca
Combine the chili-garlic sauce ingredients in a cup and whisk well to combine. Set aside.
4214a5e0-bce0-4496-8846-d7157a405eca
Unwrap the udon noodles. Fill a large pan with hot tap water. Add udon noodles to this bowl and soak for a few minutes. Using a fork gently move the noodles around to separate. Drain the noodles. Rinse under cold water and drain again.
4214a5e0-bce0-4496-8846-d7157a405eca
Transfer the drained noodles to a bowl and pour ¼ cup of the chili garlic sesame sauce. Save the rest.
4214a5e0-bce0-4496-8846-d7157a405eca
Place a heavy-bottomed pan over heat and add avocado oil. Once the oil is hot, add ginger-garlic and onions. Stir that for few minutes until the garlic becomes fragrant and onions are softened.
4214a5e0-bce0-4496-8846-d7157a405eca
Pour the remaining sauce and toss gently.
4214a5e0-bce0-4496-8846-d7157a405eca
Serve yourself a full plate and enjoy!
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Wash chicken keema in a strainer. Drain well and set aside.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Heat ghee in a heavy-bottomed pan. Add bay leaves, whole back cardamom, and black peppercorns to the pan. Sauté the whole spices until they turn a beautiful golden brown color.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Stir in cumin seeds. Sauté the cumin seeds in the ghee until they begin to crackle and pop.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Once the whole spices have released their aroma, add ginger and garlic paste.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Fry the ginger-garlic paste for a minute.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Stir in chopped onions and cook on medium-low flame until the onions become translucent and golden brown.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Stir in crushed tomatoes.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Cook for 2-3 minutes until the oil starts to separate.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Add all the spices Kashmiri red chili powder, coriander powder, salt, and garam masala powder.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Add yogurt and mix to combine.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Now add kasoori methi. Cook until the oil separates.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Add cream and mix it well.

Once everything well blended, add the chicken mince.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Cook the chicken mince over medium heat. Keep mixing and stirring frequently to prevent lump formation.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Cook until the mince is evenly brown, for 5 8 minutes.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Add matar and cook for another 2-3 minutes until peas are soft.
20e0b07b-afeb-468a-a337-ea4ab91978c6
Garnish the Chicken Keema matar with fresh cilantro leaves and serve warm with Tandoori Rotis or over the bed of warm basmati rice.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a ARROWROOT SLURRY Combine arrowroot flour and water in a bowl. Mix until lump-free. Set it aside.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Pour milk and sugar in a pour. Sprinkle with instant yeast.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Whisk to combine the ingredients.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Add unsalted butter. Pour in the arrowroot slurry and salt. Mix until combined.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Slowly spoon in the wheat flour into this mixture. Whisk until blended. Keep adding flour until all is used up.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Add the mixture starts to come together like dough. Grease the entire ball of dough with 1 teaspoon of oil. Spread it all over the dough.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Cover the kulcha dough with a clean damp kitchen towel or plastic wrap and let it rise for 40 minutes in a warm, draft-free environment.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Within 40 minutes, the dough should double in size quickly, assuming your yeast is good.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Dust your countertop with flour. Transfer the kulcha dough onto the dusted surface and knead it well.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Divide the dough into equal pieces. Roll out each piece into a circle and form it into a ball. Arrange the balls on the tray.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Cover the wheat mulch dough balls with a wet towel and let it rise for another 30 minutes or until doubled in size.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Preheat oven to 475 degrees F.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Once doubled, take a dough ball and sprinkle a bit of flour over it. To prevent drying, keep the rest of the dough balls covered while you are working on this one. Using your fingers, spread out the dough ball so that its about 5 inches in diameter.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Sprinkle spices and freshly chopped cilantro leaves on top.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Transfer the wheat kulcha onto a baking tray or skillet.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Bake the wheat kulcha in a preheated oven until golden brown, about 7-8 minutes. Once cooked, remove from oven and generously apply butter on top.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a KULCHA DOUGH Serve hot with warm matar or Pindi chole.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a WHEAT KULCHA Knead a soft and pliable dough by mixing all the ingredients mentioned above. Cover and let the dough rest in a warm place for 1 hour. Do not skip vinegar as it preserves the kulchas from going bad so fast.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a WHEAT KULCHA After the rest time is over, divide the dough into equal pieces. Roll and spread out the dough ball so that its about 5 inches in diameter.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a WHEAT KULCHA Heat a skillet. Transfer the kulcha onto a hot griddle. The kulchas will cook fairly quickly, about a minute per side. You will notice some bubbles developing on the surface.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a WHEAT KULCHA Sprinkle cilantro leaves on top.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a WHEAT KULCHA Flip and cook from the other side. I usually add a teaspoon on each side to brown my kulchas.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a WHEAT KULCHA Cook evenly from both sides until evenly cooked.
e7e34338-1221-4131-a507-df595e7bc36a WHEAT KULCHA Remove from heat and serve hot!
f1ab05ef-a967-429f-8ab4-bf803335504d
Start by dry roasting peanuts, flaxseeds, and oats. Combine all three in a skillet and dry roast over medium-low heat. Dry roast until peanuts and oats are slightly browned and fragrant.
f1ab05ef-a967-429f-8ab4-bf803335504d
Remove from heat and set aside. Allow it to cool. Transfer the dry roasted ingredients to a grinder.
f1ab05ef-a967-429f-8ab4-bf803335504d
Blend the ingredients oats until they are ground into a powder-like consistency. Set aside.
f1ab05ef-a967-429f-8ab4-bf803335504d
Combine mashed potato and moong dal sprouts in a mixing bowl. Mix until combined.
f1ab05ef-a967-429f-8ab4-bf803335504d
Stir in amchur powder, red chili powder, coriander powder, ginger paste, chopped mint leaves, cilantro leaves, and salt.
f1ab05ef-a967-429f-8ab4-bf803335504d
Add yogurt followed by ground flaxseed-peanut-oats mix.
f1ab05ef-a967-429f-8ab4-bf803335504d
Stir everything together until a non-sticky dough is formed.
f1ab05ef-a967-429f-8ab4-bf803335504d
Time to shape sprouted moong dal cutlets. Divide the mixture into 10 uniform golf-sized balls. Tightly roll the ball and shape into cutlets.
f1ab05ef-a967-429f-8ab4-bf803335504d
Grease a skilletspread cutlets in a single layer.
f1ab05ef-a967-429f-8ab4-bf803335504d
Cook the moong dal cutlets in a skillet, stirring often for four to five minutes on one side or until the cutlets turn light golden brown.
f1ab05ef-a967-429f-8ab4-bf803335504d
Flip and cook the other side too. Once done, take the moong beans cutlets off the heat. Cool the cutlets on the plate for 5 minutes before serving. This helps the cutlets to firm up a bit.
f1ab05ef-a967-429f-8ab4-bf803335504d
Serve them warm with my green chutney and enjoy!
28ea9d57-318f-4dca-9bd5-26c484bee1ff
Rinse strawberries thoroughly under cold running water.
28ea9d57-318f-4dca-9bd5-26c484bee1ff
Remove the hull and discard it.
28ea9d57-318f-4dca-9bd5-26c484bee1ff
Slice strawberries into quarters. Combine berries and fresh mint sprigs in a pitcher. Fill the pitcher with water.
28ea9d57-318f-4dca-9bd5-26c484bee1ff
Using a spoon, muddle the strawberries a little to release the juices.
28ea9d57-318f-4dca-9bd5-26c484bee1ff
Cover the pitcher with a lid and chill it in the refrigerator for 6-8 hours or overnight.
28ea9d57-318f-4dca-9bd5-26c484bee1ff
The following day, remove the pitcher from the fridge.
28ea9d57-318f-4dca-9bd5-26c484bee1ff
Pour into glasses and enjoy!
1440027c-9f3d-445c-aac6-34dba8684725 HOW TO DE-SEED AND SLICE OKRA/BHINDI Rinse bhindi thoroughly under tap water. Rub it gently to remove any dirt that usually sticks to the skin of bhindi.
1440027c-9f3d-445c-aac6-34dba8684725 HOW TO DE-SEED AND SLICE OKRA/BHINDI Pat it dry with a kitchen towel.
1440027c-9f3d-445c-aac6-34dba8684725 HOW TO DE-SEED AND SLICE OKRA/BHINDI Trim the top of each bhindi. Now, slice each bhindi in half down the center vertically. You will now have four sliced pieces of each bhindi.
1440027c-9f3d-445c-aac6-34dba8684725 HOW TO DE-SEED AND SLICE OKRA/BHINDI Use a spoon to scoop out and discard all the seeds from bhindi.
1440027c-9f3d-445c-aac6-34dba8684725 MAKE KURKURI BHINDI Transfer bhindi to a mixing bowl. Add cumin powder, coriander powder, red chili powder, haldi, chaat masala, and salt.
1440027c-9f3d-445c-aac6-34dba8684725 MAKE KURKURI BHINDI Toss to coat the bhindi in spices.
1440027c-9f3d-445c-aac6-34dba8684725 MAKE KURKURI BHINDI Let the bhindi rest for 10 minutes. Salt will help to draw some moisture from the bhindi.
1440027c-9f3d-445c-aac6-34dba8684725 MAKE KURKURI BHINDI Heat oil in a pan. When the oil becomes hot, add besan and cornstarch to the bhindi. Toss to coat.
1440027c-9f3d-445c-aac6-34dba8684725 MAKE KURKURI BHINDI Just before frying dust off the excess flour and deep fry the bhindi in batches. Do not overcrowd the pan.
1440027c-9f3d-445c-aac6-34dba8684725 MAKE KURKURI BHINDI Fry until crisp and golden. Remove from oil and drain all the excess oil off.
1440027c-9f3d-445c-aac6-34dba8684725 MAKE KURKURI BHINDI Crispy Kurkuri Bhindi is ready to be served. Sprinkle some lemon juice and chaat masala on top and enjoy!
a2634604-ae4a-4c35-81b3-9130f13cab5e
Clean, rinse, and cut the chicken into cubes.
a2634604-ae4a-4c35-81b3-9130f13cab5e
Meanwhile, let's assemble all the ingredients listed under 'The first set of ingredients.' Combine all the above ingredients in a bowl.
a2634604-ae4a-4c35-81b3-9130f13cab5e
Assemble all the ingredients listed under 'second set of ingredients.' If cilantro, green chilies or garam masala aren't your favorites, then feel free to leave them out. Your tikkas will still turn out good. Combine both the ingredients (the first set of ingredients + the second ingredients) in a large bowl.
a2634604-ae4a-4c35-81b3-9130f13cab5e
Mix it well. Do the taste test.
a2634604-ae4a-4c35-81b3-9130f13cab5e
Add chicken. Rub this marinade onto the chicken. Marinade chicken in this mix for 5-6 hours or overnight.
a2634604-ae4a-4c35-81b3-9130f13cab5e
Preheat oven @400 degree F. Remove chicken from the fridge and thread the pieces onto the skewers. Evenly divide the pieces between 6 skewers.
a2634604-ae4a-4c35-81b3-9130f13cab5e
Cook for 25-30 minutes turning them once in between until cooked through.
a2634604-ae4a-4c35-81b3-9130f13cab5e
Remove from the oven. Generously brush with butter. Transfer the skewers to a platter and serve hot.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 1- PREPARE THE MANGO PURÉE Wash, pat dry, and cut mangoes in half.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 1- PREPARE THE MANGO PURÉE Scoop out the pulp from the mangoes and scrape the pulp off the seed too. Transfer it to a blender.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 1- PREPARE THE MANGO PURÉE Blend the pulp until smooth.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 1- PREPARE THE MANGO PURÉE Pour the puréed mango through a wire mesh strainer. Set aside.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 2- BAKE THE MANGO CAKE Preheat oven at 330 degrees F.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 2- BAKE THE MANGO CAKE Combine buttermilk, oil, mango essence, and sugar in a mixing bowl. Whisk until blended.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 2- BAKE THE MANGO CAKE Stir in all-purpose flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt. Mix to combine.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 2- BAKE THE MANGO CAKE Mix the dry ingredients until just combined.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 2- BAKE THE MANGO CAKE Pour in ¾ cups of mango puree (that was prepared earlier).
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 2- BAKE THE MANGO CAKE Mix to combine.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 2- BAKE THE MANGO CAKE Grease 2 6-inch round baking springform pans.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 2- BAKE THE MANGO CAKE Pour the mango cake batter in the greased pans. Tap the pans against your countertop two to three times to get rid of air bubbles.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 2- BAKE THE MANGO CAKE Transfer the cake pans to the preheated oven and bake at 330 degrees F for 45-50 minutes. Before removing, do the toothpick test. Insert a toothpick in the center of the cake; if it comes out clean, the cake is done.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 2- BAKE THE MANGO CAKE Remove from oven and allow the eggless mango cake to cool for 10-12 minutes in pan.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 3- ASSEMBLE THE EGGLESS MANGO CAKE When ready to assemble, remove the cake from the springform pan.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 3- ASSEMBLE THE EGGLESS MANGO CAKE Gently lift the cake and remove the bottom tray.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 3- ASSEMBLE THE EGGLESS MANGO CAKE Using a sharp knife slices the cake horizontally into 2 halves. Now we have 4 half slices of an eggless mango cake.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 3- ASSEMBLE THE EGGLESS MANGO CAKE Take two halves spread mango purée over the crumb part.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 3- ASSEMBLE THE EGGLESS MANGO CAKE Take the other two halves layer it with whipped cream frosting.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 3- ASSEMBLE THE EGGLESS MANGO CAKE Invert the whipped cream frosted layer (upside down) on top of the mango layer. Gently press it down. Repeat the same with the other layer. Now we have two mango-whipped cream frosted cake sandwiches.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 3- ASSEMBLE THE EGGLESS MANGO CAKE Apply a whipped cream frosting in between and stack the cake on top of each other. Now that we have stacked up both all the layers, its time to dress our eggless mango cake (frost it).
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 3- ASSEMBLE THE EGGLESS MANGO CAKE Gather some whipped cream frosting on the spatula and apply a thin layer of frosting to the top and sides of the cake with a spatula. Smoothen it out and cover the entire cake.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 3- ASSEMBLE THE EGGLESS MANGO CAKE Transfer the eggless frosted cake to the refrigerator and chill for about 10-15 minutes.
aee80a12-9247-43b0-920c-0c0a033970e6 STEP 3- ASSEMBLE THE EGGLESS MANGO CAKE Pipe a star design all around the top and side of your cake. Add a fun touch by placing some mango scoops on the top.
010fbf92-0f45-4518-b193-af97f2f41ea4 MAKING OF PRALINE BUTTERSCOTCH CHIPS Add butter, coconut oil, and brown sugar in a heavy-bottomed pan.
010fbf92-0f45-4518-b193-af97f2f41ea4 MAKING OF PRALINE BUTTERSCOTCH CHIPS Cut into pieces, and homemade butterscotch pralines are ready.
010fbf92-0f45-4518-b193-af97f2f41ea4 HOMEMADE WHIPPED CREAM Before you start, chill the balloon electric whisk attachment and bowl in the refrigerator for an hour. Pour whipping cream and a pinch of salt to the chilled bowl.
010fbf92-0f45-4518-b193-af97f2f41ea4 HOMEMADE WHIPPED CREAM To check if the whipped cream has the right consistency remove the whisk/blender from the mixer/base. Turn it upside down and if the whipped cream maintains its soft peak firmly without falling off the blade its ready to use and is perfect. Whipped cream is all set.
010fbf92-0f45-4518-b193-af97f2f41ea4 ASSEMBLE ICE CREAM In a bowl combine whipped cream (that we had prepared earlier), along with milk powder, Butterscotch essence, and condensed milk.
010fbf92-0f45-4518-b193-af97f2f41ea4 ASSEMBLE ICE CREAM Gently fold in all the ingredients. Do not whisk, fold gently.
010fbf92-0f45-4518-b193-af97f2f41ea4 ASSEMBLE ICE CREAM Add the chopped nuts. For a nuttier ice cream add ¾ cup of chopped/crushed nuts but if you prefer fewer nuts in your ice cream than add ½ a cup of chopped/crushed nuts.
010fbf92-0f45-4518-b193-af97f2f41ea4 ASSEMBLE ICE CREAM Mix to combine. Transfer ice cream to a freezer safe bowl (9 x 5-inch pan) and freeze until firm.
09dcf5a9-0d69-4b6c-9f69-9b2a540636b1
Preheat oven on broil setting.
09dcf5a9-0d69-4b6c-9f69-9b2a540636b1
Slice bread in ½-inch thick slices.
09dcf5a9-0d69-4b6c-9f69-9b2a540636b1
Transfer slices of bread on to a baking sheet. Spray with olive oil and broil the slices in the oven for about 2 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
09dcf5a9-0d69-4b6c-9f69-9b2a540636b1
When the bread is crispy, remove from the oven.
09dcf5a9-0d69-4b6c-9f69-9b2a540636b1
Cut a clove of garlic in half. Rub garlic on all the bread slices. Garlic infuses flavor into this bread and it will dissolve as you keep rubbing it onto the bread. Set aside.
09dcf5a9-0d69-4b6c-9f69-9b2a540636b1 PREPARE TOMATO MIXTURE In a separate bowl, combine chopped tomatoes, onions, olive oil, fresh basil leaves, and salt.
09dcf5a9-0d69-4b6c-9f69-9b2a540636b1 PREPARE TOMATO MIXTURE Toss to combine.
09dcf5a9-0d69-4b6c-9f69-9b2a540636b1 PREPARE AVOCADO SPREAD Combine smashed avocadoes, lime juice, and ground pepper in a mixing bowl.
09dcf5a9-0d69-4b6c-9f69-9b2a540636b1 PREPARE AVOCADO SPREAD Mix until blended.
09dcf5a9-0d69-4b6c-9f69-9b2a540636b1 ASSEMBLE AVOCADO BRUSCHETTA Take a toasted bread slice. Spread a layer of avocado spread onto each slice.
09dcf5a9-0d69-4b6c-9f69-9b2a540636b1 ASSEMBLE AVOCADO BRUSCHETTA Generously spoon tomato mixture on top of the avocado layer.
09dcf5a9-0d69-4b6c-9f69-9b2a540636b1 ASSEMBLE AVOCADO BRUSCHETTA Serve immediately.
3c488bb1-b28c-495b-817b-20426b6265ba
Add milk to a heavy-bottomed pan and let it simmer on a low flame.
3c488bb1-b28c-495b-817b-20426b6265ba
Meanwhile, prepare cornstarch slurry. Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons milk in a bowl. Mix until smooth and lump-free.
3c488bb1-b28c-495b-817b-20426b6265ba
Pour this cornstarch slurry into the milk. Mix until blended.
3c488bb1-b28c-495b-817b-20426b6265ba
When the milk begins to foam up, stir with a spatula. Reduce the heat to the lowest setting and stir in milk powder.
3c488bb1-b28c-495b-817b-20426b6265ba
Whisk until well blended, and no lumps remain.
3c488bb1-b28c-495b-817b-20426b6265ba
Pour in condensed milk and mango essence. Mix until just combined.
3c488bb1-b28c-495b-817b-20426b6265ba
Add chopped dry nuts and eliachi powder. Mix to combine.
3c488bb1-b28c-495b-817b-20426b6265ba
Take the kulfi mixture off the flame. Allow it to cool for 30 minutes. After the rest time is over, gently fold in mango puree into the kulfi mixture.
3c488bb1-b28c-495b-817b-20426b6265ba
Whisk until fully incorporated.
3c488bb1-b28c-495b-817b-20426b6265ba
Pour mango kulfi in the molds.
3c488bb1-b28c-495b-817b-20426b6265ba
Freeze until set.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b BOIL KALA CHANA Rinse the Kale chana/ black chickpeas thoroughly under tap water.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b BOIL KALA CHANA Transfer the chickpeas to a bowl and soak the black chickpeas overnight in 3 cups of water. By the morning, the chickpeas or kale chana will swell and double in size.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b BOIL KALA CHANA Drain that water and rinse the kala chana once again under tap water.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b BOIL KALA CHANA Transfer the black chickpeas/kala chana to the Instant Pot and add enough water to cover the beans. Beans should be covered with water.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b BOIL KALA CHANA Add salt and turmeric powder to the chickpeas. Mix to combine.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b BOIL KALA CHANA Close the Instant Pot. Turn the venting knob to the sealing position. Press the Manual button. Cook on HIGH for 30 minutes.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b BOIL KALA CHANA Once the time has elapsed, and the pin is down, carefully open the Instant Pot lid. Drain the water from the cooked Kala chana and transfer the chickpeas to a mixing bowl.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b ASSEMBLING THE KABABS Mash some of the black chickpeas with a potato masher.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b ASSEMBLING THE KABABS Add mashed potatoes. Stir in the spices and chopped cilantro leaves. Set aside.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b ASSEMBLING THE KABABS Heat oil in a pan. Stir in chopped onions, crushed ginger, and chopped chilies. Cook until the onions are translucent.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b ASSEMBLING THE KABABS Add this onion mixture to the kale chana- potato mix. Mix until well blended.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b ASSEMBLING THE KABABS Stir in breadcrumbs.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b ASSEMBLING THE KABABS Mix until thoroughly blended.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b ASSEMBLING THE KABABS Grease your hands. Take some kabab mixture in your hands. Mold and shape it like a round kababs. Repeat the process until all the kababs have been assembled.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b ASSEMBLING THE KABABS Heat oil in a skillet. Add kale chana kababs to the skillet.
752e88c3-ee7f-4b8d-a5e8-2daaa791410b ASSEMBLING THE KABABS Turn the kababs and cook until both sides are golden brown and crisp. It will take about 2-3 minutes on each side. Repeat the process until all the kababs are well cooked.

bc488f5a-f4d7-498e-9e53-fdbf024ecb87
Transfer whipped cream to a bowl. Now fold in the condensed milk, milk powder, and strawberry extract.
bc488f5a-f4d7-498e-9e53-fdbf024ecb87
Fold the ingredients together slowly.
bc488f5a-f4d7-498e-9e53-fdbf024ecb87
Line your freezer trays with a plastic wrap and pour the mixture into trays.
bc488f5a-f4d7-498e-9e53-fdbf024ecb87
Swirl strawberry sauce on top along with chopped strawberries and freeze until set.

Heat the skillet pan over medium flame.
7f957d58-1f9e-4743-b5fc-4b243e3b72e8
Slice a loaf of rustic Italian bread into thick slices. Rub the bread slices with garlic.
7f957d58-1f9e-4743-b5fc-4b243e3b72e8
Take two slices and top one of slices with 2-3 slices of fresh mozzarella. Layer the other slice with sliced Italian tomatoes.
7f957d58-1f9e-4743-b5fc-4b243e3b72e8
Sprinkle each with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Top with the other slice -drizzle oil on bread.

Place the Margherita sandwich on the heated skillet. Gently press with a lid to help melt the cheese.

4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 ACTIVATE THE YEAST Combine yeast, sugar, and lukewarm water in a bowl.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 ACTIVATE THE YEAST Mix to combine. Let the yeast rest for 5 minutes.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 ACTIVATE THE YEAST Yeast will become bubbly and foamy.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 KNEAD THE DOUGH In a large mixing bowl, add all-purpose flour, baking powder, and salt.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 KNEAD THE DOUGH Add in the activated yeast and pour butter.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 KNEAD THE DOUGH Mix until blended.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 KNEAD THE DOUGH Slowly pour in water.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 KNEAD THE DOUGH Knead until it forms a soft dough.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Grease the Instant Pot insert. Transfer the dough to the Instant Pot.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Cover it with a glass lid. Turn the Instant pot on by pressing the Yogurt button. Adjust the pressure to Less. Set the timer to 20 minutes.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT After 20 minutes, the dough will expand and double in size. Depending on the weather, the dough may take longer to rise.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT While the dough is resting, let's prepare the garlic butter spread.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Assemble butter, garlic powder, dried parsley, dried basil leaves, dried oregano, and salt in a bowl. Mix until blended. Set aside.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Dust the surface with flour and transfer the kneaded dough onto the dusted surface.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Punch down the dough and knead it for 2-3 minutes.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Preheat oven @ 350 degrees F. While the oven is heating, lets shape the dough.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Divide the dough into equal parts.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Roll the dough into smooth round balls.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Flatten the dough. Apply a single layer of garlic spread to the flatten dough.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Start rolling the dough until it looks like a log.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Fold the dough in such a way that the two ends meet each other.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT It will form a big O. Pinch the ends together.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Flip the folded roll over and it will look exactly like the one as shown in the pic below. Repeat the process with the rest of the dough.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Grease a bundt pan and arrange the dough on top of each other. Make sure to butter the bottom layer before placing the other layer on top.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Butter the top layer as well and generously top with some dried parsley or cilantro.
4b7fafbb-0314-42fd-87e5-2914c1814437 PROFFING THE DOUGH IN INSTANT POT Bake for 25-30 minutes or until the tops are golden brown. Brush the hot rolls with melted butter and serve hot.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Rinse the mangos under tap water. Gently rub them with your hands to remove any debris or deposits. Set aside. Add 1.5 cups of water to the Instant Pot insert. Add the rinsed mangoes to the insert.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Place the lid on the Instant Pot. Seal and secure. Press the Pressure cook button and cook on high pressure for 10 minutes. Make sure the venting knob is in the sealing position.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Allow the pressure to release naturally. Once the pin drops, carefully open the Instant Pot. After the mangoes are boiled, they will lose their vibrant, rich green color and may not look pleasing, and thats absolutely fine.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Remove the mangoes from the boiled water and immersing them in ice-cold water to stop the cooking process altogether.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Once the mangoes are comfortable to touch, peel the outer skin of the mangoes.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Use a spoon to scoop out the pulp from the boiled mangoes. Scrape off the seed and remove all the remaining pulp. Save the pulp.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Transfer the cooled pulp to a blender. Add jaggery. Blend until smooth.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Pour in 4.5 cups of water and blend until thoroughly combined.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Pass the pureed aam ka Panna through a fine-mesh strainer.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Strain through the strainer, pressing to extract all the mango liquid into the bowl. Discard the mango fibers.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Add fresh mint leaves to a blender. Pour in 1/2 cup of water and blend until smooth.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Pass the mint puree through a fine-mesh strainer into the previously strained aam ka Panna. Discard the leftovers.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Time to spice up our Aam ka Panna. Add rock salt, black pepper, and roasted cumin seeds to the pureed aam ka Panna.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Mix until thoroughly combined. Seal the container and transfer it to the fridge to chill.
066871f1-22df-4e53-83ee-4c440bab3970
Add ice to the Aam ka Panna and serve choilledgarnished with mint leaves.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365
Transfer the raw chole to a colander and rinse thoroughly under tap water and remove any pebbles, foreign particles, damaged beans, or other gritty things. Repeat the process 23 times.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365
Add filtered water and the rinsed chole to a large mixing bowl. Cover and let soak the chole for 8-10 hours or overnight. During the soak time, the chole water may get a little foamy. Its completely okay.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365
After the soak time, the chole will swell in size.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365
Drain the soaked chole in the colander and rinse again. Set aside.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 LETS PREPARE THE POTLI FOR THE PINDI CHOLE Take a muslin cloth. Fold the fabric in half, create a double layer of cloth.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 LETS PREPARE THE POTLI FOR THE PINDI CHOLE Add loose tea leaves to the muslin cloth. Add garlic, bay leaves, black cardamom, cinnamon, and cloves on top of the tea leaves.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 LETS PREPARE THE POTLI FOR THE PINDI CHOLE Bring all the ends together and tie a tight knot. Make sure the knot is secured. Set aside.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 LETS BOIL THE CHICKPEAS Transfer the soaked chole to the Instant Pot insert. Add filtered water to the chickpeas.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 LETS BOIL THE CHICKPEAS Add salt and a pinch of baking soda. Add the spice potli/bundle that we had prepared earlier in the recipe, to the insert.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 LETS BOIL THE CHICKPEAS Place the lid on the Instant Pot. Seal and secure. Press the Pressure cook button and cook on high pressure for 25 minutes. Make sure the venting knob is in the sealing position.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 LETS BOIL THE CHICKPEAS Allow the pressure to release naturally for 10 minutes then move the steam release handle on the lid to the venting position. Once the pin drops, carefully open the Instant Pot.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 LETS BOIL THE CHICKPEAS To check if the chole are done, take a bean in between your fingers and press. Chole will still have a bit of crunch but will mash when pressed.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 LETS BOIL THE CHICKPEAS Remove the spice potli from the Instant Pot and discard. Separate the chole from the water; its boiled in and set aside. Save the water. Do not discard.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 TIME TO COOK THE PINDI CHOLE Turn the Instant Pot to Saute mode. Pour oil into the heated pot and add cumin seeds.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 TIME TO COOK THE PINDI CHOLE When the cumin seeds start to crackle, add chopped ginger to the insert cook for a few seconds.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 TIME TO COOK THE PINDI CHOLE Add chopped onions to the insert and cook for 3-4 minutes or until the onions are translucent. Add in all the Pindi chole spices (listed below) to the Instant Pot.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 TIME TO COOK THE PINDI CHOLE Mix the spices until well blended. Return the boiled chole to the Instant Pot insert.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 TIME TO COOK THE PINDI CHOLE Gently toss the chole around until coated with the spices. Pour in 1/4 cup of the boiled chickpea water.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 TIME TO COOK THE PINDI CHOLE Allow the Pindi chole to simmer. Finally, add kasoori methi.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 TIME TO COOK THE PINDI CHOLE Crush the leaves in between your palms and sprinkle on top of the chole. Turn the Instant pot OFF.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 TIME TO COOK THE PINDI CHOLE Prepare the final tempering In a separate pan, heat oil. Add chopped tomatoes to the oil. Cook for 2-3 minutes on medium heat until the tomatoes are soft.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 TIME TO COOK THE PINDI CHOLE Pour this tomato tempering on top of the cooked Pindi chole.
becf8769-834d-4ac2-a98d-44a463252365 TIME TO COOK THE PINDI CHOLE Serve hot with warm kulchas or bhaturas.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 CHICKPEA SALAD In a large mixing bowl, add chickpeas.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 CHICKPEA SALAD Stir in chopped onions, cilantro leaves, chopped tomatoes, red chili powder, roasted cumin powder, amchur powder, and salt.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 CHICKPEA SALAD Mix until thoroughly combined. Do not add lemon juice.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 CHICKPEA SALAD Set aside.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE PAPAD KATORIS Grease a microwavable katori. Set aside.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE PAPAD KATORIS Take papad. Dip the papad in water for 2 seconds or until soft.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE PAPAD KATORIS Immediately remove the papad from water and pat dry in between a paper napkin to absorb the extra water.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE PAPAD KATORIS Carefully lift the papad. At this point, wet papad will feel like a soft uncooked roti.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE PAPAD KATORIS Spread the wet papad on the greased katori.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE PAPAD KATORIS Gently press the center part into the katroi and then arrange the rest of the papad in the bowl.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE PAPAD KATORIS Microwave the papad on HIGH for a minute. If there are a couple of spots that are still wet, no worries, cook the shaped katori for another 30 seconds.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE PAPAD KATORIS Remove from the microwave and wait for a second. Gently rub a knife around the papad to release it from the katori. Invert the katori and remove the crispy papad from the katori.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE PAPAD KATORIS Repeat the process with the rest of the papad and cook all the katoris.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE THE CHAAT When ready to serve, slightly warm the mixture in the microwave for a minute.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE THE CHAAT Take one katori and add 2 tablespoons full of filling to the katori.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE THE CHAAT Top with boondi. Sprinkle lemon juice on top.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE THE CHAAT Garnish with chopped cilantro leaves and thin sev.
e4bc11e5-3578-4b21-9362-f3d9b514f191 PREPARE THE CHAAT Serve immediately. Papad katori chaat tastes good when fresh.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Grease the bottom and sides of a 7-inch round baking pan with vegan butter.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Evenly spread brown sugar at the bottom of the pan.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Place one of the pineapple circles in the middle and nine half-circles around the edges. Add cherries to the center circle and the half circles.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Preheat oven at 350 degrees F. Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in a bowl. Set aside.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Combine sugar, pineapple essence, and oil in a large mixing bowl. Beat until smooth.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Spoon in the flour mixture, alternating with buttermilk, beating on low speed until well combined.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Pineapple upside-down cake batter should be of a thick spoon drop consistency. Meaning the batter should drop off the spoon easily.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Scrape down the sides of the bowl and gently fold in the cake batter.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Pour the cake batter over the arranged pineapple slices.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Even out the batter with a spoon. Bake the cake in a preheated oven for an hour or until the toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean with a few crumbs attached.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Remove the cake from the oven and set it over the counter to cool. Allow the cake to cool in the pan for 40 to 50 minutes.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Run a knife around the edges of the cake to loosen the band.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Carefully, invert the cake onto a serving platter.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
To remove the bottom plate Wait for 40-50 minutes, then run a knife around the bottom plate to make sure it is not stuck at the corners.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Carefully lift off the bottom tray.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
A delicious cake is waiting for you.
83404c9f-cacb-47f4-8555-9aaa31d9287f
Cut a slice and enjoy!
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREP WORK Measure and transfer the rice to a mesh strainer. Rinse rice under tap water.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREP WORK Gently rub the grains against each other to remove the dirt and impurities. Rub the grains gently; rice can break if rubbed too harshly.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREP WORK Repeat the process until that water runs clear. Add the rinsed rice to the bowl. Pour in water.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREP WORK Make sure the rice grains are submerged in water. Allow the rice to rest for 10 minutes.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREP WORK Rinse and dice all the vegetables green beans, red bell pepper, and green bell pepper.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 CARAMELIZE ONIONS Turn Instant pot to Saute mode and allow it to heat. Add 2 tablespoons of ghee. Add in sliced onions.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 CARAMELIZE ONIONS Sauté the onions for 6-8 minutes until they begin to turn dark brown somewhat soft. Remove and set aside.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREPARE BIRYANI MASALA Add ghee to the Instant pot insert. Add in bay leaves, cloves, green cardamom, and cumin seeds. Allow the spices to sizzle in the ghee for 30 seconds.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREPARE BIRYANI MASALA Add in chopped onions and garlic. Sauté for 2-3 minutes or until the onions begin to soften.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREPARE BIRYANI MASALA Add in diced tomatoes and tomato puree. Mix to combine.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREPARE BIRYANI MASALA Stir in the spices red chili powder, coriander powder, fennel seeds powder, garam masala powder, and salt.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREPARE BIRYANI MASALA Mix until the spices are thoroughly combined. Add a tablespoon of water to deglaze the Instant Pot insert.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREPARE BIRYANI MASALA Stir in diced vegetables green beans, red bell pepper, and green bell pepper. Mix to combine.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREPARE BIRYANI MASALA Add in paneer cubes.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREPARE BIRYANI MASALA Mix everything together until all the ingredients are well combined coating all the veggies in the tomato sauce.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 PREPARE BIRYANI MASALA To prevent the BURN message- scrape up any browned bits from the bottom of the insert. Turn the Instant Pot OFF.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 START LAYERING Drain and rinse the rice again. Add the soaked rice to the vegetable and paneer mixture. Spread the rice on top.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 START LAYERING Pour the saffron mix on rice.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 START LAYERING Crush kasoori methi in between your palms and sprinkle on top of rice. Sprinkle the caramelized onions on top.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 START LAYERING Pour in water. Mix gently to combine. Make sure the rice is under the water.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 START LAYERING Place the lid on the Instant pot. Seal, secure, and set to cook on high pressure for 6 minutes.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 START LAYERING Once the cooking time has elapsed, let the rice rest for 4 minutes in its own steam then release the pressure (QPR quick pressure release). When the pin drops, carefully open the lid.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 START LAYERING Gently, fluff the rice with a spoon.
62845556-733b-4b1f-b1ee-de848ad12769 START LAYERING Thats it! You have a perfect Instant Pot Paneer and vegetable biryani in less than 40 minutes. Serve and enjoy!
0e99b1f2-1640-43a6-bcb2-e0ca2e6a0632
Rinse Poha (rice flakes) under tap water until soft. Rub and squeeze all the water out. Set it aside.
0e99b1f2-1640-43a6-bcb2-e0ca2e6a0632
Repeat the same with oats. Transfer the oats to a colander. Sprinkle oats with water until they are soft. Do not rinse oats or it will become soggy. Fluff it with a fork. Oats should feel soft and dry not mushy. Set it aside.
0e99b1f2-1640-43a6-bcb2-e0ca2e6a0632
Combine potato, onion, cumin powder, chili powder, chaat masala, fennel seeds, cilantro, salt, and lemon juice to a mixing bowl (except oil). Mix well.
0e99b1f2-1640-43a6-bcb2-e0ca2e6a0632
To this potato mixture add poha and oats. Mix to combine.
0e99b1f2-1640-43a6-bcb2-e0ca2e6a0632
The mixture will feel sticky at this point. Add cornstarch and mix again.
0e99b1f2-1640-43a6-bcb2-e0ca2e6a0632
After adding cornstarch, the mixture will come together like a non-sticky dough. If it still feels sticky, you can add an extra teaspoon but not more than that.
0e99b1f2-1640-43a6-bcb2-e0ca2e6a0632
Grease a square dish and spread this mixture in that dish.
0e99b1f2-1640-43a6-bcb2-e0ca2e6a0632
Chill this mix for 30 minutes in the refrigerator.
0e99b1f2-1640-43a6-bcb2-e0ca2e6a0632
After the resting time, remove the dish from the refrigerator and cut into desired shapes.
0e99b1f2-1640-43a6-bcb2-e0ca2e6a0632
Grease a pan and spread the cutlets around.
0e99b1f2-1640-43a6-bcb2-e0ca2e6a0632
Cook from all the sides until evenly brown.
0e99b1f2-1640-43a6-bcb2-e0ca2e6a0632
Serve hot with the dip or chutney of your choice.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE DAL Start by combining all the lentils in a large mixing bowl. Pour water and rinse the lentils by rubbing them between your fingertips. The water will become slightly dirty and cloudy.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE DAL Drain this water and repeat the process until the water is relatively clean. Rinse the lentils and drain. Set aside.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE DAL Start the Instant Pot in SAUTE mode. Add ghee to the Instant Pot insert. Once the ghee is hot, add cumin seeds cook the cumin seeds for a few seconds.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE DAL Add chopped ginger to the insert cook for a minute.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE DAL Add diced onions to the Instant Pot insert. Sauté for 2-3 minutes. Add green chilies and diced tomatoes.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE DAL Stir in the dry spices red chilies, turmeric powder, coriander powder, and salt to the insert.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE DAL Mix to combine. Sauté the spices for a minute. Add rinsed panchmel lentils to the insert.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE DAL Pour in water. Mix until blended.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE DAL Seal the lid of the Instant Pot with the vent in the sealing position. Cancel the saute mode. Select the PRESSURE COOK OR MANUAL mode. Cook on high pressure for 8 minutes.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE DAL Once the cooking time has elapsed, turn off the Instant Pot. Allow the pressure to release naturally. When the pin drops, carefully open the lid.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE DAL Pour water and adjust the consistency to your liking.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE DAL Press SAUTE mode again and simmer the dal for 4-5 minutes. As it starts to boil, turn the saute mode off.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE THE TEMPERING Heat ghee in a pan. Add hing, cumin seeds, and mustard seeds. As the seeds start to crackle, add the whole chilies and red chili powder to it. Stir to combine. Take it off the flame.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE THE TEMPERING Pour the tempering over the cooked dal. Stir until well blended.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE THE TEMPERING Your Instant Pot Panchmel dal is ready. Crush kasoori methi in between your palms and sprinkle on the cooked dal.
b7cfe3b1-741b-4072-a302-84f3a5960486 PREPARE THE TEMPERING Pair the Instant Pot Panchmel dal with tandoori roti, and methi paneer, create restaurant-style dining.
711a0944-79de-4521-8614-a287e5d025ab
Pour milk in a large bowl. Add vanilla pudding and whisk it well until the mixture thickens.
711a0944-79de-4521-8614-a287e5d025ab
Whether using instant boxed pudding or homemade vanilla custard, make sure it is thick and at room temperature.
711a0944-79de-4521-8614-a287e5d025ab
In a serving bowl, start with the first layer cookies. Then add sliced bananas.
711a0944-79de-4521-8614-a287e5d025ab
Top with a layer of vanilla custard that we had prepared earlier in the recipe.
711a0944-79de-4521-8614-a287e5d025ab
Top with cherries and bananas.
711a0944-79de-4521-8614-a287e5d025ab
Repeat all layers until you reach the top of your glass. Finish the top layer with vanilla custard. Once everything is layered (custard, cookies, and fruits), chill the pudding for a few hours in the refrigerator for all the flavors to settle.
711a0944-79de-4521-8614-a287e5d025ab
Refrigerate for 2-3 hours.
711a0944-79de-4521-8614-a287e5d025ab
Just before serving, finish off with a swirl of whipped cream, chopped nuts and a drizzle of chocolate syrup pure indulgence and divine!
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Combine wheat flour, garlic powder, salt, baking powder, baking soda, and sugar to a large mixing bowl. Mix to combine.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Add yogurt, buttermilk, and oil.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Mix with a spoon to combine.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Knead until you form a soft, pliable dough. If needed, add an extra tablespoon of buttermilk.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Cover with a clean and damp cloth. Leave to rest for 1 hour.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
During the resting period, gluten will develop, and the flour will get hydrated, resulting in a firm dough.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Remove the cover and knead the dough for a couple of minutes. Flatten the dough.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Divide the dough into 8 equal logs. Roll each log into a ball.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Cover the dough balls and let it rest for another 30 minutes.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Dust the surface with flour. Take a dough ball and roll it into the flour. With the help of a rolling pin, shape the dough ball into flat disc-shaped rotis. Move the rolling pin all around the roti. Evenly press the dough as you roll. This way, it will roll evenly from all sides.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Grease the top part of the rolled roti with butter. Spread chopped garlic and cilantro leaves on top.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Transfer the garlic roti onto a Tawa by taking it on your palm. But before placing it onto the tawa, brush the plain side of the roti with some water. This will help the roti to stick better onto the Tawa.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Cook the Tandoori garlic roti on the tawa. When it starts to puff up.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Flip the tawa over. Lower the heat to medium and then cook the roti over the direct flame.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Cook until evenly brown from all sides.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
Remove from heat, brush with ghee or butter. Serve hot.
a01f9b6f-f76b-4975-8f36-7fd72213b477
PROTIP While you are working on the other rotis, store the cooked tandoori Rotis wrapped in a towel. This way, they will not dry out and stay warm for a more extended period.
618e281c-4d67-4cbc-a7d3-aa66142967b9
Add the rinsed chopped spinach and washed lentils to the Instant Pot. Pour in water.
618e281c-4d67-4cbc-a7d3-aa66142967b9
When the instant pot beeps, do a quick pressure release and when the pin drops, carefully open the lid.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 ACTIVATE THE YEAST In a small bowl, combine yeast and sugar in ¼ cup of lukewarm water.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 ACTIVATE THE YEAST Mix to combine. Let it sit for 5 minutes. Soon it will look creamy and frothy.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 ACTIVATE THE YEAST In another 3-4 minutes, it will bloom and become all frothy and bubbly.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 ACTIVATE THE YEAST This proofing procedure shows that yeast is alive and active. If by now your yeast has not become frothy, please discard and start over.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 PREPARE THE GARLIC KNOTS DOUGH Add flour to a large mixing bowl. Add salt and baking powder. Mix it well.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 PREPARE THE GARLIC KNOTS DOUGH Pour in the yeast mixture.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 PREPARE THE GARLIC KNOTS DOUGH Add olive oil and the reamining ¾ cup of water water. If needed add a tablespoon more to bind the dough.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 PREPARE THE GARLIC KNOTS DOUGH Mix all the ingredients for 3-5 minutes until it forms a soft, pliable dough.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 PROOFING THE DOUGH IN THE INSTANT POT Grease the Instant Pot insert. Transfer the dough to the Instant Pot.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 PROOFING THE DOUGH IN THE INSTANT POT Cover it with a glass lid.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 PROOFING THE DOUGH IN THE INSTANT POT Turn the Instant pot on by pressing the Yogurt button. Adjust the pressure to Less. Set the timer to 30 minutes.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 PROOFING THE DOUGH IN THE INSTANT POT After 30 minutes, the dough will expand and double in size.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Dust the surface with flour and transfer the kneaded dough onto the dusted surface. Punch down the dough and knead it for 2-3 minutes.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Preheat oven @ 375 degrees F. While the oven is heating, flatten the dough.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Cut the flattened dough into long strips.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Roll the dough strips like logs. If the dough feels sticky than dust it with extra flour, and lets make some garlic knots.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Take a dough log. Fold and make it look like a horseshoe.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH We will work with the right end of the dough Take the right end of the dough and lap it over the left end.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH It will form a loop. Now pass the right end of the dough through it.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Make a loose knot. Tighten it to form the knot. You will still have dough left at both ends.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Take one end of the dough, wrap it over the knot and into the hole (where you see my finger). Gently press it down.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Repeat the same with the right end -wrap it over the knot and into the hole.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Press and secure both ends. Your garlic knots are ready. Repeat the process with the rest of the dough.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Grease a baking tray. Spread the garlic knots on the tray.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Brush each roll with garlic-parsley butter spread.
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Bake the garlic knots for 12-15 minutes in a preheated oven (@375 degree F).
fbda6425-1d6c-48e0-85c3-64c497becdd4 KNEAD AND SHAPE THE DOUGH Once baked, brush with butter and serve hot.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX On medium heat, dry roast chana dal, and peanuts until lightly toasted.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX Allow it to cool. Transfer chana dal and peanuts to a grinder.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX Blend or grind until powdered. Combine the rest of the ingredients in a bowl along with this lentil-peanut blend to make the bharwan masala ( spice blend).
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX Rinse baingan/eggplants under tap water until clean. Pat dry with a towel. Using a paring knife, make a slit in each eggplant. Be careful not to cut all the way through.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX TIP Make a + on each eggplant.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX Tightly spoon the peanut-lentil blend into each baingan/eggplant. Be careful not to break the eggplant. Set aside.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX Press the saute button on the Instant Pot. Once it displays hot, add oil.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX To the hot oil, add mustard seeds. Sauté for about 30 seconds.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX Add cumin seeds, and as it starts to crackle, add tomatoes and green chilies. Cook the tomatoes for about 3 to 4 minutes, until theyre soft and tender.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX Add bharwan baingan ( stuffed eggplants) and the masala (spice blend) to the instant pot insert.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX Pour in water. Mix to combine. Turn off the Saute button.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX Close the Instant Pot with its lid. Turn the venting knob to the sealing position.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX Now press the Manual button. Cook on Medium Pressure for 4 minutes. Once the Instant Pot beeps, wait for 4 minutes then do the QPR (quick pressure release).
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX As the safety pin drops down, open the lid. Stir in desiccated unsweetened coconut, jaggery, and mix until combined.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX Add cilantro leaves. Give it a gentle stir and serve hot.
bbcc1fd5-acde-4376-add6-8d39c77299cd LENTIL-PEANUT BLEND/ SPICE MIX We love pairing it with warm rotis and cucumber raita.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f VANILLA BATTER Sift the flour, baking powder, salt & baking soda in a bowl and set it aside.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f VANILLA BATTER Combine milk and vinegar in a bowl. Stir to combine and set aside for 5-10 minutes.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f VANILLA BATTER Lets make flaxseed egg In a bowl, combine water and flaxseed together.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f VANILLA BATTER Mix together and set aside for 15 minutes to thicken. This is your flaxseed egg. Add to recipes in place of 1 egg.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f VANILLA BATTER Combine oil and sugar in a large bowl. Mix until they are combined.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f VANILLA BATTER Add flaxseed egg. Next, add the flour mixture. Alternate adding the flour and the milk+vinegar mixture.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f VANILLA BATTER That would be flour then milk+vinegar mixture, then another round of flour followed by the milk+vinegar mixture. Repeat till all the flour and liquid is used.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f VANILLA BATTER Scrape the sides of your mixing bowl with a spatula to get any of the remaining ingredients that is not mixed into the batter.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f VANILLA BATTER The consistency of the batter should be flowing.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f CHOCOLATE BATTER Now add 3/4 cup of the vanilla batter to this chocolate mix. Mix well.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f CHOCOLATE BATTER Fill the batter in two separate cones. Fill the prepared cupcake liners with approximately 1/4 cup of vanilla batter.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f CHOCOLATE BATTER Pour chocolate batter on top of the vanilla batter until it is evenly distributed between all cupcake liners.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f CHOCOLATE BATTER Using a butter knife or a toothpick, swirl the chocolate into the vanilla batter a few times.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f CHOCOLATE BATTER Bake @350 degrees F for approximately 20 minutes.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f BUTTERCREAM NUTELLA FROSTING While the cupcakes are cooling, let's start with the frosting. Combine softened butter, powdered sugar, Nutella, salt, whipped cream, and vanilla essence in a bowl.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f BUTTERCREAM NUTELLA FROSTING Beat the frosting until it forms stiff peaks, and the frosting is smooth and creamy.
2062f98f-1470-4f99-a4ae-c9df061a425f BUTTERCREAM NUTELLA FROSTING Top with your favorite sprinkles and enjoy!
aee9aa6f-9a7b-45d1-8e69-d48b37f34b59
Rinse rice thoroughly until the water runs clear. Set it aside.
aee9aa6f-9a7b-45d1-8e69-d48b37f34b59
Press the saute button on the Instant Pot. Once it displays hot, add oil. To the hot oil, add onion and garlic. Saute for about 3-4 minutes until the onions turn translucent.
aee9aa6f-9a7b-45d1-8e69-d48b37f34b59
Add tomatoes and cook until soft. Instead of chopped tomatoes, you can add tomato puree too.
aee9aa6f-9a7b-45d1-8e69-d48b37f34b59
Stir in the black beans, corn, and spices. I have used a can of store-bought black beans and corn for my recipe. I highly recommend that you always rinse and drain the beans/corn before adding it to any recipe.
aee9aa6f-9a7b-45d1-8e69-d48b37f34b59
Pour vegetable stock or water into the insert. Add rinsed rice and stir to combine.
aee9aa6f-9a7b-45d1-8e69-d48b37f34b59
Finally, add red bell peppers. Close the Instant Pot with its lid. Turn the venting knob to the sealing position.
aee9aa6f-9a7b-45d1-8e69-d48b37f34b59
Now press the Manual button. Cook on High Pressure for 6 minutes. Once the Instant Pot beeps, wait for 10 minutes then do the QPR (quick pressure release).
aee9aa6f-9a7b-45d1-8e69-d48b37f34b59
As the safety pin drops down, open the lid.
aee9aa6f-9a7b-45d1-8e69-d48b37f34b59
Allow the steam to escape. Then gently fluff the rice with a fork.
aee9aa6f-9a7b-45d1-8e69-d48b37f34b59
Serve hot with Sour Cream, Salsa or guacamole.
e2e40eb5-7e29-4cb9-9edb-f6cdad09a05e
Coat an 8x 8 baking pan with oil.
e2e40eb5-7e29-4cb9-9edb-f6cdad09a05e
Combine all-purpose flour, milk powder, rapid rise yeast, salt, olive oil, and sugar in a mixing bowl.
e2e40eb5-7e29-4cb9-9edb-f6cdad09a05e
Pour lukewarm water into the dry ingredients and knead a soft, pliable dough.
e2e40eb5-7e29-4cb9-9edb-f6cdad09a05e
PROTIP If the dough is sticky, add in an extra 1 tablespoon flour and knead until it comes together like a smooth dough.
e2e40eb5-7e29-4cb9-9edb-f6cdad09a05e
Spread the focaccia dough into the greased pan. Cover the bowl with a damp towel.
e2e40eb5-7e29-4cb9-9edb-f6cdad09a05e
Place the focaccia dough in a warm place and let it rise for 30-35 minutes, or until the dough has doubled in size.
e2e40eb5-7e29-4cb9-9edb-f6cdad09a05e
Preheat oven @350 degree F. Use your fingers or the back of a spoon to poke deep indents all over the dough.
e2e40eb5-7e29-4cb9-9edb-f6cdad09a05e
Evenly brush pesto all over the top surface of the dough.
e2e40eb5-7e29-4cb9-9edb-f6cdad09a05e
Bake in a preheated oven (@350 degree F) for 18-20 minutes or until the crust is golden brown. Once done, remove from the oven.
e2e40eb5-7e29-4cb9-9edb-f6cdad09a05e
Allow it to sit on the counter for 3-4 minutes. Drizzle with olive oil, slice, and serve warm.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Pour 3/4 cup milk in a bowl. Add agar-Agar powder to the milk. Mix to combine. Let it rest for 7-8 minutes.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Assemble the paan ingredients paan leaves, fennel seeds, Gulkand (rose petal jam), and Thandai powder.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Transfer the paan ingredients to a blender. Add 2 tablespoons of water and blend until smooth.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
TIP Do not add more water.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Strain the paan mix through a fine strainer. Set aside.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Meanwhile, add cream and the remaining 1/4 cup milk to a pan. Allow it to simmer.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Add sugar. Whisk constantly until the sugar is fully dissolved and mixed in properly.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Stir in agar-agar mixture. Continue stirring for about 2-3 minutes until agar-agar is fully dissolved.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Pour in the paan mixture.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Continue stirring until the cream is steaming (do not boil).
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Remove from heat and let it cool 5 minutes. Strain the liquid through a fine strainer.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Lightly grease your ramekins or molds. Pour the mixture into 4 ramekins or bowls. Allow the panna cotta to sit at room temperature for 3-4 minutes before refrigerating. Cover with a plastic wrap and refrigerate.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Refrigerate and allow it to set for at least 5 hours.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
TIP- To unmold the paan panna cotta, place the cups (in which panna cotta is set) in lukewarm water for 2-3 minutes.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Carefully loosen the sides of the mold with a knife. Be careful not to cut through the Panna cotta. Invert the mold over a plate. Gently pat on top of the mold and jiggle it, paan panna cotta will slip out easily.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
