Garnish with thandai powder, saffron strands, and cherry.
0719ba66-0fbc-4c63-a455-635c0cf79245
Spoon rose syrup all around the panna cotta and serve.
fbb74c48-55b8-4399-9f75-e079bc124179
Rinse and soak chana dal in 1 cup of water for 3 hours. Soaking helps to aid in digestion.
fbb74c48-55b8-4399-9f75-e079bc124179
After the soaking time, soaked lentils will swell in size. Discard the soak water and rinse the soaked dal well with tap water.
fbb74c48-55b8-4399-9f75-e079bc124179
Transfer the lentils to a blender. Blend the dal until coarsely ground.
fbb74c48-55b8-4399-9f75-e079bc124179
Transfer the lentils to a mixing bowl. Add onions, spinach, ginger, green chilies, peanut powder, cilantro leaves, curry leaves, and all the spices.
fbb74c48-55b8-4399-9f75-e079bc124179
Use your hands or a spoon to mix the spices into the lentils thoroughly. Mix until all ingredients are combined.
fbb74c48-55b8-4399-9f75-e079bc124179
Separate the dal vada mixture into 12 equal portions. Shape each portion into a ball. Then, gently flatten the ball into a vada. Use your fingers to smoothen the edges of the vada.
fbb74c48-55b8-4399-9f75-e079bc124179
Repeat the process with the rest of the mixture.
fbb74c48-55b8-4399-9f75-e079bc124179
Heat oil in a pan. To check if your oil has reached the frying temperature, put the end of a wooden spoon in the oil. If the oil starts bubbling around the spoon, then the oil is ready. Add dal vada to the hot oil. Fry dal vada on medium heat for 4-6 minutes per side.
fbb74c48-55b8-4399-9f75-e079bc124179
Work in batches. Do not overcrowd the pan. Depending on the pan size fry 4-5 vadas at a time. Fry until the dal vadas are deeply golden in color, turning them halfway through the cooking.
fbb74c48-55b8-4399-9f75-e079bc124179
Once cooked, transfer the dal vada to a paper towel-lined plate to soak up excess oil. Repeat this step until all the vadas are fried.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d MARINATE PANEER In a heavy-bottomed pan, dry roast the spices.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d MARINATE PANEER Allow the spices to cool completely. Coarsely grind the spices. Set aside.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d MARINATE PANEER In a large bowl, beat the yogurt until smooth. Add the above-prepared spices to it. Mix to combine.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d MARINATE PANEER Add paneer cubes to this marinate and toss to coat. Set it aside for 30 minutes.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d PREPARE THE SAUCE Meanwhile, lets prepare the paneer kali mirch gravy. Heat 2 tablespoon ghee in a pan. Add sliced onions and cook until slightly caramelized.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d PREPARE THE SAUCE Stir in ginger-garlic paste and cook for another 1-2 minutes. Take it off the flame and allow it to cool.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d PREPARE THE SAUCE When comfortable to touch, transfer onion mixture to a blender and blend until completely smooth. If needed, you can add a teaspoon of water to create a thinner paste. Set aside.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d PREPARE THE SAUCE In a separate pan, heat the remaining 2 tablespoon ghee to the pan. Add whole spices. As they start to crackle pour-in the onion-ginger-garlic paste.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d PREPARE THE SAUCE Add green chilies and tomato puree. Sauté until the mixture starts to leave oil.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d PREPARE THE SAUCE Stir in the spices. Cook for a minute or so.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d PREPARE THE SAUCE Add cashew paste and lemon juice. Mix to combine. Cook until the oil separates.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d PREPARE THE SAUCE Return the marinated paneer cubes to the cooking curry. Mix gently.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d PREPARE THE SAUCE Add garam masala and crushed black pepper.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d PREPARE THE SAUCE Pour in 3/4 cup of water and bring the paneer kali mirch curry to a boil. Adjust water consistency to liking.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d PREPARE THE SAUCE Allow the paneer to simmer in the gravy for a few minutes. This way, it will soak up more flavors and become soft.
be4a7278-5385-48ba-9b9c-792c4df2611d PREPARE THE SAUCE Serve hot with warm Indian bread and steamed rice.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Open the tofu box and allow the packed liquid to drain completely. Layer a plate with a kitchen towel. Place tofu over it.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Cover the tofu with another layer of folded paper towel and place a big canned jar or a heavy thing over the paper towel. Let it rest for 20 minutes. This will press the extra liquid out of tofu.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
After pressing and draining liquid from the tofu, cut your block of tofu into slices (or however shape you like). Set aside.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Heat oil in a pan. Add the tofu slices.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Cook the tofu slices until golden and crisp, turning occasionally. Set aside.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Add water to a large bowl. Put it on high heat. Add salt and then add the linguine noodles to the pan and stir to combine. For al-dente noodles, boil noodles for 9-10 minutes stirring it often to keep it from sticking.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Drain the noodles in a colander. Rinse the noodles once again under tap water to wash away all the starch. Set aside.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
In a separate bowl, combine all the sauces tamari, chili garlic paste, vinegar, and hoisin sauce. Mix to combine. Set aside.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Return the same pan to the burner. Add the oil, sliced bell peppers, and carrots. Saute gently for 2-3 minutes until bell peppers are softened.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Mix in shredded cabbage. Cook for a minute.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Transfer the cooked veggies to a bowl and set aside.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Add sesame oil to the pan. Add garlic and saute for 30 seconds.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Stir in the white part of the scallions and cook for another 30 seconds. Pour in the sauce mixture. Along with the cornstarch mix. Mix to combine.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Continue to cook until the sauce thickens. Lower the flame to the lowest setting, stir in sauteed vegetables, crispy tofu slices, and the drained Linguine noodles to the pan. Toss to coat.
5337f371-faa4-43c0-a2e4-c136a84cbcdb
Serve hot! Garnish generously with green parts of scallions, nigella seeds, and cilantro leaves.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
Cut paneer into cubes. Transfer it to a large mixing bowl. Add white pepper and salt to the paneer cubes.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
Pour in oil and mix to combine. Set aside.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
In a separate bowl, combine breadcrumbs, rice flour, cornstarch, wheat flour, paprika, onion powder, garlic powder, and dried mint. Mix to combine. Set aside.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
On a separate plate, combine rice flour, cornstarch, and wheat flour. Mix well. Set it aside.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
Combine milk + vinegar in a bowl. Let it rest for 2-3 minutes until the milk curdles.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
Pour soy sauce and chili garlic sauce to the curdled milk. Mix to combine.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
Pick a piece of paneer, dip it into the flour mix thoroughly.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
Dip paneer into the buttermilk mixture.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
Finally, roll the paneer cube in the breadcrumb mix and set it on a plate.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
Repeat the process with the rest of the paneer cubes until all the pieces are evenly coated.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
Heat oil in a pan. To check if your oil has reached the frying temperature, put the end of a wooden spoon in the oil. If the oil starts bubbling around the spoon, then the oil is ready. Add paneer bites to the hot oil.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
Work in batches. Do not overcrowd the pan. Depending on the pan size fry 5-7 bites at a time. Fry until the paneer nuggets are deep golden in color, turning them halfway through the cooking.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
Once cooked, transfer the paneer nuggets to a paper towel-lined plate to soak up excess oil.
ad81c95b-4392-4541-9535-9e4f00a89551
Repeat this step until all the spicy paneer bites are cooked. Serve hot with sriracha mayonnaise.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c BAKE THE CAKE Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c BAKE THE CAKE Combine milk with vinegar in a medium bowl and set aside for 5 minutes.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c BAKE THE CAKE Meanwhile, in a large mixing bowl, sift all-purpose flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt together. Set aside.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c BAKE THE CAKE Combine sugar and oil in a mixing bowl and whisk until smooth. Add pineapple essence.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c BAKE THE CAKE Add the dry ingredient first then alternate it with milk+vinegar mixture. Mix until just combined, do not over mix the batter.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c BAKE THE CAKE Keep scraping down the sides of the bowl as needed. While the batter is getting ready, coat a 9×13 baking sheet/tray with nonstick spray. Line the bottom of the pan with parchment paper and grease again.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c BAKE THE CAKE Spread the cake batter into the prepared sheet/tray. With the help of a spreader knife, even out the batter in the tray.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c BAKE THE CAKE Bake the cake right away in a preheated oven for approximately 12-14 minutes or until the top is golden.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c BAKE THE CAKE Remove the cake from the oven. With a thin spatula loosen the edges of the cake from all sides. Place a fresh parchment paper on top of a wire rack and carefully flip over the cake onto the lined wired rack.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c BAKE THE CAKE Immediately peel the parchment paper from the flipped cake and discard it. Measure and slice the cake in half. Allow the eggless cake sheets to cool completely.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c ASSEMBLE THE PINEAPPLE PASTRY On a rectangular cake board, place the first layer of cake top side down.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c ASSEMBLE THE PINEAPPLE PASTRY Use a fork to poke holes over the cake. Pour the pineapple juice all over the top of the cake, making sure it goes in the holes.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c ASSEMBLE THE PINEAPPLE PASTRY Pipe the whipped cream frosting all over the juice-drizzled cake.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c ASSEMBLE THE PINEAPPLE PASTRY Place the other half of the cake over the frosted cake. Repeat the process again poke cake with a fork, drizzle pineapple juice all over the holes.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c ASSEMBLE THE PINEAPPLE PASTRY Layer with whipped cream frosting. Finally, finish the pineapple pastry with whipped cream frosting.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c ASSEMBLE THE PINEAPPLE PASTRY For a smooth finish, place a large dollop of whipped cream on top of the cake. Spread the frosting cleanly around the top and sides of the cake.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c ASSEMBLE THE PINEAPPLE PASTRY Dip a clean, offset spatula in boiling water and smooth out the frosting all over the cake.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c ASSEMBLE THE PINEAPPLE PASTRY Divide the pastry into 10 equal-size slices.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c ASSEMBLE THE PINEAPPLE PASTRY Decorate each slice of eggless pineapple pastry with a swirl of whipped cream, pineapple slices, and maraschino cherries.
dd7178ee-3185-410e-ad4b-c7382bee8c2c ASSEMBLE THE PINEAPPLE PASTRY Set in refrigerator to chill.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a PRE- PREPARATIONS Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Grease and line your muffin pans with 12 cupcake liners. Set aside.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a PRE- PREPARATIONS Combine milk and vinegar in a bowl. Whisk it well. Set aside for 5 minutes to curdle.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a MAKING RED VELVET CUPCAKES In a large mixing bowl, whisk together all-purpose flour, cornstarch, cocoa powder, baking soda, baking powder, and salt.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a MAKING RED VELVET CUPCAKES Sift them to remove lumps of flour and cocoa powder. Set it aside.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a MAKING RED VELVET CUPCAKES Combine butter and sugar in the mixing bowl of an electric mixer.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a MAKING RED VELVET CUPCAKES Using a whisk or balloon attachment, cream butter and sugar together on medium speed for 4-5 minutes. Add vanilla essence to the bowl.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a MAKING RED VELVET CUPCAKES Add the red food coloring, milk + vinegar combo (buttermilk) to the mixing bowl.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a MAKING RED VELVET CUPCAKES Mix in the dry ingredient. Mix until just combined, do not over mix the batter. Keep scraping down the sides of the bowl as needed.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a MAKING RED VELVET CUPCAKES Evenly distribute the batter between 12 cupcake liners. Fill each liner about halfway full.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a MAKING RED VELVET CUPCAKES Bake in a preheated oven for 20-25 minutes or until the toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a MAKING RED VELVET CUPCAKES Once baked, remove from the oven and set the muffin pans on the kitchen counter.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a MAKING RED VELVET CUPCAKES Carefully remove the cupcakes from the pan and transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a BUTTERCREAM FROSTING Beat vegan butter for 5 minutes until light and airy. Butter will lose most of its yellow color at this point.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a BUTTERCREAM FROSTING Slowly add powdered sugar/icing sugar (spoon by spoon) and beat until it is well blended.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a BUTTERCREAM FROSTING Add milk to thin out its consistency.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a BUTTERCREAM FROSTING Mix again. Icing is suitable for 1-2 weeks in your fridge and a month in your freezer.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a BUTTERCREAM FROSTING Frost the cooled cupcakes with swirls of buttercream frosting and garnish with few crumbles of red velvet cupcake.
1bc979a0-f032-40d0-bb60-df52f7fb545a BUTTERCREAM FROSTING Note I used my Wilton 1M piping tip to frost my cupcakes.
965e691c-a9a4-4aef-bb37-670ca4f3ba3a
Preheat the oven @350 degrees F. Transfer the softened butter and sugar to a mixing bowl. PROTIP Before you start, allow butter to come to room temperature. Butter and sugar will blend easily if they are at room temperature.
965e691c-a9a4-4aef-bb37-670ca4f3ba3a
On medium speed, cream butter and sugar until they are light in color. While the butter+sugar is creaming, add in almond extract.
965e691c-a9a4-4aef-bb37-670ca4f3ba3a
Meanwhile, sift the dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
965e691c-a9a4-4aef-bb37-670ca4f3ba3a
Lower the speed setting to low and slowly spoon the dry ingredients into the butter+sugar mixture. Mix until fully incorporated. Do not over-mix the dough.
965e691c-a9a4-4aef-bb37-670ca4f3ba3a
The finished dough should look like a stiff frosting. Scrape down the sides of the stand mixer bowl to ensure even mixing of the ingredients.
965e691c-a9a4-4aef-bb37-670ca4f3ba3a
Transfer the dough to a pastry bag. I have used a Star nozzle to make these cookies.
965e691c-a9a4-4aef-bb37-670ca4f3ba3a
Pipe the dough like rosettes.
965e691c-a9a4-4aef-bb37-670ca4f3ba3a
PROTIP For the rosettes, the best practice is to pipe a few on some parchment first. This will release any trapped air, and you will end up with perfect rosettes.
965e691c-a9a4-4aef-bb37-670ca4f3ba3a
Chill the tray in the refrigerator for 20 mins before baking. Chilling the dough will prevent the cookies from being flat.
965e691c-a9a4-4aef-bb37-670ca4f3ba3a
Transfer the swirl shortbread butter cookies to the hot oven and bake for 10-12 minutes or until very lightly browned on the edges.
965e691c-a9a4-4aef-bb37-670ca4f3ba3a
Once done, remove from the oven. Allow the spritz cookies to cool on the baking sheet for 4-5 minutes before transferring them to a wire rack.
965e691c-a9a4-4aef-bb37-670ca4f3ba3a
The eggless butter cookies will still be soft when out of the oven. Allow them to cool completely, and they will become firm.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca BOILING MATAR Measure the peas and quickly glance over them and discard any shriveled or unappealing peas. Rinse and soak the dried white peas or matar for 6-8 hours or overnight.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca BOILING MATAR The next morning, matar or white peas will have absorbed enough water and nearly doubled in size.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca BOILING MATAR Drain the peas from their soaking water. Rinse the matar or dried white peas gently under tap water. Transfer the matar to the Instant Pot insert and pour in 3 cups of water. Add salt and mix to combine. Seal the lid. The valve on top should be in the sealed position. Press the Bean/Chili button and cook on High Pressure for 15 minutes.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca BOILING MATAR Once the Instant Pot beeps, let the pressure release naturally. When the pin drops, open the lid. Cover the cooked peas with a lid and allow it to rest while we assemble the rest of the ingredients.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca COOK MATAR IN AN INDIAN PRESSURE COOKER Rinse and soak the dried white peas or matar for 6-8 hours or overnight. After the soaking time is over, drain the peas from their soaking water. Rinse the matar or dried white peas gently under tap water. Transfer the matar to a pressure cooker. Pour in water, add salt and stir to combine. Close the lid and pressure cook the matar for 3-4 whistles.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca COOK MATAR IN AN INDIAN PRESSURE COOKER After the cooking time is done, take the pressure cooker off the heat. Allow the steam to release naturally. Open the lid and check matar. It should be soft and slightly mushy. Follow the recipe below.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca ASSEMBLING MATAR Transfer the cooked matar to a large mixing bowl.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca ASSEMBLING MATAR Add chopped onions and tomatoes to the matar.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca ASSEMBLING MATAR Generously sprinkle green chutney and tamarind chutney over the cooked matar kulcha recipe.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca ASSEMBLING MATAR Add chaat masala, roasted cumin seeds, chopped green chilies, and red chili powder over the matar.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca ASSEMBLING MATAR PROTIP- If the matar feels dry, add 1.5 teaspoons of oil to the chaat.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca ASSEMBLING MATAR Finally, add julienned slivers of ginger and chopped cilantro leaves. Toss until combined.
d796d8f7-5791-4137-9abe-47efd18af5ca ASSEMBLING MATAR Serve hot garnished with some more julienned slivers of ginger, chopped onions, diced tomatoes, and lemon juice.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Heat oil in a pan. Once the oil is hot, add carrots to it. On medium heat, cook carrots for 2-3 minutes until they are fork-tender.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Add cabbage to the pan and cook for another 1 minute.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Stir in chopped scallions (green onions) and mix to combine.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Pour in cream of corn. Stir to combine.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Pour in tamari. The non-gluten-free option is soy sauce.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Add salt, pepper, and vinegar to this sweet corn soup mix.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Pour in water or vegetable stock. Stir to combine.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Cover the pot and allow the veggies to simmer on medium heat for 4-5 minutes.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Dissolve 1 tablespoon of cornstarch in 1/3 cup of water. Whisk it well until blended. Make sure there are no lumps in the cornflour mixture.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
If there are lumps in the mixture, sieve it through a strainer and then add it to the cooking sweet corn soup. Stir it well.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Add sugar to the sweet corn soup and mix it well.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Lower the heat to the lowest setting and allow the soup to boil for 2-3 minutes.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Because of cornstarch, the soup will start to thicken. Take it off the heat.
672d85c0-ad5f-4bb4-991e-57f8474ffa7c
Garnish the sweet corn soup with scallions, corn kernels, and serve hot with the bread of your choice.
38d8d54d-092b-48b6-a852-3e3f1692f072 PREPARE THE BASE LAYER Preheat oven at 425 degrees F. Grease an 8-inch pre-seasoned cast iron skillet.
38d8d54d-092b-48b6-a852-3e3f1692f072 PREPARE THE BASE LAYER Combine shredded potatoes, oil, salt, and pepper in a large bowl.
38d8d54d-092b-48b6-a852-3e3f1692f072 PREPARE THE BASE LAYER Transfer this hash brown mixture to the greased cast-iron skillet, pressing it down to pack it firmly around the edges and to the bottom of the skillet. It will look like an unbaked pie-crust.
38d8d54d-092b-48b6-a852-3e3f1692f072 PREPARE THE BASE LAYER Bake this frittata recipe in the preheated oven for about 25 minutes or until the edges and top have browned. Once the hash brown crust is cooked, remove from the oven and turn the oven off.
38d8d54d-092b-48b6-a852-3e3f1692f072 THE TOP LAYER While the hash brown layer is cooking, lets prepare the top egg layer. In a large bowl, whisk eggs, salt, and pepper.
38d8d54d-092b-48b6-a852-3e3f1692f072 THE TOP LAYER Add milk, whisk until frothy.
38d8d54d-092b-48b6-a852-3e3f1692f072 THE TOP LAYER Add chopped scallions, bell peppers, tomatoes, and spinach to the egg mixture. Stir to combine. Set aside.
38d8d54d-092b-48b6-a852-3e3f1692f072 THE TOP LAYER PROTIP- De-seed your tomatoes before adding them to the egg mixture.
38d8d54d-092b-48b6-a852-3e3f1692f072 THE TOP LAYER Preheat oven at 350 degrees F. Evenly spread the shredded cheddar cheese at the top of the baked hash brown crust.
38d8d54d-092b-48b6-a852-3e3f1692f072 THE TOP LAYER Pour the egg mixture into the baked crust and bake the frittata for 30-35 minutes at 350 degrees F until golden brown and the middle is set or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
38d8d54d-092b-48b6-a852-3e3f1692f072 THE TOP LAYER Once cooked, remove from oven and allow it to cool for at least 10 minutes before serving.
7db98a25-7f27-4c36-bdb5-4fff6f683b0d
Wash and thoroughly dry the chicken drumsticks. Remove the skin.
7db98a25-7f27-4c36-bdb5-4fff6f683b0d
In a separate bowl, combine dried oregano, dried thyme, cayenne pepper, salt, pepper, garlic powder, onion powder, and dried rosemary. Pour in oil and mix to combine.
7db98a25-7f27-4c36-bdb5-4fff6f683b0d
Pour this mixture over the chicken legs. Rub the herb marinade in every part of the chicken legs.
7db98a25-7f27-4c36-bdb5-4fff6f683b0d BAKING CHICKEN LEGS IN MEALTHY CRISPLID Spread the chicken legs into a single layer.
7db98a25-7f27-4c36-bdb5-4fff6f683b0d BAKING CHICKEN LEGS IN MEALTHY CRISPLID Put the Mealthy Crisplid on and bake at 375 degrees F for 20 minutes or so until the chicken begins to brown, turning halfway during the cooking time.
7db98a25-7f27-4c36-bdb5-4fff6f683b0d BAKING CHICKEN LEGS IN MEALTHY CRISPLID As the chicken bakes, it will pick up all the flavors of the herbs, and the oil in the marinade will ensure that the chicken drumsticks stay juicy and moist.
7db98a25-7f27-4c36-bdb5-4fff6f683b0d BAKING CHICKEN LEGS IN MEALTHY CRISPLID PROTIP For the pearl onions, peel and rinse onions in tap water. Pat them dry. Toss in the oil-herb marinade and arrange in a single layer in the Mealthy CrispLid tray Bake at 375 degrees F for 6 minutes.
7db98a25-7f27-4c36-bdb5-4fff6f683b0d BAKING CHICKEN LEGS IN MEALTHY CRISPLID Onions bake quickly; therefore, I have baked them separately.
7db98a25-7f27-4c36-bdb5-4fff6f683b0d BAKING CHICKEN IN THE OVEN Preheat oven at 375 degrees F.
7db98a25-7f27-4c36-bdb5-4fff6f683b0d BAKING CHICKEN IN THE OVEN Grease a grill tray. Arrange chicken in a single layer.
7db98a25-7f27-4c36-bdb5-4fff6f683b0d BAKING CHICKEN IN THE OVEN Bake in a preheated oven for 25-30 minutes or so until the chicken begins to brown, turning halfway during the cooking time.
7db98a25-7f27-4c36-bdb5-4fff6f683b0d BAKING CHICKEN IN THE OVEN Remove from the oven. Generously drizzle fresh lemon juice on chicken legs and serve hot garnished with fresh herbs and lemon wedges.
e33ff7ec-ac3a-4264-913f-4fbd9442add6
Dry roast the fine sooji or semolina on medium-low heat for 5-7 minutes until fragrant.
e33ff7ec-ac3a-4264-913f-4fbd9442add6
keep stirring continuously. Be careful as sooji gets burned quickly. Therefore, so not leave sooji unattended at any time. Once done, transfer the roasted sooji to a clean plate and set aside.
e33ff7ec-ac3a-4264-913f-4fbd9442add6
To the same pan, add 1 tablespoon oil. Add cashew pieces to the hot oil and cook for 2-3 minutes until lightly golden. Remove cashews from the pan and set aside.
e33ff7ec-ac3a-4264-913f-4fbd9442add6
To the same pan, add the remaining oil. Add mustard seeds and allow them to crackle.
e33ff7ec-ac3a-4264-913f-4fbd9442add6
Add hing to the mustard seeds. Stir in chopped onions and mix to combine. Cook onions for 2 minutes until translucent.
e33ff7ec-ac3a-4264-913f-4fbd9442add6
Add chopped carrots and cook for another 3-4 minutes stirring occasionally. Stir in soaked chana dal and curry leaves.
e33ff7ec-ac3a-4264-913f-4fbd9442add6
Add frozen peas and mix to combine. Cook for 2 minutes until the peas lose their frozen smell. Stir in red chili powder and salt. Mix to combine.
e33ff7ec-ac3a-4264-913f-4fbd9442add6
Pour in lukewarm water, lemon juice, and sugar. Bring the water to a boil. When the water starts boiling, add roasted sooji and stir the spoon in the clockwise direction continuously to combine.
e33ff7ec-ac3a-4264-913f-4fbd9442add6
Cover the pan with a lid. Allow the sooji to simmer on a low heat for 3-4 minutes until sooji absorbs all the water.
e33ff7ec-ac3a-4264-913f-4fbd9442add6
After the desired time is over, remove from heat and uncover the pan. Allow the upma to rest for 4-5 minutes in the pan. Fluff upma with a fork and serve hot with the chutney of your choice.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab PREPARING THE DOUGH Clean and wash methi leaves. Trim the leaves and discard the stems.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab PREPARING THE DOUGH Using a sharp knife coarsely chop methi leaves.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab PREPARING THE DOUGH Combine whole-wheat flour, chickpea flour, onion, chopped methi leaves, and spices in a large mixing bowl.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab PREPARING THE DOUGH Mix until all the dry ingredients are combined. Set it aside for 10 minutes.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab PREPARING THE DOUGH PROTIP- Allow the methi and flour mixture to rest for a while. Methi will release its water, and therefore less water will be required to knead the dough.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab PREPARING THE DOUGH By now, methi leaves should have released their water content, therefore add the water very slowly. Add just enough water to knead a soft dough. Pour in oil and finish the dough.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab PREPARING THE DOUGH Cover the dough with a damp cloth and let it rest for 10-15 minutes.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab ROLL AND COOK THE PARATHA After the resting time, divide the dough into 8 equal-sized balls.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab ROLL AND COOK THE PARATHA Dust the ball with flour. Flatten the ball. Roll the balls to a 5-6 inch circle, dusting with flour as and when needed.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab ROLL AND COOK THE PARATHA Heat a skillet/tawa. Transfer the rolled Methi ka paratha to the hot skillet. Apply oil and cook the paratha from both sides.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab ROLL AND COOK THE PARATHA Press down with a spatula to ensure proper cooking. Cook until the paratha has dark spots on both sides.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab ROLL AND COOK THE PARATHA Transfer the cooked paratha onto a plate. Remove from heat and repeat the process with the rest of the dough balls.
79a196bd-1fbf-4cfd-a6f1-d7101297ffab ROLL AND COOK THE PARATHA Serve them hot with raita or pickle of your choice.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 1: BLANCH SPINACH Clean and trim spinach leaves. Wash them thoroughly under cold water.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 1: BLANCH SPINACH Boil water in a pan. Add spinach rinsed spinach leaves to it and let it boil for 2-3 minutes.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 1: BLANCH SPINACH After the boiling time is over, use a slotting spoon to remove the spinach leaves from water and immediately plunge it into a large bowl full of ice water.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 1: BLANCH SPINACH This will stop the cooking process. Remove spinach from water and tightly squeeze out all of the excess water from the spinach leaves. Form a small ball and store it in a Ziploc bag. Freeze for future use.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 1: BLANCH SPINACH Transfer the blanched spinach to a blender and blend until smooth. Blanched spinach is ready. Set it aside.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 2: MARINATE CHICKEN In a large mixing bowl, combine yogurt (thick hung curd) with red chili powder, coriander powder, kasoori methi, garam masala, salt, and lemon juice. Whisk until combined.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 2: MARINATE CHICKEN Place the chicken cubes in a deep dish. Pour the marinade over the chicken cubes.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 2: MARINATE CHICKEN Rub the marinade all over the chicken cubes making sure it is well coated. Cover and refrigerate for 3-4 hours.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 3: COOK THE MARINATED CHICKEN After the resting time is over, heat ghee in a heavy-bottomed pan. Add the marinated chicken to the pan.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 3: COOK THE MARINATED CHICKEN Continue cooking on medium-high heat, frequently stirring until the chicken is cooked. Remove from heat, and set aside.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 4: ASSEMBLING SPINACH AND CHICKEN TOGETHER Heat mustard oil in a pan. Mustard oil has a very strong flavor. Therefore, to get rid of that pungent flavor, cook mustard oil to its smoking point and take it off the flame. Let it cool.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 4: ASSEMBLING SPINACH AND CHICKEN TOGETHER When ready to make the masala slightly warm the mustard oil and add whole spices and cumin seeds to the pan.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 4: ASSEMBLING SPINACH AND CHICKEN TOGETHER As the seeds start to crackle, add onion and ginger-garlic paste. Mix to combine. Sauté for 3-4 minutes until the oil starts to separate.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 4: ASSEMBLING SPINACH AND CHICKEN TOGETHER Stir in the tomato puree. Mix to combine.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 4: ASSEMBLING SPINACH AND CHICKEN TOGETHER Stir in all the spices coriander powder, chili powder, kasoori methi, garam masala, and salt. Mix until combined.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 4: ASSEMBLING SPINACH AND CHICKEN TOGETHER Cook the tomatoes for another 3-4 minutes or until the oil separates.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 4: ASSEMBLING SPINACH AND CHICKEN TOGETHER Pour in the blanched spinach puree. Stir to combine.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 4: ASSEMBLING SPINACH AND CHICKEN TOGETHER Add chicken pieces to the blanched spinach. Cook for another 3-4 minutes on medium-low heat, stirring occasionally.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 4: ASSEMBLING SPINACH AND CHICKEN TOGETHER Finally, add the cream. Give it a gentle stir and take it off the flame.
f894ed44-e405-4c84-9a03-35acdbd37368 STEP 4: ASSEMBLING SPINACH AND CHICKEN TOGETHER Serve hot with warm rotis, naan or white rice.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. In the bowl of your stand mixer, combine the Duncan Hines Classic Yellow Cake Mix with eggs, oil, and water.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Mix on low speed for 20 seconds. After that, increase the speed to medium; mix for another 3 minutes, scraping the sides of the bowl as necessary.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE While the batter is getting ready, coat a 15×21 baking sheet/tray with nonstick spray. Line the bottom of the pan with parchment paper and grease again.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Spread the cake batter into the prepared sheet/tray. With the help of a spreader knife, even out the batter in the tray.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Bake the cake right away in a preheated oven for approximately 12-14 minutes or until the top is golden. A deliciously moist cake made with Duncan Hines Classic Yellow Cake Mix is ready.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE But since I am making a Yule log cake, we will advance to the next step.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Remove the cake from the oven. With a thin spatula loosen the edges of the cake from all sides. Dust the top with confectioners sugar.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Take a thin (damp) kitchen towel and a fresh sheet of parchment paper. Dust them with a generous amount of confectioners /powdered sugar too. Lay the parchment paper first, then the towel on top of the cake.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Finally, place a wire rack on top of the kitchen towel and carefully flip over the cake onto the towel. Immediately peel the parchment paper from the flipped cake and discard it.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Dust the other side (flipped side) of the cake too with confectioners sugar.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Time to roll the cake. Start from one end and begin rolling the cake gently. Do not apply too much pressure. Roll with the towel and parchment paper. The towel and paper will get folded along with the cake. Roll till the end. The towel will prevent the cake from cracking.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Allow the rolled cake to rest for an hour at room temperature.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Once the cake has cooled, carefully unroll the cake along with the towel and parchment paper.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Spread the Duncan Hines Creamy Home-Style Frosting Classic Chocolate over the unrolled cooled cake.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE PROTIP Layer the cake with a very thin frosting layer. We do not want to overdo on the frosting because it will start to ooze out of the cake when we begin to re-roll the cake again.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Once the frosting is evenly spread, its time to re-roll the cake again.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE PROTIP Begin rolling the cake in the same direction, just like the first time you had rolled it.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE This time you will not roll the towel or paper inside the cake. This time, we will lift the parchment paper as we re-roll the cake.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a MAKING OF CAKE Line a tray with a fresh parchment paper. Carefully lift and transfer the rolled cake onto that lined tray with the folded side down. Refrigerate the cake until we prepare the chocolate ganache.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a PREPARE CHOCOLATE GANACHE Melt butter in a small pan on medium heat.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a PREPARE CHOCOLATE GANACHE When the butter has melted, whisk in cocoa powder, sugar, cream, and vanilla essence.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a PREPARE CHOCOLATE GANACHE Remove from heat and whisk until smooth and creamy.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a PREPARE CHOCOLATE GANACHE Allow it to cool for a couple of minutes. Keep stirring.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a PREPARE CHOCOLATE GANACHE Immediately pour the ganache over the cake. Spread the ganache evenly all over the cake.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a PREPARE CHOCOLATE GANACHE The ganache will thicken as it cools, therefore spread it over the cake while it is still warm.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a PREPARE CHOCOLATE GANACHE Chill the cake roll in the refrigerator for 3-4 hours.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a PREPARE CHOCOLATE GANACHE Once the cake has cooled completely, use a fork to make the marks on the yule log that resembles a bark.
519df9d9-a72b-4db8-a877-16a41e9d2f5a PREPARE CHOCOLATE GANACHE Decorate the yule cake as you please. I have decorated my Yule Log cake with fresh cranberries and rosemary sprigs.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF CORN DIP Begin by caramelizing corn kernels in a pan. Over medium-high heat, add oil or butter to a heavy-bottomed pan. Add corn and cook for 12 to 15 minutes or until corn starts to brown, stirring occasionally. Once the corn kernels are brown, remove from heat and set aside to cool.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF CORN DIP Preheat oven to 350°F. In a large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, and mayonnaise.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF CORN DIP Stir in the spices chili flakes, cumin powder, garlic powder, and salt. Add 1/4 cup of shredded cheese. Using a blender, blend all the ingredients until they are thoroughly combined and smooth.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF CORN DIP Add chopped onions, red bell pepper, and cooled caramelized corn kernels.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF CORN DIP Now lets add some flavor and zest to this recipe. Add RO*TEL® Original Diced Tomatoes and Green Chilies to the cream cheese+ mayonnaise mixture. Mix to combine.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF CORN DIP Pour the corn dip mix into an oven-safe baking dish. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF CORN DIP Bake in a preheated oven for 25-30 minutes or until the cheese is hot and bubbly.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF CORN DIP Serve hot with the chips of your choice.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF CORN DIP If baking just the corn dip cooking time is as follows Prep time: 10 minutes + Cook Time: 22 minutes = Total time: 32 minutes
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS Combine flour, sugar, instant yeast, and salt in a large bowl.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS In a microwavable bowl, melt butter. Remove from heat and add milk. Whisk to combine. Set aside for a minute.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS Pour lukewarm milk + butter over the dry ingredients and knead a soft, pliable dough.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS The dough should be smooth. If it is sticky, add a tablespoon of flour and knead the dough until smooth.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS Cover the dough with a wet cloth and let it rise in a warm place for about 1.5 hours.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS Line an 18-inch round pizza tray with parchment paper. Place a 4-inch round bowl in the center.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS By now, the dough must have doubled in size. Transfer the dough onto a lightly dusted floured surface. Punch it down and knead the dough for 3-4 minutes.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS Divide the dough evenly into 31 pieces. Shape the dough into balls. Fold and secure all the ends of the dough until it looks like a smooth ball.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS Arrange the balls all around the bowl in a ring shape.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS The outer ring will have 18 pieces, and the inner circle will have 13 pieces.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS Cover the tray with a wet towel and let it rise in a warm place for another 45 minutes or until the dough balls double in size.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS Preheat oven to 350°F. Once the dough has doubled in size, remove the bowl from the center.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS Before adding the corn dip inside the wreath bread, we need to make a slight variation. To match the baking temperature, microwave the corn dip for 2-3 minutes to melt the cheeses. Remove from microwave and stir to combine.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS Now arrange the cheesy corn dip in the center. Sprinkle the remaining cheese.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS Bake in a preheated oven for 18-20 minutes or until the rolls are all golden, and the cheese is all melted and the dip is golden and bubbly.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS Brush the freshly-baked pull-apart dinner rolls with melted butter and server hot.
f87698ab-37d5-4c83-9d34-ea17fc51b8b8 MAKING OF PULL-APART WREATH ROLLS If making the corn dip with the pull-apart wreath bread Prep time: 30 minutes + Resting Time: 2 hours + Cook time: 18 minutes = Total Time: 2 hours 48 minutes
fd43cf21-1823-4726-a6f0-b7405d858e95
Combine 3/4 cup flour, sugar, dry yeast and salt in a large mixer bowl and stir until blended. Combine milk, water, and butter in a small microwave-safe bowl.
fd43cf21-1823-4726-a6f0-b7405d858e95
Microwave on HIGH in 15-second increments until very warm but not hot to the touch. Add lukewarm water (heated to 120F-130F) and if you are not sure always use a thermometer to check the temperature. Add the milk+water mix to the flour mixture.
fd43cf21-1823-4726-a6f0-b7405d858e95
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally. Add 1/4 cup flour; beat 2 minutes at high speed.
fd43cf21-1823-4726-a6f0-b7405d858e95
Stir in the remaining flour. Add garlic-herb seasoning and mix. The dough will form into a ball.
fd43cf21-1823-4726-a6f0-b7405d858e95
Time to pamper the dough. Transfer the dough on to a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
fd43cf21-1823-4726-a6f0-b7405d858e95
Transfer the dough to a bowl. Cover with a towel. As with any other bread, these garlic skillet rolls also need some time alone, therefore, let the dough rest for 10 minutes.
fd43cf21-1823-4726-a6f0-b7405d858e95
Cut dough into 12 equal pieces; shape into balls using your hands. Place in greased 8-inch round or square pan.
fd43cf21-1823-4726-a6f0-b7405d858e95
Cover with towel; let rise in a warm place until doubled in size, about 30 minutes. For pillowy-soft and fluffy dinner rolls, the second rise is an important step. After the resting time, generously top these skillet rolls with garlic herb seasoning.
fd43cf21-1823-4726-a6f0-b7405d858e95
Bake in preheated 375ºF oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown. These garlic rolls will bake up beautifully in a cast-iron skillet because cast iron retains the heat really well, and you end up with nice crusty rolls.
fd43cf21-1823-4726-a6f0-b7405d858e95
Brush the freshly-baked rolls with additional melted butter and serve warm.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a THAI PEANUT SAUCE Lets begin by making the peanut sauce first. In a small bowl, add brown sugar.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a THAI PEANUT SAUCE Add all the remaining sauce ingredients to the same bowl and stir to combine. Mix the peanut sauce until smooth and creamy. Set aside. PROTIP- Instead of stirring all the ingredients with hand, you can transfer all the ingredients to a food processor or a blender and puree it to perfection. This way, you will end up in a creamy and thick peanut sauce.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES Meanwhile, transfer the gluten-free pad Thai noodles to a large bowl. Pour hot boiling water just enough to cover the noodles.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES Stir and make sure the Thai noodles are submerged in water.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES Cover the bowl and let the noodles sit undisturbed for 5-6 minutes or until al dente. (follow the instructions on the package)
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES PROTIP After the resting time is over, drain the noodles and toss with little oil to prevent sticking. Set aside.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES Remove the Mori-Nu Silken Tofu Extra Firm one from the packet. Briefly press it and cut it into cubes.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES Heat oil in a heavy-bottomed skillet. Once the oil is hot, add tofu and season it with paprika and red chili flakes.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES Sauté it for 3-4 minutes until evenly brown on each side, turning occasionally. When cooked on both sides, remove and set aside.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES To the same pan, add chopped garlic, sauté for 1-2 minutes. Add bell peppers and cook for about 1-2 minutes.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES Take the skillet off the heat. Add chopped scallions. Mix everything to combine. Spread all the ingredients around to make room for the noodles.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES Add pad Thai noodles and bean sprouts. Top with more scallions, browned tofu, cilantro leaves, and coarsely crushed peanuts.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES Finally, add the flavor-booster Thai peanut sauce that we had prepared earlier in the recipe. Return it to the heat and cook for another 2-3 minutes on medium-low heat, tossing occasionally.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES PROTIP- Use tongs to mix all the ingredients until everything is coated in the peanut sauce.
aea2fc5b-1cd1-41aa-a42a-6d96af5e817a PAD THAI NOODLES Remove from heat and serve. To serve, garnish the Vegan Pad Thai noodles with lemon wedges, additional bean sprouts, scallions, cilantro, and black sesame seeds (optional).
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
The recipe starts by peeling the butternut squash. Its a tough job, but with this simple trick, you can easily peel and de-seed a butternut squash. Clean butternut squash with a wet towel to remove dirt or grits. Poke holes in the squash.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
Microwave on HIGH for 3-4 minutes. Microwaving it will soften the skin and make it easy to peel.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
After 3 minutes, carefully remove the squash from the microwave. Allow it to cool for 2-3 minutes. Peel the outer layer. Slice the top and end off.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
Cut squash into the half. Using a spoon, remove seeds from the squash. Cut the butternut squash into cubes.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
Preheat oven @375 degrees F. Grease a baking dish. Add cubed butternut squash, carrots chopped into cubes, celery, garlic cloves, bay leaves, and black peppercorns to this dish.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
Spray olive oil and add sea salt. Mix it well. Make sure garlic is not on top of the vegetables as it burns quickly.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
Bake in the preheated oven (375 degrees F) for 30 minutes or until the veggies are fork-tender.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
Wash lentils and pressure cook lentils for 1 whistle(5-10 minutes) until soft. Red lentils lose their shape and often end up mushy during pressure cooking. No worries at all. Set it aside.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
check on the veggies. When they are fork-tender (meaning when the fork slides through the baked vegetables without any resistance), remove from oven.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook until translucent. Add baked veggies and cook for 5 minutes.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
Pour in vegetable stock and season with spices.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
Add the cooked lentils to this vegetable mix.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
Give it a good mix. Cook veggies for another 5 minutes. This allows the veggies to blend beautifully with cooked lentils and vegetable stock. Remove bay leaves and discard.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
Use an immersion blender to blend the veggies+lentil mix until smooth and creamy. Bring it to a boil. Adjust seasonings to taste.
fc00751e-446c-484f-b0da-cdf9c0bc059a
Take it off the flame. Pour in soup bowls. Finally, complete the soup with a drizzle of coconut cream, chopped green onions, and pomegranate seeds. Serve hot!
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc ROASTED RED BELL PEPPER AND TOMATO SAUCE Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Brush the baking tray with oil. Cut bell peppers in quarters. Discard the stem and the seeds. Likewise, cut tomatoes into quarters. Arrange tomatoes and bell pepper on the greased baking tray.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc ROASTED RED BELL PEPPER AND TOMATO SAUCE Place the halved side down on the baking tray. Brush with oil. Roast the bell peppers and tomatoes until tender and slightly charred. It will take about 20-22 minutes.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc ROASTED RED BELL PEPPER AND TOMATO SAUCE Remove from the oven and allow them to cool completely. Transfer the roasted bell peppers and tomatoes to a blender.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc ROASTED RED BELL PEPPER AND TOMATO SAUCE Pour in the tomato puree and blend until smooth and creamy. Set it aside
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc CUT THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH Clean butternut squash with a wet towel to remove dirt or grits. Poke holes in the squash. Microwave on HIGH for 3-4 minutes. Microwaving it will soften the skin and make it easy to peel.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc CUT THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH After the cooking time is over, carefully remove the squash from the microwave.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc CUT THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH Lay the butternut squash on a chopping board. Allow it to cool. Once the butternut squash is cool enough to handle, peel the outer layer with a sharp peeler.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc CUT THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH Slice the top and end off. Using a spoon, scoop out the seeds and flesh attached to the seeds. Cut the butternut squash into cubes and set it aside.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Turn the Instant Pot to Saute mode. Once it displays hot, add avocado oil to the insert. Add cumin seeds, bay leaves, black peppercorns to the oil. Sauté for 1-2 minutes. This way, the spices will release more flavor.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Stir in ginger-garlic paste. Cook for 2-3 minutes. Stir in chopped onions. Cook until its soft and translucent.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Add green chilies to the cooking onions. Cook for 1 minute.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Add the spices. Add the roasted bell pepper and tomato sauce (that was prepared earlier in the recipe). Mix to combine.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Pour in vegetable stock to deglaze the Instant Pot insert.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Add chopped zucchini. Mix until incorporated in the sauce.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Add the butternut squash. Make sure the squash pieces are submerged in the sauce. Do not stir.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Turn the Instant Pot off. Close the lid and seal the pot. Press the Manual or pressure cook button and cook the Instant Pot Butternut squash curry for 6 minutes on HIGH.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Once the cooking time has elapsed, turn off the Instant Pot. Allow the pressure to release naturally for 10 minutes, then do a quick pressure release. When the pin drops, carefully open the lid.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Stir in chopped spinach leaves. Spinach leaves will wilt in the hot curry.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Taste and adjust the recipe to suit your preferences.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Add lemon juice to the curry. Lemon juice will enhance the flavors more and add a burst of freshness.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Bring the curry to a light boil until all the flavors are blended together.
f21251c6-3b48-408f-9406-bec51d708dcc PREPARE THE BUTTERNUT SQUASH CURRY Serve the Instant Pot Butternut squash curry over rice and enjoy!
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 KAJU (CASHEW) LAYER Transfer 2/3 cup raw cashews to a food processor. Do not overcrowd the grinder or processor.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 KAJU (CASHEW) LAYER Grind in batches. I have done 2/3 cups of cashews in 3 batches. Pulse until it forms a fine flour-like texture.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 KAJU (CASHEW) LAYER Sift the cashew powder through a sieve.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 KAJU (CASHEW) LAYER If there are larger cashew pieces left behind in the strainer, collect them all and blend again until it turns into a fine powder. Set it aside.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 KAJU (CASHEW) LAYER PROTIP Do not over-blend the cashews, or it could turn into cashew butter. If the cashew powder looks sticky, then the cashews have released their oil, and you need to start all over again.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 SUGAR SYRUP 1 THREAD CHASNI Time to prepare the sugar syrup. Combine sugar and water in a pan. Add rose essence to the boiling syrup. Feel free to try other flavors like cardamom or kewara.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 SUGAR SYRUP 1 THREAD CHASNI Bring this mixture to a boil. Boil until it reaches 112 degrees C. Thats the perfect temperature to 1-thread consistency ( 1-taar chashni).
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 SUGAR SYRUP 1 THREAD CHASNI To check for consistency, carefully take a drop of this sugar syrup in between your index finger and thumb.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 SUGAR SYRUP 1 THREAD CHASNI Press down firmly on the syrup and slowly pull apart the fingers. The sugar syrup will form a string in between your two fingers. Your 1-thread sugar syrup is ready. Be very careful this is a boiling syrup. Therefore, I would highly recommend using a cooking thermometer.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 ASSEMBLING KAJU AND SUGAR MIXTURE Reduce the heat and add powdered cashew to the sugar syrup. Stir to combine.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 ASSEMBLING KAJU AND SUGAR MIXTURE Add milk powder. Mix until the cashew+milkpowder+sugar mixture is smooth and lump-free.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 ASSEMBLING KAJU AND SUGAR MIXTURE Keep stirring for 8-10 minutes on the low heat setting until the mixture starts to come together like a thick dough. Keep scraping the sides of the pan. Mixing at this point will require some real muscle power.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 ASSEMBLING KAJU AND SUGAR MIXTURE PROTIP- Do not leave the cashew mix unattended at this time. Keep stirring. To check if the dough is done take some mixture in between your fingers and roll. It should come together like a non-sticky ball.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 ASSEMBLING KAJU AND SUGAR MIXTURE Transfer this hot cashew dough on to a parchment paper. The dough will be really hot, therefore, try to knead it with a spoon.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 ASSEMBLING KAJU AND SUGAR MIXTURE When comfortable to touch, knead the kaju dough with your hands until smooth.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 ASSEMBLING KAJU AND SUGAR MIXTURE Just remember the dough is still hot, so be extra careful while kneading. Take turns in between your hands and the spoon to knead a smooth kaju dough.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 FILLING Transfer all the ingredients gulkand, unsweetened desiccated coconut, assorted sliced nuts, raisins, and fennel seeds to a bowl and mix to combine. Set it aside.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 MAKING OF LADOOS Take a golf-ball-size piece from the dough. Roll it in between your palms until it forms a round shape.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 MAKING OF LADOOS Flatten the kaju dough.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 MAKING OF LADOOS Place a teaspoon of gulkand filling in the center and top it with a raisin. Bring all the ends together and seal the edges.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 MAKING OF LADOOS Gently roll the dough until it forms a smooth and crack-free ladoo. Make sure all the edges are sealed and secured.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 MAKING OF LADOOS Repeat the process until all the kaju dough and gulkand filling is used up.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 MAKING OF LADOOS With the help of a toothpick, stick the silver leaf (Chandi vark) over the balls.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 MAKING OF LADOOS Take a small bottle cover. Dip the cap in saffron thread paste and gently press down on top of the Kaju/cashew ladoos. That will form an orange ring on top of the ladoos.
c82a110e-6228-4104-bd24-dce5233215c3 MAKING OF LADOOS Insert sliced pistachio in the center of that orange ring, and your Kaju Gulkand ladoos are ready.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 MARINATE PANEER Cut paneer in little cubes (about 3/4-inch each). Feel free to cut any size you like long rectangle, or triangles.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 MARINATE PANEER Start by marinating paneer cubes. In a bowl, whisk the yogurt with a few spices. Always use hung curd (the thick kind) for marination.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 MARINATE PANEER Add in paneer cubes and toss to coat.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 MARINATE PANEER Place in refrigerator and marinate for at least 20 minutes.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 ONION-CASHEW SAUCE While the paneer is resting, lets make the first sauce: the onion-cashew sauce. For that, heat oil in a tawa/flat skillet. Add onions and cook for 3-4 minutes until slightly golden.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 ONION-CASHEW SAUCE Stir in raw cashews and cook for another 2-3 minutes.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 ONION-CASHEW SAUCE Once cooked, remove from heat and allow it to cool comfortably.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 ONION-CASHEW SAUCE Transfer the onion-cashew mix to a blender and blend until smooth. Set it aside.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE Heat ghee to the tawa.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE Add cumin seeds, green cardamom, and cloves.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE As the whole spices start to crackle, stir in the ginger-garlic paste. Cook for 1-2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE Add green chilies to the ginger-garlic paste.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE Stir in the chopped onions and mix.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE Cover and cook for 2-3 minutes or until the onions are translucent.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE Add tomato puree to the onions and mix to combine. Stir in all the spices. Feel free to use store-bought tomato puree to save some time.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE Cover and cook for another 3-4 minutes. By this time, your kitchen will be filled with an inviting aroma.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE Stir in the onion-cashew paste, the one that we had prepared earlier. Mix to combine.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE Stir in the cream and kasoori methi. Mix until blended. Allow it to simmer for 3-4 minutes until the oil leaves the pan.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE Time to drop in the marinated paneer cubes into this thick and creamy simmering sauce.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE Mix (gently) until paneer is smeared into this thick sauce. Cook for another 2-3 minutes until paneer soaks up all the richness from the curry.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE Garnish with chopped green scallions and cilantro leaves. Serve hot.
e258062b-7550-4d47-ba39-6fbdc2af3622 PREPARE THE BASE SAUCE This dish goes perfectly well with warm rotis and naan. But I personally relish it with tandooritandoori roti and plain rice.
fef1b3a1-0e48-4198-a9a6-810688522318
Before you begin, make sure all the ingredients are at room temperature. Let's start by preheating your oven to 350 degrees F and greasing a bundt pan.
fef1b3a1-0e48-4198-a9a6-810688522318
In a medium bowl sift together the all-purpose flour, baking powder, and salt. Set it aside. SAVE 1 TABLESPOON DRY MIX TO COAT THE BLUEBERRIES.
fef1b3a1-0e48-4198-a9a6-810688522318
Dust the blueberries with saved flour. This will prevent them from sinking to the bottom of the cake. Set aside.
fef1b3a1-0e48-4198-a9a6-810688522318
Next, in the bowl of your stand mixer cream butter and sugar for 3-4 minutes until light and fluffy. Mix in cream cheese and blend until well incorporated.
fef1b3a1-0e48-4198-a9a6-810688522318
Time to add your eggs one at a time. To avoid the eggy taste in cakes, add eggs one by one. Make sure the first one is blended well into the mix before the second one goes in. Lemon zest is next.
fef1b3a1-0e48-4198-a9a6-810688522318
Mix wet ingredients into dry ingredients until just combined.
fef1b3a1-0e48-4198-a9a6-810688522318
Now, fold in the berries (coated with flour in the previous step) into the cake batter. Be very careful with the blueberries. Fold gently. Because if you mix more they will start to bleed in the batter and you will end up with a purple blueberry cake.
fef1b3a1-0e48-4198-a9a6-810688522318
Transfer the cake batter to the pan and bake it at preheated oven (350 degrees F) for 45 minutes. Before placing the bundt pan in the oven, tap the cake pan on the counter couple of times this will pop all the bubbles and help in the rising of the cake.
fef1b3a1-0e48-4198-a9a6-810688522318
Bake for 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Every oven is different so start checking around 40 minutes.
fef1b3a1-0e48-4198-a9a6-810688522318
Transfer the baked cake on to a baking rack and allow it to cool for 15 minutes.
fef1b3a1-0e48-4198-a9a6-810688522318
Once cooled carefully remove from pan and cool completely. Cut a big slice and enjoy this super moist and deliciously yummy cake.
fef1b3a1-0e48-4198-a9a6-810688522318
For the lemon glaze: Sift 2 cups of powdered sugar into a bowl. Pour in 3-4 tablespoons of lemon juice and stir until the glaze is thin. Add more lemon juice to reach the desired consistency. Pour the glaze all over the cake and serve.
a18b560d-4f6d-4766-83bd-ac72ffe46254
Rinse sabudana under tap water until the water runs completely clear. Transfer the sabudana to a large bowl. Add 1 cup of water to sabudana. Just enough to cover them. Cover and allow it to rest for 4-5 hours.
a18b560d-4f6d-4766-83bd-ac72ffe46254
Turn the Instant Pot to Saute mode. Once it displays hot, add half and half to the insert. You can substitute rich and creamy half-and-half for full cream milk (whole milk).
a18b560d-4f6d-4766-83bd-ac72ffe46254
Bring it to a boil. Keep a watchful eye on the milk as it may boil over.
a18b560d-4f6d-4766-83bd-ac72ffe46254
When the milk comes to a full boil, stir in soaked sabudana pearls/tapioca pearls, sugar, and cardamom powder. Mix to combine.
a18b560d-4f6d-4766-83bd-ac72ffe46254
Turn the Instant Pot off.
a18b560d-4f6d-4766-83bd-ac72ffe46254
Close the lid and seal the pot. Press the Manual or pressure cook button and cook the Instant Pot Sabudna Kheer on High Pressure for 5 minutes with the pressure valve in sealing position.
a18b560d-4f6d-4766-83bd-ac72ffe46254
Once the cooking time has elapsed, turn off the pressure cooker. Allow the pressure to release naturally for 10 minutes, then do a quick pressure release.
a18b560d-4f6d-4766-83bd-ac72ffe46254
When the pin drops, carefully open the lid. Stir in the dry nuts and mix to combine. The kheer will look liquidy but do not add extra milk to the kheer as sabudana pearls will absorb quite a lot of milk and when cooled comfortably, (at room temperature) the kheer will thicken.
a18b560d-4f6d-4766-83bd-ac72ffe46254
Garnish with assorted nuts and serve.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 LENTIL PREPARATION Start with lentils first. Quickly sort through the lentils to make sure there are no dirty and gritty things in the lentils. Rinse the lentils well. Transfer the lentils to a bowl, cover with regular tap water, and leave to soak for 30 minutes.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 LENTIL PREPARATION Move on to the bottle gourd. Peel the bottle gourd skin and discard the stem (the top part). Wash the peeled bottle gourd and cut into squares. Set it aside.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 LENTIL PREPARATION Turn the Instant Pot to Saute mode. Once it displays hot, add oil to the insert. Add cumin seeds. As it starts to crackle, add chopped onions and ginger paste to the insert. Saute for 2-3 minutes.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 LENTIL PREPARATION Mix in tomatoes along with all the dried spices. Stir until everything is pretty well combined. Pour in a little water and scrape up the browned bits on the bottom of the insert to prevent a burn warning.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 LENTIL PREPARATION Drain the water from the soaked lentils and wash them again tap water. Add the soaked lentils to the insert. Pour in water and mix to combine. Add the chopped bottle gourd and mix.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 LENTIL PREPARATION Turn the Instant Pot off. Add the trivet in the Instant Pot insert. This will separate the lentils from rice that are also being cooked in the insert.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 RICE PREPARATION Rinse rice under tap water until the water runs completely clear.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 RICE PREPARATION Transfer rice to an insert Stackable pan, pour water, oil, and salt. Stir until combined. Rest the rice pan on the trivet.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 ASSEMBLE AND COOK Close the lid and seal the pot. Press the Manual or pressure cook button and cook the Instant Pot Lauki Chana Dal with Rice on High Pressure for 6 minutes with the pressure valve in sealing position.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 ASSEMBLE AND COOK Once the cooking time has elapsed, turn off the pressure cooker. Allow the pressure to release naturally for 10 minutes, then do a quick pressure release.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 ASSEMBLE AND COOK When the pin drops, carefully open the lid.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 ASSEMBLE AND COOK Fluff rice with a fork and use a silicone mitt to remove the rice dish from the Instant Pot carefully.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 ASSEMBLE AND COOK Carefully remove the hot insert from the Instant Pot. Turn the Instant Pot to Saute mode.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 ASSEMBLE AND COOK Feel free to add extra 1/2 cup to 3/4 cup of water to the lentils to match the consistency you like. Boil for 3-4 minutes and turn the Instant Pot off.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 ASSEMBLE AND COOK Finish off with lemon juice and cilantro leaves.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 ASSEMBLE AND COOK Serve hot with warm rice.
d4540835-1426-41b6-9452-fd42d97a35d5 ASSEMBLE AND COOK To read all about the health benefits and Faq's related to this recipe, please see the main post above.

Transfer the refried beans to a large mixing bowl. Add sour cream, taco seasoning, and salt. Whisk to combine.
2a6cd411-c095-4029-90d5-f6398c6353f3
OTHER OPTION: you can use yogurt instead of sour cream.
2a6cd411-c095-4029-90d5-f6398c6353f3
Transfer this mixture on to a serving tray or plate. This is the first layer.
2a6cd411-c095-4029-90d5-f6398c6353f3
Followed by-
2a6cd411-c095-4029-90d5-f6398c6353f3
a) Shredded lettuce.
2a6cd411-c095-4029-90d5-f6398c6353f3
b) the shredded cheese layer,
2a6cd411-c095-4029-90d5-f6398c6353f3
c) red bell peppers,
2a6cd411-c095-4029-90d5-f6398c6353f3
d) red onions,
2a6cd411-c095-4029-90d5-f6398c6353f3
e) scallions, and
2a6cd411-c095-4029-90d5-f6398c6353f3
f) black olives.
2a6cd411-c095-4029-90d5-f6398c6353f3
Time to chill the dip tray. Chilling the dip for an hour or more will enhance the flavors more.

Bring it out to the table and its time to dig in friends. Pair it with a bag of tortilla chips and watch it disappear!
1f48a214-b046-4719-bba2-f6166654d807
Preheat oven at 350 degrees F.
1f48a214-b046-4719-bba2-f6166654d807
Add the black beans, onion, parsley, garlic, lemon zest, nutritional yeast, and spices to food processor and pulse until all the ingredients are well blended.
1f48a214-b046-4719-bba2-f6166654d807
You may need to stop the food processor in between and scrape the sides of the bowl during the blending process.
1f48a214-b046-4719-bba2-f6166654d807
Transfer the black bean mixture to a mixing bowl.
1f48a214-b046-4719-bba2-f6166654d807
Stir in boiled quinoa along with 1 teaspoon of Corn Oil. Mix until combined.
1f48a214-b046-4719-bba2-f6166654d807
Do the taste test. If needed, adjust the seasonings at this point.
1f48a214-b046-4719-bba2-f6166654d807
Grease your hands with Corn Oil and shape the mixture into small discs.
1f48a214-b046-4719-bba2-f6166654d807
Chill the shaped falafels in the fridge for 30 minutes. This will intensify the flavor and adds depth to the falafel. Therefore, do not skip this step.
1f48a214-b046-4719-bba2-f6166654d807
After the resting time, arrange the falafels on a baking tray and bake in a preheated oven for 10-15 minutes until lightly brown and crisp around the edges, turning them halfway through cooking time.
1f48a214-b046-4719-bba2-f6166654d807
Remove from oven and serve the warm falafels alongside a rainbow salad and roasted bell pepper cashew cream sauce.
1f48a214-b046-4719-bba2-f6166654d807
For the roasted red bell pepper cashew cream sauce: toss all the ingredients from 'Cashews to Salt' to a food processor and pulse until smooth and creamy. Adjust the seasonings and serve.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
Turn Instant Pot to SAUTE mode. When the display reads Hot, add the minced chicken. Stir occasionally.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
Cook for 3-4 minutes or until you cant see any pink in the chicken.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
Add the onion, garlic and cook for a couple of minutes, until the onions turn translucent.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
Next add the diced tomatoes, followed by crushed tomatoes. Mix to combine. Make sure, to scrape the browned bits on the bottom of the insert to prevent a burn warning.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
Stir in the spices. Mix to combine. Pour in the chicken broth.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
Stir in the lasagna noodles. Gently mix the noodles. Turn the Instant pot Off.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
Secure the lid and seal the pot. Press the Manual (pressure cook) button and cook the soup on High Pressure for 5 minutes with the pressure valve in sealing position. It will take about 10-15 minutes for the pressure to build. After that, the countdown timer will start.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
Once the cooking time has elapsed, turn off the pressure cooker. Allow the pressure to release naturally for 10 minutes, then do a quick pressure release.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
When the pin drops, carefully open the lid and gently stir everything together.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
Adjust the seasonings, if needed. I prefer a thick soup but feel free to adjust the soup to the consistency you enjoy.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
Topping: In a separate bowl combine the shredded parmesan, mozzarella, and crushed red pepper flakes. Set it aside.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
Ladle the hot soup into a big bowl, sprinkle with some topping , add some fresh basil leaves and devour! Serve immediately. If allowed to sit for long, the lasagna noodles will absorb all the delicious soup.
37d10d0a-15cc-4d17-96fe-70c5eef2c0f1
To make it a complete meal, pair it with homemade garlic knots or focaccia bread.

b5ee97e1-b60e-4331-a167-a02c849ca500
Wash and clean the chicken. Cut it into roughly 1½ inch sized cubes and set aside.
b5ee97e1-b60e-4331-a167-a02c849ca500 PREPARE THE CURRY/BASE SAUCE Press the sauté button on the Instant Pot. Once it displays hot, add the oil to the insert.
b5ee97e1-b60e-4331-a167-a02c849ca500 PREPARE THE CURRY/BASE SAUCE Add cumin seeds, Bay leaves, and whole black cardamom. Sauté the whole spices for 40 seconds until they start omitting their aroma. Add the chopped onions.
b5ee97e1-b60e-4331-a167-a02c849ca500 PREPARE THE CURRY/BASE SAUCE Cook onions for a minute then add crushed ginger and crushed garlic to the insert. Sauté for 5 to 6 minutes until the onion is soft and translucent.
b5ee97e1-b60e-4331-a167-a02c849ca500 PREPARE THE CURRY/BASE SAUCE Pour in pureed tomatoes and cook for 3-4 minutes until the oil starts to separate. Add yogurt along with all the spices: coriander powder, red chili powder, garam masala powder, and salt.
b5ee97e1-b60e-4331-a167-a02c849ca500 PREPARE THE CURRY/BASE SAUCE Add kasoori methi or dried fenugreek leaves. Mix to combine. Sauté the yogurt and spices together for 3-4 minutes.
b5ee97e1-b60e-4331-a167-a02c849ca500 ASSEMBLING Add the chicken pieces and saute again for a minute. Pour in water and de-glaze the insert. Scrape the sides and bottom of the pot to make sure there is no masala/sauce stuck at the bottom of the pot.
b5ee97e1-b60e-4331-a167-a02c849ca500 ASSEMBLING Close the lid and seal the pot. Press the Manual or pressure cook button and cook the chicken curry on High Pressure for 4 minutes with the pressure valve in sealing position.
b5ee97e1-b60e-4331-a167-a02c849ca500 ASSEMBLING Once the pot beeps, allow the pressure to release naturally. When the pin drops, carefully open the lid. If the curry is thick, then feel free to add extra water to match the consistency you like. Feel free to remove the whole spices before serving.
b5ee97e1-b60e-4331-a167-a02c849ca500 ASSEMBLING Garnish with chopped cilantro leaves, a drizzle of cream (optional) and serve hot with white Basmati rice.
931f1550-15f7-44cb-a77b-81090c1a2715
Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F/ 180 degrees C.
931f1550-15f7-44cb-a77b-81090c1a2715
Lets prepare the Streusel topping first. To make a perfect crunchy topping, mix flour, sugar or brown sugar, cinnamon, and butter in a bowl. Mix until the mixture resembles a coarse and crumbly texture. Set it aside.
931f1550-15f7-44cb-a77b-81090c1a2715
In a bowl sift together the dry ingredients: flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt. Set it aside.
931f1550-15f7-44cb-a77b-81090c1a2715
In a separate bowl combine the wet ingredients: granulated sugar with vegetable oil. Mix until they are fully combined. Whisk in the egg and mix until combined.

931f1550-15f7-44cb-a77b-81090c1a2715
Time to add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients. Gently fold together. Stir until smooth.
931f1550-15f7-44cb-a77b-81090c1a2715
Dust blueberries with flour to avoid sinking. Carefully, fold in the blueberries into the batter. Mix to combine. Save some dusted blueberries to sprinkle on top.

Line the muffin tray with liners. Measure the batter into the lined muffin liners. Fill each cup 2/3 of the way up. Top with blueberries.

Generously sprinkle the streusel topping over the muffins.
931f1550-15f7-44cb-a77b-81090c1a2715
Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes or until the toothpick inserted comes out clean with no wet crumbs or batter.
931f1550-15f7-44cb-a77b-81090c1a2715
Remove from oven. Let the muffins cool in the muffin tray for 10 minutes before inverting. Enjoy!

If you are working with fresh corn, then the first step is to remove the corn kernels off the cob. Remove the husk and silk from the corn. Hold the corn from the ear/stem at an angle into a bowl. Take a sharp knife and carefully strip the kernels off the cob. Corn kernels will fall off in the bowl. Rotate the corn and repeat the same process on the other side.
d916852f-2178-46f9-8b07-eb1af60d1f11
Next step is to blanch the corn kernels in boiling water for 3-4 minutes and rinse immediately under cold water to stop the cooking process entirely. Allow it to cool.
d916852f-2178-46f9-8b07-eb1af60d1f11
Meanwhile, assemble rest of the ingredients. Wash and dice onions and bell peppers and transfer them to a bowl. Squeeze the juice out of a lime.
d916852f-2178-46f9-8b07-eb1af60d1f11
Add all the ingredients into the bowl blanched corn kernels, diced veggies, lime juice, and spices. Give it a quick stir and mix it well.
d916852f-2178-46f9-8b07-eb1af60d1f11
Allow the salsa to rest in the fridge for at least 2 hours for the flavors to mend and achieve a deeper and more complex flavor.
d916852f-2178-46f9-8b07-eb1af60d1f11
Serve with your favorite chips and enjoy!
