Add pineapple chunks, mango puree, coconut milk, pineapple juice, coconut sugar, and ice to a high-speed blender.
f617e8b9-6c9e-48e2-9af1-b88401ca7f28
Blend on high until smooth.
f617e8b9-6c9e-48e2-9af1-b88401ca7f28
Do the taste test and adjust sugar if needed. The amount of sugar can be adjusted depending on the sweetness of the pineapple.
f617e8b9-6c9e-48e2-9af1-b88401ca7f28
Pour into serving glasses, garnish with a fresh pineapple wedge and maraschino cherry and serve.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 PREPARE THE FILLING In a pan heat oil, add chana dal and saute for a minute. Add all the spices one by one..
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 PREPARE THE FILLING Mix in chickpea flour (besan) and saute for for 2-3 minutes till the flour is thoroughly cooked and is dark in color. Allow it to cool down completely.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 PREPARE THE OUTER LAYER Assemble all the ingredients for outer covering.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 PREPARE THE OUTER LAYER
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 PREPARE THE OUTER LAYER Wash and soak poha (thick rice flakes) for 2-3 minutes in cold water. After the desired time, drain the water. Make sure it is well drained.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 PREPARE THE OUTER LAYER Allow the poha (thick rice flakes) rest a while in the strainer until the excess water is drained through and the flakes feel dry.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 PREPARE THE OUTER LAYER Add poha (flattened rice) and mash it into the potato mixture .
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 PREPARE THE OUTER LAYER Knead the mashed potatoes like a dough, if it feels sticky add 1 teaspoon of rice flour and knead the mixture till it's smooth like a dough. If you opted to add rice flour to the potato mix then adjust seasonings.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 PREPARE THE OUTER LAYER Finish the dough with a teaspoon of oil.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 ASSEMBLING ALOO TIKKI Take some potato mixture in your hands and roll it like a ball.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 ASSEMBLING ALOO TIKKI Flatten this ball and add 1 tablespoon cooked lentil mixture in the center.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 ASSEMBLING ALOO TIKKI Bring all the sides together and secure the potato ball. Seal and pinch the ball in the center until it look like a big dough ball.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 ASSEMBLING ALOO TIKKI Gently flatten the ball. Repeat the process with rest of the dough and filling.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 TIME TO FRY OR PAN-COOK THE TIKKIS Heat and grease a pan, add tikkis to the hot pan.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 TIME TO FRY OR PAN-COOK THE TIKKIS Cook from one side and apply oil as needed.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 TIME TO FRY OR PAN-COOK THE TIKKIS Turn occasionally and brown them evenly on both sides. Once crisp and brown, remove and serve it hot with green chutney of your choice.
81cd7784-1db1-4094-9375-dec66e9e9b57 TIME TO FRY OR PAN-COOK THE TIKKIS If you choose to fry these tikkis, then heat oil in a pan. When hot, add tikkis and fry until golden brown. Transfer the fried tikkis on to a paper napkin and drain the excess oil. Top these aloo tikkis with your choice chutneys, curd, some chopped onions, chaat masala and enjoy it like a chaat!!

Remove the thawed puff pastry sheet from the refrigerator. (Read all about how to handle puff pastry sheets in the above post). Work with one sheet at a time and keep the unused sheet wrapped in a plastic bag and return it to the refrigerator.

Slice the dough log into even pieces and place on a greased baking dish.

Bake at 400 F degrees for 20 -22 minutes or until golden brown.

7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac CHOCOLATE GANACHE Start by making the chocolate ganache first. Combine melted chocolate and coconut cream in a large bowl.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac CHOCOLATE GANACHE Fold them together. Keep stirring until blended. Cover the bowl with a plastic wrap and chill in the refrigerate for 4-6 hours.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac CHOCOLATE GANACHE The ganache will firm up and become thick once cooled.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac CHOCOLATE CAKE Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Greased the 8-inch pan or 9×13-inch pan and set aside.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac CHOCOLATE CAKE In a mixing bowl, sift flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and mix well.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac CHOCOLATE CAKE In a separate bowl, combine non-dairy milk, water, oil, and vinegar. Whisk it well.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac CHOCOLATE CAKE Add the wet ingredients into dry and mix until the batter is smooth.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac CHOCOLATE CAKE Pour batter into the greased pan and bake for 45-50 minutes or until the inserted toothpick comes out clean.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac CHOCOLATE CAKE Allow the cake to sit for 5 minutes then start to poke holes all over the cake with a spoon. Make sure you make the holes while the cake is still hot.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac CHOCOLATE CAKE Warm dulce-de-leche in the microwave for 20 seconds. Stir to combine. Pour it all over the cake in such a way that it gets in all the holes and the cake is thoroughly drenched in dulce-de-leche. Gently, even out the filing with a spoon.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac CHOCOLATE CAKE After the filing, let the cake cool for 10-20 minutes while we prepare the chocolate ganache frosting and toasted coconut flakes.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac TOASTED COCONUT FLAKES Preheat oven to 300 degrees F. Spread coconut flakes on a baking sheet in a single layer and bake for 5-7 minutes.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac TOASTED COCONUT FLAKES Keep a watchful eye as the flakes will toast very quickly. Remove from oven and mix the flakes for an even color.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac WHIPPED CHOCOLATE GANACHE FROSTING Connect the paddle attachment to the stand mixer. Combine butter, salt, and chilled chocolate ganache in the stand mixer bowl. whip on medium to high speed for about 3-4 mins.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac WHIPPED CHOCOLATE GANACHE FROSTING Lower the speed to low and add the sifted powdered sugar. Mix on low speed until combined.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac WHIPPED CHOCOLATE GANACHE FROSTING Scrape the bottom and sides of the bowl and mix again on high speed for 2-3 mins until smooth and creamy.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac WHIPPED CHOCOLATE GANACHE FROSTING Since it contains coconut cream, the frosting will have a light and fluffy texture. Whipped chocolate ganache frosting is much sturdier than the whipped cream frosting. Salt is optional. But to bring out the flavor of the frosting, it is highly recommended.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac WHIPPED CHOCOLATE GANACHE FROSTING Spread this ganache frosting over the cooled cake and generously top with toasted coconut flakes. Cover with a plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac WHIPPED CHOCOLATE GANACHE FROSTING Now comes the finishing part: drizzle with melted chocolate and Maraschino cherries and enjoy!
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac VEGAN DULCE-DE-LECHE Whisk coconut milk, sugar, and salt in a heavy bottomed pan over medium heat. Stir to combine.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac VEGAN DULCE-DE-LECHE Boil until mixture on medium heat and keep stirring until it is reduced to half. This will take about 25-30 minutes.
7de0ecde-fa3b-4917-8454-6099eb52aeac VEGAN DULCE-DE-LECHE The mixture will become thick as it cools. Allow it to cool and then transfer the sauce to a canned jar. Chill entirely and use a directed. Can be made 2-3 days in advance.

e6f168bd-a631-4984-9553-b4c1952d8bef MAKING BATTER Drain all the water and wash the soaked and swelled up dal again for a couple of minutes.
e6f168bd-a631-4984-9553-b4c1952d8bef MAKING BATTER Strain it through a strainer and let all the water drain out. Make sure dal has no water left in it.
e6f168bd-a631-4984-9553-b4c1952d8bef MAKING BATTER Transfer it to a mixer/food processor. Ground it to a smooth paste. Add 1 teaspoon curd while grinding. PLEASE NOTE if the mixture is already too runny then leave the curd out.
e6f168bd-a631-4984-9553-b4c1952d8bef MAKING BATTER Transfer this dal mixture to a big bowl and add the green chilies, ginger paste, red chili powder, cumin seeds, hing, salt, and eno to this batter. Mix to combine.
e6f168bd-a631-4984-9553-b4c1952d8bef MAKING BATTER Just like a cake batter beat the mixture couple of times until its light and fluffy.
e6f168bd-a631-4984-9553-b4c1952d8bef MAKING BATTER The trick to soft and spongy vadas lies in beating the batter. Take a whisk or a beater and beat the batter for 3-4 minutes until light and airy.
e6f168bd-a631-4984-9553-b4c1952d8bef MAKING BATTER To check if the batter is light and fluffy drop some batter in cold water and if it keeps floating then the batter is perfect for vadas but if it sinks to the bottom of the bowl then it requires more beating. Once the batter is ready, lets move on to the next step.
e6f168bd-a631-4984-9553-b4c1952d8bef FRYING VADAS The traditional method would be to fry these vadas. Heat oil in a pan.
e6f168bd-a631-4984-9553-b4c1952d8bef FRYING VADAS For perfect shaped vadas use an ice scooper to scoop the batter into the hot oil. This will yield the same size of vadas each time.
e6f168bd-a631-4984-9553-b4c1952d8bef FRYING VADAS Fry the vadas until golden brown. Trim all the extras.
e6f168bd-a631-4984-9553-b4c1952d8bef FRYING VADAS Remove from oil and drain the vadas on a paper napkin.
e6f168bd-a631-4984-9553-b4c1952d8bef MAKING VADAS IN MICROWAVE Boil water in a pan, add a pinch of salt and add the vadas. Let it soak in hot water for 10-15 minutes.

9da0ccc6-d75a-42e3-9d40-14404763255e TIME TO ASSEMBLE Fold the triangle part of the crescent sheet over the cream cheese.
9da0ccc6-d75a-42e3-9d40-14404763255e TIME TO ASSEMBLE Carefully lift and tuck this part under the sheets.

55a6d71b-6530-4830-b892-a5de71403130 TOFU SCRAMBLE PREPARATION Crumble the pressed tofu into a medium bowl.
55a6d71b-6530-4830-b892-a5de71403130 TOFU SCRAMBLE PREPARATION TIP - to press tofu - wrap the tofu block in between a layer of paper towels. Apply steady weight to the tofu and squeeze out all the moisture from the block. Make sure there is no moisture in the tofu.

55a6d71b-6530-4830-b892-a5de71403130 TIME TO ASSEMBLE Trin the crusts off of the bread slices and flatten each slice with a rolling pin. Roll each slice gently with the rolling pin, do not make the slices to thin. (see pics above)
55a6d71b-6530-4830-b892-a5de71403130 TIME TO ASSEMBLE Take a slice and lay it flat on the plate. Apply a layer of green chutney, followed by spinach leaves.
55a6d71b-6530-4830-b892-a5de71403130 TIME TO ASSEMBLE Cover it with another layer of bread. Top this layer of bread with 2 tablespoons of tofu scramble. Spread it evenly across the bread slice. (see pics above)
55a6d71b-6530-4830-b892-a5de71403130 TIME TO ASSEMBLE Apply another layer of bread and gently press the whole stack.
55a6d71b-6530-4830-b892-a5de71403130 TIME TO ASSEMBLE Transfer this stock on a foil and gently roll the bread into a log. Wrap this log with a foil.
55a6d71b-6530-4830-b892-a5de71403130 TIME TO ASSEMBLE Repeat the process with rest of the bread and this recipe will make 6 logs.
55a6d71b-6530-4830-b892-a5de71403130 TIME TO ASSEMBLE Chill the logs in the refrigerator for 25 minutes. After the desired resting time, unwrap the logs and spread them in a single layer in the airfryer. Lightly spray oil all over your pinwheels.
55a6d71b-6530-4830-b892-a5de71403130 TIME TO ASSEMBLE Bake in the airfryer @ 350 degrees F for 8 minutes turning them halfway until crisp and brown. (see pics above)
55a6d71b-6530-4830-b892-a5de71403130 TIME TO ASSEMBLE Remove from oven and serve hot with tomato ketchup or dip of your choice.

04d9bf92-843a-488f-be30-81e8181894e8 FIRST METHOD - ROCK SOLID REWARI (JUST LIKE STORE BOUGHT) For a perfect outcome, cook sugar/jaggery to its right stage(between 255-260 degrees F). Do not rush through this step. If the syrup is not cooked well, then you will end up with a gooey syrup. It took me some time to master this technique.
04d9bf92-843a-488f-be30-81e8181894e8 FIRST METHOD - ROCK SOLID REWARI (JUST LIKE STORE BOUGHT) Repeat with rest of the dough. Homemade sugar rewari is ready. This is the traditional method.
04d9bf92-843a-488f-be30-81e8181894e8 SECOND METHOD WITHOUT CORN SYRUP - BRITTLE BUT NOT ROCK SOLID This method is equally good but it is not as rock solid like the traditional one. Combine water and sugar. Add eliachi powder.
04d9bf92-843a-488f-be30-81e8181894e8 SECOND METHOD WITHOUT CORN SYRUP - BRITTLE BUT NOT ROCK SOLID Add 1 teaspoon lemon juice or any acid to prevent crystallization. (read notes above). Add kewra essence and cook the syrup on a medium flame.
04d9bf92-843a-488f-be30-81e8181894e8 SECOND METHOD WITHOUT CORN SYRUP - BRITTLE BUT NOT ROCK SOLID Lower the flame and add roasted sesame seeds. Cook the mixture for 2-3 minutes.
04d9bf92-843a-488f-be30-81e8181894e8 SECOND METHOD WITHOUT CORN SYRUP - BRITTLE BUT NOT ROCK SOLID Remove from flame. Keep stirring the mixture. Soon the mix will become thick.
04d9bf92-843a-488f-be30-81e8181894e8 SECOND METHOD WITHOUT CORN SYRUP - BRITTLE BUT NOT ROCK SOLID When comfortable to touch, grease your hands with ghee and start shaping the dough.
04d9bf92-843a-488f-be30-81e8181894e8 FOR GUR REWARI WITHOUT CORN SYRUP To check its consistency drop few drops in water. If it forms a thick strand, the syrup is ready. For a perfect outcome, cook sugar/jaggery to its right stage, do not hurry through this step. If this step is not correct, you will end up with a gooey syrup.
04d9bf92-843a-488f-be30-81e8181894e8 FOR GUR REWARI WITHOUT CORN SYRUP Add roasted sesame seeds to the jaggery syrup. Mix it well. Cook the mix again for 2-3 minutes until the mixture starts to come together like a dough. Remove from heat and allow it to cool until comfortable to touch. Add sesame seeds.
04d9bf92-843a-488f-be30-81e8181894e8 FOR GUR REWARI WITHOUT CORN SYRUP Rewari can be stored for a longer time. A perfect after-meal treat that will keep the body warm during winters.

c2942060-6e95-4cf5-b7f2-98b05ebb26ec PREPARING MILK PEDA At this point check the sugar and adjust according to taste. If while kneading the dough feels sticky apply some ghee or butter to your hands and knead the dough.

c2942060-6e95-4cf5-b7f2-98b05ebb26ec PREPARING MILK PEDA Spread the dough on a clean surface. Use a cookie cutter or a small katori to make pedas.

I am using a stand mixer for making butter but a food processor or hand mixer will work just fine.
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
Pour heavy whipping cream to a large bowl.
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
Turn the mixer or hand blender to the lowest speed (setting #4) and start whipping the cream.
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
Within 2 minutes, the cream will start to get frothy and thicken up, it will form a soft peak. Depending on the speed, this step may take longer.
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
Increase the speed (setting #6) and start mixing again. For a food processor, use the highest setting.
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
Another 8-9 minutes of mixing (on setting#6) cream will start to curdle. Depending on the speed, this step may take longer.
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
If you have not attained this texture, please do not add ice cubes. Keep mixing until you achieve this texture.
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
Add ice cubes 2 at a time to the bowl and start mixing. Be careful, cover your mixer, as ice cubes will splash all around.
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
LOWER THE SPEED to setting #2 and mix. Keep adding ice in batches (2 at a time). For a food processor, use the Lowest setting.
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
Fat and liquid have separated.
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
End product.
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
Fat is the butter and
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
Rinse butter/fat under cold water to get rid of the buttermilk residue. Sieve and squeeze butter as tight as you can until all the traces of buttermilk is removed.
75bb7b6b-03c0-4475-b20e-b02362fa7ac6
This will prevent the butter from spoiling!! This recipe makes 1 cup of butter.

Rinse sama rice or barnyard millets thoroughly under running water. Transfer sama rice to a bowl and add enough water to soak the rice. Soak for 2 hours.
adf2154c-8507-44e1-be49-ce5818b0ca05
After the soak cycle is over, drain and transfer it to a food processor.
adf2154c-8507-44e1-be49-ce5818b0ca05
Add the rest of the ingredients coconut, yogurt, lemon juice, carrots, and spices into the food processor.
adf2154c-8507-44e1-be49-ce5818b0ca05
Pulse until smooth.
adf2154c-8507-44e1-be49-ce5818b0ca05
Heat water in a steamer pan. Lightly grease the idli molds.
adf2154c-8507-44e1-be49-ce5818b0ca05
Just before pouring the idli batter into the molds, add citric acid and ENO to the batter and whisk for 2-3 minutes until combined and frothy.
adf2154c-8507-44e1-be49-ce5818b0ca05
Spoon the sama rice batter into the greased idli molds.
adf2154c-8507-44e1-be49-ce5818b0ca05
Transfer the filled molds to the steamer pan, cover with the lid, and steam-cook for 6-7 minutes.
adf2154c-8507-44e1-be49-ce5818b0ca05
After the cooking time is over, insert the toothpick and check. The toothpick should come out clean.
adf2154c-8507-44e1-be49-ce5818b0ca05
Carefully remove the hot idli molds from the steamer pan. Allow it to cool for a few minutes. Use the back of the spoon to gently remove the idlis from each mold.
adf2154c-8507-44e1-be49-ce5818b0ca05
Serve hot with coconut chutney.
a6e4b613-0215-458e-8c90-4121ea24e73a MAKING BHALLAS Rinse sabudana under tap water until the water runs completely clear. Transfer the sabudana to a large bowl. Add water to sabudana. Just enough to cover them.
a6e4b613-0215-458e-8c90-4121ea24e73a MAKING BHALLAS Cover and leave it unattended for 3-5 hours.
a6e4b613-0215-458e-8c90-4121ea24e73a MAKING BHALLAS After the soak cycle is done, combine sabudana with boiled potatoes.
a6e4b613-0215-458e-8c90-4121ea24e73a MAKING BHALLAS Stir in Singhara flour, green chilies, cilantro, and spices.
a6e4b613-0215-458e-8c90-4121ea24e73a MAKING BHALLAS Mix well until evenly blended.
a6e4b613-0215-458e-8c90-4121ea24e73a MAKING BHALLAS Take a small ball of sabudana mixture. Flatten the ball and make it look like a tikki.
a6e4b613-0215-458e-8c90-4121ea24e73a MAKING BHALLAS Using your finger make an indent in the tikki. It will now look like a vada/bhalla.
a6e4b613-0215-458e-8c90-4121ea24e73a MAKING BHALLAS Carefully lift the vada and fry in hot oil until golden brown. Make sure the oil is not too hot. The trick is to cook in medium-hot oil until golden brown, occasionally turning with a slotted spoon.
a6e4b613-0215-458e-8c90-4121ea24e73a MAKING BHALLAS When done, remove the crispy vadas from hot oil with a slotted spoon and set aside to drain on kitchen paper. Repeat the process with rest of the dough until all the mixture is used up.
a6e4b613-0215-458e-8c90-4121ea24e73a ASSEMBLING BHALLAS Like regular bhallas, you dont have to soak vrat dahi bhallas in warm water. Combine yogurt, salt, and red chili powder in a large bowl. Whisk constantly until smooth and well blended.
a6e4b613-0215-458e-8c90-4121ea24e73a ASSEMBLING BHALLAS Dip all the bhallas in curd. Keep it in the fridge to cool.
a6e4b613-0215-458e-8c90-4121ea24e73a ASSEMBLING BHALLAS When ready to eat, transfer the bhallas to a plate. Pour extra yogurt on top. Garnish with red chili powder, vrat ki green chutney, and dried mint leaves. Enjoy!

Before you begin with the recipe, chill the mixing bowl and whisk in the refrigerator for 30 minutes. Or you can place it in the freezer for at least 10 minutes to chill. (see pics above)
7395c659-3fdd-4d77-942c-8215f437424d

7395c659-3fdd-4d77-942c-8215f437424d
Beat the beat cream on low speed for 1-2 minutes.
7395c659-3fdd-4d77-942c-8215f437424d

7395c659-3fdd-4d77-942c-8215f437424d
Once all the sugar has been added, the cream will have a smooth finish.
7395c659-3fdd-4d77-942c-8215f437424d
Add cornstarch to the cream and gradually increasing speed to high. Medium speed 4 to 6 on KitchenAid and Cuisinart stand mixer.

Heat ricotta cheese over medium-heat in a heavy-bottomed pan .
4ad5bedc-708d-4136-82db-a1759cdbda83
Stir continuously. Soon the cheese will start to melt and spread. Use a big spoon because the cheese will start to splatter as it starts to bubble.
4ad5bedc-708d-4136-82db-a1759cdbda83
Do not leave ricotta cheese unattended at any time as it burn quickly. Keep stirring until the moisture starts to evaporate.
4ad5bedc-708d-4136-82db-a1759cdbda83
Now add ghee to the pan and stir to combine. Soon the mixture will start to thicken and start to leave the sides of the pan.
4ad5bedc-708d-4136-82db-a1759cdbda83
Stir constantly, and soon the cheese will come together like dough. Take the mawa off the heat and transfer it to a clean bowl.
4ad5bedc-708d-4136-82db-a1759cdbda83
This unsweetened mawa can be used in just about any recipe ranging from sweet to savory.
4ad5bedc-708d-4136-82db-a1759cdbda83 MAKING MAWA 6 RICOTTA CHEESE MAWA IN MICROWAVE Grease a microwavable bowl. Add ricotta cheese to it.
4ad5bedc-708d-4136-82db-a1759cdbda83 MAKING MAWA 6 RICOTTA CHEESE MAWA IN MICROWAVE Microwave the cheese for 2 minutes on HIGH.
4ad5bedc-708d-4136-82db-a1759cdbda83 MAKING MAWA 6 RICOTTA CHEESE MAWA IN MICROWAVE Remove from the microwave. Ricotta cheese will look like a wet mix. Give it a good mix.
4ad5bedc-708d-4136-82db-a1759cdbda83 MAKING MAWA 6 RICOTTA CHEESE MAWA IN MICROWAVE Place the bowl back into the microwave and cook for another 2 minutes. Remove and stir.
4ad5bedc-708d-4136-82db-a1759cdbda83 MAKING MAWA 6 RICOTTA CHEESE MAWA IN MICROWAVE Repeat this process 3 more times, microwaving the cheese mixture for a total of 6 additonal minutes. Keep stirring at all times in between.
4ad5bedc-708d-4136-82db-a1759cdbda83 MAKING MAWA 6 RICOTTA CHEESE MAWA IN MICROWAVE By this time, all the moisture from the cheese should have evaporated, and the cheese inside the bowl will appear to resemble crumbs yet moist and soft to touch.
4ad5bedc-708d-4136-82db-a1759cdbda83 MAKING MAWA 6 RICOTTA CHEESE MAWA IN MICROWAVE Allow the mixture to cool comfortably. Now knead the mawa until smooth. You can use this danedar mawa in just about anything that calls for mawa.

Add eggs one at a time and wait till each egg is blended in the mixture and the mixture is frothy.

Eggs are the base of this cake kind of rising agent (that makes the cake rise) so mix it well.

3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 YEAST PREPARATION Assemble all the ingredients. For few seconds warm up milk, water, and sugar. Milk and water should be LUKEWARM and not warm. Take it off the flame and mix in the yeast.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 YEAST PREPARATION Whisk it well.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 YEAST PREPARATION Let it sit for 10 minutes. After 10 minutes it will look like a thick creamy paste. This proofing procedure shows that yeast is alive and active.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 YEAST PREPARATION If the yeast doesn't foam or bubble as shown in the pic, please discard the yeast and start over Do not continue with flat yeast as it will result in dense and sticky pav.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 KNEAD THE DOUGH In a bowl combine flour with salt and baking powder. Mix it well. Slowly and gradually add water/milk.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 KNEAD THE DOUGH PROTIP Do not add all the water at once. Add water as needed, you might not need all the water. If the dough doesn't bind, add an extra tablespoon of water.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 KNEAD THE DOUGH Time to add yeast.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 KNEAD THE DOUGH Add yeast and mix until combined.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 KNEAD THE DOUGH Add butter and oil to the flour. Mix until fully incoprporated.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 KNEAD THE DOUGH Knead the dough for 5-10 minutes.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 KNEAD THE DOUGH The dough should be smooth. Not sticky.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 KNEAD THE DOUGH Transfer the dough to a bowl. Cover the dough with a wet towel.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 KNEAD THE DOUGH And set it in a warm place for at least 1- 2 hours. The dough will double in size. The dough should be all airy and puffed up.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 KNEAD THE DOUGH Remove the dough from the bowl, dust it with some flour and start kneading the dough. This step is necessary if the dough is not kneaded well, pav will turn out dense. Dough elasticity and gluten formation are enhanced by kneading.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 ASSEMBLE PAV Divide the dough into equal parts. Form the dough into smooth circular shape.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 ASSEMBLE PAV Arrange the pavs in a greased tray.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 ASSEMBLE PAV Leave some space between each dough ball and provide them some room to spread as they rise.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 ASSEMBLE PAV Cover them with a wet towel and set it in a warm place for at least 30 minutes. Lift the wet towel to see them doubled in size.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 ASSEMBLE PAV The pav will double in size. If they are not doubled in the desired time- let the pav rise for another 30 minutes. Preheat oven at 400 degrees F.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 ASSEMBLE PAV Brush pavs with milk and Bake them in a preheated oven (400 degrees F) for 10 -15 minutes or until light brown from the top. It took me 12 minutes to lightly brown the pavs and a minute on BROIL 9which was closely monitored).
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 ASSEMBLE PAV Apply butter to the freshly baked pavs and it will soften the top.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 ASSEMBLE PAV Run a butter knife around the edges to loosen up the pavs. Run the knife a couple of times and make sure no sides are attached to the baking pan. This way, the pav will toss right out of the baking pan when inverted.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 ASSEMBLE PAV If the pavs are allowed to sit for long in the baking tray they will turn moist at the base due to heat condensation.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 ASSEMBLE PAV When pressed, the pavs will spring right back into it's shape.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 ASSEMBLE PAV Once you start making this recipe at home you will stop buying market buns easiest and tastiest bun recipe ever!!
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 PAV WITHOUT OVEN Add 1½ cups of sand at the bottom of a pan or pressure cooker. Place a strainer over the sand.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 PAV WITHOUT OVEN Grease a steel container. Arrange pavs in the greased container. Place pavs over the strainer
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 PAV WITHOUT OVEN After 30 minutes of total cooking well-cooked pavs. Carefully remove them from the pan.
3d7701e3-3591-4aae-9f2e-851d1a5e90b4 PAV WITHOUT OVEN Let it cool down completely and then run a knife across the pan to loosen the pavs. Flip it over. Brush with melted butter. Enjoy!! Beautifully crusted at the bottom and soft and velvety at the top.

Soak raw, roasted cashews for 2 hours.
38978601-cd84-40c4-99d1-28672b6927ae
Drain cashews and wash under cold water for few seconds. Transfer the cashews to a food processor and ground into a fine powder. If using unsoaked cashews (right off the refrigerator), soak it in warm water for 30- 40 minutes, before grinding.
38978601-cd84-40c4-99d1-28672b6927ae
Slowly add water to the granulated cashews and grind it to a fine paste.
38978601-cd84-40c4-99d1-28672b6927ae
If the mixture is grainy in texture, add some more water and keep grinding the cashews until you get the desired consistency smooth and creamy.
38978601-cd84-40c4-99d1-28672b6927ae
Store it in an airtight container and use as desired.

Thoroughly wash the chana dal and transfer it into a pressure cooker. Add 1.25 cups of water to it. Add salt along with turmeric powder. Cover the pressure cooker and set on the cooktop at a medium-high flame. Pressure cook the dal for 3 whistles.
78a394a2-fe94-497a-8400-826b59d2a11e
After the cooking time, take the pressure cooker off the flame. Allow the pressure to release naturally. Set it aside.
78a394a2-fe94-497a-8400-826b59d2a11e
Time to boil Lauki. Peel and wash lauki/bottle gourd. Cut into cubes.
78a394a2-fe94-497a-8400-826b59d2a11e
Transfer it to a pressure cooker and cook for 2 whistles.
78a394a2-fe94-497a-8400-826b59d2a11e
After the cooking time, take the pressure cooker off the flame. Allow the pressure to release naturally. Set it aside.
78a394a2-fe94-497a-8400-826b59d2a11e PREPARE THE TEMPERING/TADKA In a heavy-bottomed pan, heat ghee on a medium flame. Add cumin seeds and as it starts to splutter, add the chopped onions, garlic, and ginger. Saute for 2-3 minutes. Stir in the spices and mix to combine.
78a394a2-fe94-497a-8400-826b59d2a11e PREPARE THE TEMPERING/TADKA Cover the pan and cook the tempering on low heat for 2-3 minutes until the ghee starts to leave the pan.
78a394a2-fe94-497a-8400-826b59d2a11e PREPARE THE TEMPERING/TADKA Stir in the dal.
78a394a2-fe94-497a-8400-826b59d2a11e PREPARE THE TEMPERING/TADKA Mix well to combine.
78a394a2-fe94-497a-8400-826b59d2a11e PREPARE THE TEMPERING/TADKA Add boiled lauki/bottle gourd to the lentils. Once added, stir the lentils carefully so that the bottle gourd doesnt get mushy and disintegrates.
78a394a2-fe94-497a-8400-826b59d2a11e PREPARE THE TEMPERING/TADKA Feel free to add an extra 1/4 to 1/2 cup of water to the lentils to match the consistency you like. Do the taste test. Boil for 3-4 minutes and take it off the flame.

Use cashews that are at room temperature.
169d0d94-216d-404b-9c54-bb7d1308c827
Transfer cashews to a food processor. Blend until finely ground just like fine flour. Dont over-blend the cashews or it could turn into cashew butter. Sift the cashew powder through a sieve. Set it aside. PRO TIP Blend cashews batches and make sure that the cashew powder does not become a sticky powder. If it does then the cashews have released their oil and this will not work. You need to start all over again.
169d0d94-216d-404b-9c54-bb7d1308c827
Meanwhile, let's start with the sugar syrup. In a heavy-bottomed pan mix sugar and water as stated and set it to boil till it becomes thick and forms a 1- thread consistency. The temperature for 1-thread syrup is 112 degrees C.
169d0d94-216d-404b-9c54-bb7d1308c827
In this picture sugar syrup has reached its one thread consistency.
169d0d94-216d-404b-9c54-bb7d1308c827
Add cashew powder and milk powder to the hot sugar syrup. Keep stirring continuously until the mixture is well blended and lump-free. Soon the mixture will start to leave the corners of the pan and will form a thick ball. Take the pan off the flame.
169d0d94-216d-404b-9c54-bb7d1308c827
Allow it to cool until it is comfortable to touch. Once comfortably cooled and pliable, start kneading the mixture until it comes together like a soft dough. If the dough feels sticky, apply some ghee on your hand and work with the mixture. Spread the mixture in between two sheets of parchment paper. Using the rolling pin, flatten the kaju dough.
169d0d94-216d-404b-9c54-bb7d1308c827
Apply silver leaf (chandi ka varak) on top of the flattened kaju dough. Using a knife or a pizza cutter cut the dough into a diamond shape.
169d0d94-216d-404b-9c54-bb7d1308c827
Kaju katli is ready to serve.
169d0d94-216d-404b-9c54-bb7d1308c827
Store Kaju Katli at room temperature (in an airtight container). They will stay good for up to two weeks. This festive season, enjoy this nutty sweet delicacy!!
301f3606-1b44-4bdc-8067-85056e9b34a0
Measure Sabudana/sago/tapioca. Transfer it to a colander and wash under tap water until water runs clear.
301f3606-1b44-4bdc-8067-85056e9b34a0
Transfer sabudana to a large bowl and cover it with the same amount of water.
301f3606-1b44-4bdc-8067-85056e9b34a0
Remember just enough water to cover sabudana DO NOT DRENCH IT IN WATER OR YOU WILL END UP IN A GOOEY PASTE. Sabudana after 3 hours still some grains are hard.
301f3606-1b44-4bdc-8067-85056e9b34a0
Cover and let it sit undisturbed for 4 -5 hours. Total soaking time is 4-5 hours, above pictures shows how the pearls will look like after 3 hours. Depending on the grain you may need to soak it a little longer maybe another hour or so.
301f3606-1b44-4bdc-8067-85056e9b34a0
After 4-5 hours you will find perfectly puffed up sabudana pearls. All the water added gets soaked up by sabudana. But to be on the safe side, drain sabudana through a strainer to get rid of that starch.
301f3606-1b44-4bdc-8067-85056e9b34a0
There you have it perfectly puffed up sabudana pearls. Rub few beads in between your fingers, and if they get crushed easily. If they do then you are good to go.
301f3606-1b44-4bdc-8067-85056e9b34a0
You can make sabudana pearls in advance and store in an airtight container for future use. They can remain fresh for 2-3 days in your refrigerator.
301f3606-1b44-4bdc-8067-85056e9b34a0
Use as directed in your recipe.

Add chickpea flour (besan) to a large mixing bowl.
bb62e033-cf5d-4156-b008-f3e1861d720c
Add in all the other ingredients onions, fresh spinach leaves, carrots, red bell pepper, coriander leaves, cumin powder, salt, and pepper to the bowl. Mix well until combined.
bb62e033-cf5d-4156-b008-f3e1861d720c
Slowly pour in water, whisking all the time to make a smooth lump-free batter.
bb62e033-cf5d-4156-b008-f3e1861d720c
Before cooking, allow the besan puda batter to rest, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, heat the skillet.
bb62e033-cf5d-4156-b008-f3e1861d720c

bb62e033-cf5d-4156-b008-f3e1861d720c
Gently run a spatula under the besan cheela. Make sure it is not stuck to the pan and then flip it over.
bb62e033-cf5d-4156-b008-f3e1861d720c
Cook until the other side is lightly browned. Remove and serve. Repeat until all the batter is used.
bb62e033-cf5d-4156-b008-f3e1861d720c
Serve hot!

8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b KHAMAN DHOKLA PREPARATION In a large bowl add besan, sooji, hing, salt, and sugar. You can store this mix in an airtight container and when ready mix in the ingredients mentioned under "wet ingredients".
8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b KHAMAN DHOKLA PREPARATION De-seed green chilies. Using a motor pestle pound chilies and ginger to a fine paste. Add oil, citric acid, green chili + ginger paste, and salt. Add water and mix until well blended.
8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b KHAMAN DHOKLA PREPARATION PROTIP Beat the dhokla batter a couple of times to incorporate air into it. This will result in a fluffy and light dhokla. This has to be done before adding eno.
8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b KHAMAN DHOKLA PREPARATION Time to instantly ferment the batter by adding eno. Stir in eno and whisk until it is well blended. Wisk the batter in one direction either clockwise or anti-clockwise. The batter will become frothy, and double in size.
8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b KHAMAN DHOKLA PREPARATION PROTIP- Do not whisk after the batter has become frothy. The batter at this point should be of thick flowing consistency.
8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b KHAMAN DHOKLA PREPARATION Fill a large pan with water and place a trivet at the base. Instantly transfer the batter to a greased container. Place this container over the trivet.
8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b KHAMAN DHOKLA PREPARATION When the cooking time is up, carefully remove the khaman container from the steamer and set it on the counter.
8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b KHAMAN DHOKLA PREPARATION Insert a toothpick to check if khaman is properly cooked. It should come out clean. Allow it to cool for 10 minutes. Insert a knife around the edges to loosen up Khaman. Flip it over onto a plate.
8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b KHAMAN DHOKLA PREPARATION Perfectly steamed Khaman is ready for tempering. Using a sharp knife cut khaman into pieces. Dont press the knife down rather cut it the way we cut a cake. Holding a knife insert the pointy side of the knife first in the Khaman, lift it a little and again cut gently, keep repeating till all the pieces are cut. This way you will get perfect fluffy pieces.
8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b MICROWAVE DHOKLA Pour batter in a greased microwave bowl. Cook for 3-4 minutes (depending on the microwave, cooking times may vary). Carefully remove the dhokla from the bowl. Check for doneness Insert a toothpick, if the toothpick comes out with some batter, return it to the microwave and cook for another 30 seconds.
8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b MICROWAVE DHOKLA Allow it to cool. Cut into squares and prepare the tempering.
8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b FOR TEMPERING In a pan heat oil, add green chilies and let it crackle on a low flame. Add curry leaves and when they are crisp, add sugar, and water. Mix to combine.
8e1a94e9-3671-4b42-a62d-bfc9b8d8585b FOR TEMPERING Pour this hot mixture over steamed khaman. Enjoy this delicious and nutritious Gujarati snack with the chutney of your choice.

Clean butternut squash with a wet towel to remove dirt or grits. Poke holes in the squash.
3010c139-104c-450b-b247-e50412d0a28b
Microwave on HIGH for 3-4 minutes. Microwaving it will soften the skin and make it easy to peel.
3010c139-104c-450b-b247-e50412d0a28b
After 3 minutes, carefully remove squash from the microwave. Allow it to cool for 2-3 minute. Peel the outer layer. Slice the top and end off.
3010c139-104c-450b-b247-e50412d0a28b
Cut squash into the half. Using a spoon, remove seeds from the squash.
3010c139-104c-450b-b247-e50412d0a28b
Clean and chop petha (pumpkin).
3010c139-104c-450b-b247-e50412d0a28b
Heat ghee in a pan. Add the whole spices (dried whole chilies, Cinnamon, Whole black Cardamon, Cloves, star anise, Black peppercorns, and methi dana) to the pan. When the spices start to crackle add petha to the pan.
3010c139-104c-450b-b247-e50412d0a28b
Add all the dry spices at this time and mix to combine.
3010c139-104c-450b-b247-e50412d0a28b
Cover and cook for 10- 15 minutes or until petha becomes soft and watery. Depending on what type of a petha it is raw or ripped - the cooking process may vary.
3010c139-104c-450b-b247-e50412d0a28b
If you prefer your petha vegetable to be soft and chunky, then leave it as is. Avoid stirring the vegetable as the soften cubes may get crushed. Allow the excess water to evaporate. Do the taste test, add sugar, and mix. Garnish with cilantro leaves and enjoy.
3010c139-104c-450b-b247-e50412d0a28b
But if you like it crushed and mushy, then mash the soften petha cubes with a spoon.
3010c139-104c-450b-b247-e50412d0a28b
Petha sabzi is ready once all the excess liquid has evaporated.
3010c139-104c-450b-b247-e50412d0a28b
Garnish with fresh cilantro leaves and enjoy with puris or rotis.

Roughly chop the onions. Peel garlic pods and ginger. Transfer these ingredients to a food processor/blender. Pulse or blend until pureed.
5ae8f70a-c007-4ebb-884f-a4950cd73748
Heat oil in a pan. Add cumin seeds. When it starts to crackle
5ae8f70a-c007-4ebb-884f-a4950cd73748
Add onion, ginger, and garlic paste to the pan.
5ae8f70a-c007-4ebb-884f-a4950cd73748
Cook at a medium flame until the color changes from light purple to light brown. Do stir 3-4 minutes so that the paste doesnt burn or stick to the bottom of the pan. While the onion paste is cooking, wash and roughly chop tomatoes. Add it to a blender and blend until smooth and pureed. After 20-25 minutes of cooking, onions will change its color from light purple to pale brown.
5ae8f70a-c007-4ebb-884f-a4950cd73748
Stir in the pureed tomatoes and mix to combine.
5ae8f70a-c007-4ebb-884f-a4950cd73748
Cook for another 15-20 minutes until all the moisture has evaporated and oil starts to separate from the masala. Keep stirring in between (probably every 5 minutes or so).
5ae8f70a-c007-4ebb-884f-a4950cd73748
When you see a super-thin layer of oil bubbles popping at the edge of the masala, this means it is thoroughly cooked. At this point, the color of the masala will become deep red.
5ae8f70a-c007-4ebb-884f-a4950cd73748
Switch off the gas and allow it to cool. Store in an airtight container in your refrigerator. It freezes beautifully.
5ae8f70a-c007-4ebb-884f-a4950cd73748
If a recipe calls for onion, garlic, ginger, and tomatoes then use 1/4 -1/2 cup of cooked magic masala and voila you are all set, follow rest of your recipe and your meal will be on the table in no time.
